#. [side], type=Hannuk Tarkan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:97
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:166
msgid "Ughure"
msgstr "Ughure"

#. [unit], id=Houlagou, type=Hannuk Great Shaman
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:108
msgid "Houlagou"
msgstr "Houlagou"

#. [side], type=Hannuk Conqueror
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:126
msgid "Atyllan"
msgstr "Atyllan"

#. [side], type=Hannuk Conqueror
#. [side], type=Hannuk Tarkan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:131
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:148
msgid "Hannuk Clans"
msgstr "Clanes Hannuk"

#. [side], type=Hannuk Tarkan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:143
msgid "Rugar"
msgstr "Rugar"

#. [side], type=Hannuk Tarkan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:161
msgid "Mundzuk"
msgstr "Mundzuk"

#. [message], speaker=Rugar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:260
msgid "The dragons are coming! We're not prepared yet!"
msgstr "¡Vienen los dragones! ¡Aún no estamos preparados!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:264
msgid ""
"Get a hold of yourself! We have no choices but to defend Ughure until more "
"tribes answer to the Call!"
msgstr ""
"¡Contrólate! No tenemos más opción que defender Ughure hasta que más tribus "
"respondan a la Llamada!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:268
msgid "And in this, the Windsong and the Aragwaithi shall help!"
msgstr "¡Y en eso nos ayudarán las Hijas del Viento y los aragwaithi!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:272
msgid ""
"Chieftain Tarkyn is right, we have nowhere to go now... Hannuks, prepare for "
"a long, bloody and difficult-"
msgstr ""
"El jefe Tarkyn tiene razón, ahora no tenemos adónde ir… Hannuk, preparaos "
"para una larga, sangrienta y difícil…"

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:276
msgid ""
"(roaring) You point your sharp arrows towards us, steppe people; may I ask "
"you why?"
msgstr ""
"(rugiendo) Apuntáis vuestras afiladas flechas hacia nosotros, gente de la "
"estepa; ¿puedo preguntar por qué?"

#. [message], speaker=Houlagou
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:280
msgid ""
"Is that not obvious? You want to sweep us and take our lands, but know we "
"will not give them up without a brutal fight!"
msgstr ""
"¿No es obvio? Queréis barrernos y tomar nuestras tierras, pero sabed que no "
"las entregaremos sin una lucha brutal."

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:284
msgid "Heed me, horse-lovers, conquering your steppes was never my intention!"
msgstr ""
"¡Escuchadme, amantes de los caballos, conquistar vuestras estepas nunca fue "
"mi intención!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:288
msgid ""
"Do not insult our intelligence, dragon! Do you really think we would believe "
"this nonsense, when you come at the forefront of such army?"
msgstr ""
"¡No insultes nuestra inteligencia, dragón! ¿De verdad crees que nos "
"creeríamos esa tontería cuando vienes al frente de semejante ejército?"

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:292
msgid ""
"Not that I take pride in this, but the fact is that I need this army to "
"seize what I want, because what I want is under the possession of a very "
"dangerous person: this black-haired, green-eyed young woman who sits at one "
"of your keeps right now, the pesky Myra of Hiera'Shirsha!"
msgstr ""
"No es que me enorgullezca, pero lo cierto es que necesito este ejército para "
"apoderarme de lo que quiero, porque lo que quiero está en posesión de una "
"persona muy peligrosa: esta joven de pelo negro y ojos verdes que ahora está "
"en uno de vuestros torreones, ¡la molesta Myra de Hiera’Shirsha!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:296
msgid "What are you talking about, you bastard?"
msgstr "¿De qué estás hablando, maldito?"

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:300
msgid ""
"I'm talking about the soul of the Sky Dragon, which has been imprisoned "
"again by High Ascendant Maat, and which you now keep in your possession!"
msgstr ""
"¡Hablo del alma del Dragón del Cielo, que fue nuevamente aprisionada por la "
"Gran Ascendente Maat, ¡y que ahora tú guardas en tu posesión!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:304
msgid "*What?!*"
msgstr "¡¿Qué?!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:308
msgid ""
"You brainless dragon, the High Ascendant has destroyed your precious Sky "
"Dragon forever! Myra does not have his soul!"
msgstr ""
"¡Dragón sin cerebro, la Gran Ascendente destruyó para siempre a tu precioso "
"Dragón del Cielo! ¡Myra no tiene su alma!"

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:312
msgid ""
"Impudent boy, Svarballi cannot be destroyed by mere mortals, only bound! "
"Aahh, it seems that your trusted leader hasn't told you anything..."
msgstr ""
"Muchacho impertinente, ¡Svarballi no puede ser destruido por simples "
"mortales, solo puede ser atado! Aahh, parece que vuestra líder de confianza "
"no os ha contado nada…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:316
msgid ""
"(in rage) Accursed dragon, when will you tire of plaguing us? Why don't you "
"go back to Dragons' Land and LEAVE US IN PEACE?!"
msgstr ""
"¡(furiosa) Maldito dragón, ¿cuándo te cansarás de atormentarnos? ¿Por qué no "
"te vuelves a la Tierra de los Dragones y NOS DEJAS EN PAZ?!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:320
msgid ""
"It does not matter to us what he has done to you in the west; what matters "
"now is: does the dragon speak the truth? Do you have this... soul in your "
"possession?"
msgstr ""
"No nos importa lo que te haya hecho en el oeste; lo que importa ahora es: "
"¿dice la verdad el dragón? ¿Tienes tú… esa alma en tu posesión?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:324
msgid ""
"Of course I do! My foster-mother left it for me to guard, lest it will fall "
"in the wrong hands and..."
msgstr ""
"¡Claro que sí! Mi madre adoptiva me la dejó para que la guardara, no fuera a "
"caer en malas manos y…"

#. [message], speaker=Houlagou
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:328
msgid ""
"Ha! Now I see your real intentions, Aragwaithi: since your numbers have been "
"reduced, you wanted to make us fight your war. I should have expected it "
"from arrogant, hypocritical scum like you!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ja! Ahora veo vuestras verdaderas intenciones, aragwaithi: como vuestros "
"números se han reducido, queríais que nosotros lucháramos vuestra guerra. "
"¡Tendría que haberlo esperado de escoria arrogante e hipócrita como vosotros!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:332
msgid ""
"Great Shaman, this dragon that attacks Ughure now has caused much "
"devastation in the west with the sole intention of tyrannizing all free "
"peoples of this world, and has already destroyed and displaced many Hannuk "
"clans, will you really give heed to <i>him</i>?"
msgstr ""
"Gran Chamán, este dragón que ahora ataca Ughure ha causado mucha devastación "
"en el oeste con la única intención de tiranizar a todos los pueblos libres "
"de este mundo, y ya ha destruido y desplazado muchos clanes hannuk, ¿de "
"verdad vas a hacerle caso a <i>él</i>?"

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:336
msgid ""
"He may destroy the whole world, as long as he leaves the steppes in peace; "
"and, as I can now notice, he's only come here lured by this treacherous half-"
"breed. Great Shek'har, if we fight this Myra and help you retrieve this "
"artefact you so crave, do I have your word that you will not harm our lands?"
msgstr ""
"Puede destruir el mundo entero mientras deje en paz las estepas; y, como "
"ahora veo, solo ha venido aquí atraído por esta mestiza traidora. Gran "
"Shek’har, si luchamos contra esta Myra y te ayudamos a recuperar ese "
"artefacto que tanto deseas, ¿tienes tu palabra de que no tocarás nuestras "
"tierras?"

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:340
msgid ""
"Not only that, but I will also send you a great compensation for the tribes "
"I have regretfully harassed. We dragons live long, and we remember our oaths."
msgstr ""
"No solo eso, sino que también os enviaré una gran compensación por las "
"tribus a las que lamentablemente he acosado. Los dragones vivimos mucho "
"tiempo y recordamos nuestros juramentos."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:344
msgid "Disgraceful cowards! How can they side with those lizards?!"
msgstr "¡Cobardes sin honor! ¿Cómo pueden ponerse del lado de esos lagartos?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:348
msgid ""
"Hatred, Dvalin. They hate the Aragwaithi so much, that they will side with "
"anyone willing to destroy them, just like many Aragwaithi would have done to "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Odio, Dvalin. Odian tanto a los aragwaithi que se aliarán con cualquiera "
"dispuesto a destruirlos, igual que muchos aragwaithi habrían hecho con ellos."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:352
msgid ""
"That aside, how will we escape this situation? You're aware that we're "
"completely surrounded, aren't you?"
msgstr ""
"Dejando eso de lado, ¿cómo vamos a salir de esta? Te das cuenta de que "
"estamos completamente rodeados, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:356
msgid ""
"We should go east at full gallop. But we must defeat Rugar and Atyllan "
"first, or they'll harass our group all the way."
msgstr ""
"Deberíamos ir al este a todo galope. Pero primero debemos derrotar a Rugar y "
"Atyllan, o nos acosarán todo el camino."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:360
msgid "Let's do it then."
msgstr "Hagámoslo entonces."

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:368
msgid ""
"You were a great and renowned warrior once, Tarkyn. Was that Aragwaithi "
"woman so desirable that betraying your own people for her was worthwhile?"
msgstr ""
"En otro tiempo fuiste un guerrero grande y renombrado, Tarkyn. ¿Tan deseable "
"era esa mujer aragwaithi que valió la pena traicionar a tu propio pueblo por "
"ella?"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:372
msgid ""
"You wash your mouth before talking about her, you corrupt old man! You, who "
"take advantage of our wars to boost your popularity!"
msgstr ""
"¡Lávate la boca antes de hablar de ella, viejo corrupto! ¡Tú, que aprovechas "
"nuestras guerras para hinchar tu popularidad!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:376
msgid ""
"Don't heed his venomous words, Hannuks! Just kill off this traitorous weed "
"before it spreads all over the steppes!"
msgstr ""
"¡No hagáis caso a sus palabras venenosas, hannuk! ¡Acabad con esta mala "
"hierba traidora antes de que se extienda por toda la estepa!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:389
msgid ""
"The dirty traitors are almost reaching the Holy Island! We must not allow "
"their filth to defile our sacred ground!"
msgstr ""
"¡Los sucios traidores están a punto de llegar a la Isla Sagrada! ¡No podemos "
"permitir que su inmundicia profane nuestro suelo sagrado!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:399
msgid ""
"Forget him! Let's kill Atyllan and Rugar and flee this place once and for "
"all!"
msgstr ""
"¡Olvidadlo! ¡Matemos a Atyllan y Rugar y salgamos de este lugar de una vez "
"por todas!"

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:406
msgid ""
"Never ask a human to do a dragon's job... You may have killed their petty "
"horsemen, Myra, but will you manage to evade my Hurricanes?"
msgstr ""
"Nunca hay que pedirle a un humano que haga el trabajo de un dragón… Puede "
"que hayas matado a sus míseros jinetes, Myra, ¡pero podrás escapar de mis "
"Huracanes?"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:452
msgid "Oh no, that is bad, very bad!"
msgstr "¡Oh no, esto es malo, muy malo!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:456
msgid ""
"Even our swiftest horses cannot outride flying beings. I fear we won't be "
"able to escape..."
msgstr ""
"Ni siquiera nuestros caballos más rápidos pueden dejar atrás a seres "
"voladores. Me temo que no podremos escapar…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:460
msgid ""
"(trembling) M-maybe if we, I don't know, run into a nearby wood and try to "
"entangle the drakes amidst the trees..."
msgstr ""
"(temblando) T-tal vez si, no sé, corremos a un bosque cercano e intentamos "
"enredar a los dracos entre los árboles…"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:464
msgid ""
"I won't allow those stinking lizards to prevail after everything we have "
"suffered! Come, boys, let's dig a hole into those hills, and use the "
"corridor's narrowness to compensate our lesser numbers!"
msgstr ""
"¡No permitiré que esos lagartos apestosos triunfen después de todo lo que "
"hemos sufrido! ¡Venid, muchachos, cavemos un agujero en esas colinas y "
"usemos la estrechez del corredor para compensar que somos menos!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:468
msgid ""
"And meanwhile, I will keep them busy! They won't go through me before you "
"finish your job, even if both my arms are ripped off!"
msgstr ""
"¡Y mientras tanto, yo los entretendré! ¡No pasarán por encima de mí hasta "
"que terminéis vuestra tarea, aunque me arranquen los dos brazos!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:472
msgid ""
"*No, I can't... I won't see more friends of mine dying! Maybe I could use "
"its power... I now know its power can be channelled, but will I be able to "
"wield it without letting it go berserk...?*"
msgstr ""
"*No, no puedo… ¡No veré morir a más amigos míos! Tal vez podría usar su "
"poder… Ahora sé que su poder puede canalizarse, pero ¿seré capaz de "
"manejarlo sin que se descontrole…?*"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:476
msgid "Myra, could you make your earth elementals lend us some extra hands?"
msgstr "Myra, ¿podrías hacer que tus elementales de tierra nos echen una mano?"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:487
msgid "Myra? What are you doing?"
msgstr "¿Myra? ¿Qué estás haciendo?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:491
msgid "And do not get any closer to me! I know what I'm doing, trust me!"
msgstr "¡Y no os acerquéis más! ¡Sé lo que hago, confiad en mí!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:495
msgid "What the hell is she trying to do...?"
msgstr "¿Qué demonios está intentando hacer…?"

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:499
msgid ""
"It seems like she has noticed there is no escape, and seeks to parlay! Bold, "
"but useless; onwards, Hurricanes, and delay them while the Enforcers and "
"Blademasters catch up!"
msgstr ""
"Parece que se ha dado cuenta de que no hay escapatoria y busca parlamentar. "
"¡Valiente, pero inútil! ¡Adelante, Huracanes, retrasadlos mientras los "
"Ejecutores y Maestros de la Espada los alcanzan!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:503
msgid ""
"As the seasoned drakes charged at her, Myra unwrapped the large purple gem "
"she had kept hidden during all those months; a strange, fiery glitter "
"flickered on its irregular surface, and the young woman knew the power "
"inside it was anxious to explode. 'If being unleashed is what you want, I'll "
"comply' she said, and then she pointed the gem straight at Shek'har, and "
"unleashed the contained wrath of the Sky Dragon."
msgstr ""
"Mientras los dracos veteranos cargaban contra ella, Myra desveló la gran "
"gema púrpura que había mantenido oculta todos esos meses; un extraño brillo "
"ardiente centelleó en su superficie irregular y la joven supo que el poder "
"que contenía estaba ansioso por explotar. «Si lo que quieres es ser "
"liberado, lo haré», dijo, y apuntó la gema directamente a Shek’har, "
"liberando la ira contenida del Dragón del Cielo."

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:522
msgid "What... What is..."
msgstr "Qué… Qué es…"

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:532
msgid "N-o... It cannot... be hap-"
msgstr "N-no… No puede… estar pa-"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:564
msgid "MYRA!"
msgstr "¡MYRA!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:573
msgid "No... no, no, NO!"
msgstr "¡No… no, no, NO!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:577
msgid "W-what the hell has s-she just d-done...?"
msgstr "¿Q-qué demonios ha h-hecho…?"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:581
msgid ""
"I don't know, but she has given us an opportunity to escape. Quickly, pick "
"up her body gently and place it on my chariot, and let's flee this place "
"while the drakes and the Hannuk are still too stunned to react!"
msgstr ""
"No lo sé, pero nos ha dado una oportunidad para escapar. ¡Rápido, coged su "
"cuerpo con cuidado y ponedlo en mi carroza, y huyamos de este lugar mientras "
"los dracos y los hannuk siguen demasiado aturdidos para reaccionar!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:585
msgid "And I will keep this gem for now; we must examine it later, Akashia."
msgstr ""
"Y yo guardaré esta gema por ahora; tenemos que examinarla más tarde, Akashia."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:589
msgid ""
"By the Nine Hells we must! But now I... we must tend to Myra, her situation "
"is critical!"
msgstr ""
"¡Por los Nueve Infiernos que sí! ¡Pero ahora yo… nosotros tenemos que "
"atender a Myra, su estado es crítico!"

#. [message], speaker=Houlagou
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:615
msgid ""
"They are fleeing, Elder Shaman! I don't know how that girl did that, but she "
"has been knocked out, so we must make haste and chase them!"
msgstr ""
"¡Están huyendo, Gran Chamán! No sé cómo lo ha hecho esa chica, pero está "
"inconsciente, ¡así que debemos apresurarnos y perseguirlos!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:619
msgid "(stunned) No, let them... let them be."
msgstr "(atónito) No, dejadlos… dejadlos ir."

#. [message], speaker=Houlagou
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:623
msgid "But, Elder Shaman...!"
msgstr "¡Pero, Gran Chamán…!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:627
msgid ""
"I don't care about what you do now, just... don't go after that girl. "
"Haven't you felt it, Mundzuk? Haven't you felt the overwhelming evil that "
"emanated from that jewel? Haven't you noticed its sheer power? That girl "
"wields Death, and I wouldn't see it being unleashed on our people. No, let "
"them be, please..."
msgstr ""
"Me da igual lo que hagáis ahora, solo… no persigáis a esa chica. ¿No lo "
"habéis sentido, Mundzuk? ¿No habéis sentido el mal abrumador que emanaba de "
"ese rayo? ¿No habéis notado su poder absoluto? Esa chica maneja la Muerte, o "
"algo muy cercano a ella, y no quiero verla desatada sobre nuestro pueblo. "
"No, dejadlos ir, por favor…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:649
msgid "Now we must only defeat Rugar! Do not lose heart, warriors!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ahora solo tenemos que derrotar a Rugar! ¡No perdáis el ánimo, guerreros!"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:655
msgid "Defeat Rugar"
msgstr "Derrotar a Rugar"

#. [message], speaker=Ogatai
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:699
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:768
msgid ""
"How can this be? How can lowly traitors and dirty losers overcome two Hannuk "
"chieftains at the very heart of Ughure?"
msgstr ""
"¿Cómo puede ser esto? ¿Cómo pueden unos miserables traidores y perdedores "
"sucios vencer a dos jefes hannuk en el mismísimo corazón de Ughure?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:718
msgid "Now we must only defeat Atyllan! Do not lose heart, warriors!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ahora solo tenemos que derrotar a Atyllan! ¡No perdáis el ánimo, guerreros!"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:724
msgid "Defeat Atyllan"
msgstr "Derrotar a Atyllan"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:860
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:858
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:749
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:944
msgid "I can't fall, milady needs me..!"
msgstr "¡No puedo caer, mi señora me necesita…!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:874
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:872
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:958
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:504
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:957
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:657
msgid "No... Forgive me, my daughter..."
msgstr "No… Perdóname, hija mía…"

#. [message], speaker=Shek'har
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:886
msgid ""
"(roaring) I must confess these apes are tough... But even they will not be "
"able to resist my next attack!"
msgstr ""
"(rugiendo) Debo reconocer que estos monos son duros… ¡Pero ni siquiera ellos "
"podrán resistir mi próximo ataque!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/18_Besieged.cfg:890
msgid ""
"Damn it, Shek'har has called on massive reinforcements! We have no hope of "
"escaping this siege now..."
msgstr ""
"¡Maldición, Shek’har ha llamado refuerzos masivos! ¡Ya no tenemos esperanza "
"de escapar de este asedio!"

#. [scenario], id=19_Fires_Of_Hope
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:4
msgid "Fires of Hope"
msgstr "Fuegos de Esperanza"

#. [side], type=Drake Enforcer
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:106
msgid "Gakre Ohn"
msgstr "Gakre Ohn"

#. [side], type=Armageddon Drake
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:125
msgid "Egar"
msgstr "Egar"

#. [side]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:145
msgid "Sea Mercenaries"
msgstr "Mercenarios del Mar"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:197
msgid ""
"At long last, we've reached the Far East. Before us, stretching over the "
"horizon, there is the Stormy Ocean, and both to the south and to the north, "
"there is only a vast, uninhabited extension of plains."
msgstr ""
"Por fin hemos llegado al Lejano Oriente. Ante nosotros, extendiéndose hasta "
"el horizonte, está el Océano Tempestuoso, y tanto al sur como al norte solo "
"hay una vasta extensión de llanuras deshabitadas."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:201
msgid ""
"This will be a good place for us Hannuks to settle; we need vast level "
"regions to raise our horses."
msgstr ""
"Este será un buen lugar para que nos asentemos los hannuk; necesitamos "
"regiones llanas y amplias para criar nuestros caballos."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:205
msgid ""
"I have seen some hills on the way here. They're not like the Windy "
"Mountains, but they will serve for the time being, until we have dug a "
"tunnel to our kinsmen in the Far West."
msgstr ""
"He visto algunas colinas por el camino. No son como las Montañas Ventosas, "
"pero servirán por ahora, hasta que hayamos excavado un túnel hasta nuestros "
"parientes del Lejano Occidente."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:209
msgid ""
"You want to dig all the way to those realms?! My goodness, it will be one "
"big enterprise for you!"
msgstr ""
"¡¿Queréis excavar hasta esos reinos?! ¡Por todos los dioses, será una gran "
"empresa para vosotros!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:213
msgid "Pah, that's nothing we dwarves can't do."
msgstr "¡Bah, eso no es nada que nosotros los enanos no podamos hacer!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:217
msgid ""
"Certainly it isn't. When you finish it, will I have permission to cross it? "
"You know, I still want to see my home again."
msgstr ""
"Seguro que no. Cuando lo terminéis, ¿tendré permiso para cruzarlo? Sabes, "
"aún quiero volver a ver mi hogar."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:221
msgid ""
"Of course! Like we would leave such a beautiful damsel stuck this faraway "
"from her forests..."
msgstr ""
"¡Por supuesto! Como si fuéramos a dejar a una doncella tan hermosa atrapada "
"tan lejos de sus bosques…"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:245
msgid ""
"That can't be! Even with their king dead they insist on chasing us? Will we "
"have to exterminate every single one of them to have peace?!"
msgstr ""
"¡No puede ser! ¿Incluso con su rey muerto insisten en perseguirnos? "
"¿Tendremos que exterminarlos a todos para tener paz?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:249
msgid ""
"It seems like we will... I recognise the dragon leading them: Khrakrahs, son "
"of Shek'har. He's big, but not the brightest tactician, so we stand a chance "
"against him; and don't worry, Alenya, I won't use the Soul like I did in "
"Ughure."
msgstr ""
"Parece que sí… Reconozco al dragón que los lidera: Khrakrahs, hijo de "
"Shek’har. Es grande, pero no el estratega más brillante, así que tenemos una "
"oportunidad contra él; y no te preocupes, Alenya, no usaré el Alma como hice "
"en Ughure."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:253
msgid ""
"And what shall we do after defeating Khrakrahs? Because more dragons will "
"certainly come, and our forces are already depleted by the battles in the "
"steppes; how many more attack waves will we have to face?"
msgstr ""
"¿Y después de derrotar a Khrakrahs, ¿qué haremos? Porque seguro que vendrán "
"más dragones, y nuestras fuerzas ya están mermadas por las batallas en las "
"estepas; ¿cuántas oleadas de ataque más tendremos que soportar?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:262
msgid "If anyone has suggestions, I'm all ears."
msgstr "Si alguien tiene sugerencias, soy todo oídos."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:266
msgid "Erm... Have you ever heard of Netjer-Ta?"
msgstr "Eh… ¿Has oído hablar de Netjer-Ta?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:270
msgid "The name sounds vaguely familiar, but I don't recognise it."
msgstr "El nombre me suena vagamente, pero no lo reconozco."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:274
msgid ""
"It is a continent that lies on the other side of the world, which we can "
"reach by crossing the Stormy Ocean. It was explored by the Windsong in the "
"past, but hasn't been visited by any of us in ages. The scrolls tell that it "
"was mostly inhabited by wild beasts and small nations, though even so they "
"were quite dangerous."
msgstr ""
"Es un continente que está al otro lado del mundo, al que podemos llegar "
"cruzando el Océano Tempestuoso. Fue explorado por las Hijas del Viento en el "
"pasado, pero hace siglos que ninguno de nosotros lo ha visitado. Los "
"pergaminos cuentan que estaba habitado principalmente por bestias salvajes y "
"pequeñas naciones, aunque aun así eran bastante peligrosas."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:278
msgid "I doubt any monster can be more dangerous than dragons."
msgstr "Dudo que ningún monstruo pueda ser más peligroso que los dragones."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:282
msgid ""
"But, crossing this enormous ocean to colonise an unknown continent? Is it "
"really a good idea?"
msgstr ""
"Pero… ¿cruzar este océano enorme para colonizar un continente desconocido? "
"¿Es realmente buena idea?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:286
msgid ""
"Let's measure our options: we could stay here and face a certain, and very "
"serious danger at the hands of dragons, drakes, saurians and possibly "
"Hannuks, or we could go to this other continent and face a possible, but not "
"certain, danger..."
msgstr ""
"Veamos nuestras opciones: podemos quedarnos aquí y enfrentar un peligro "
"cierto y muy grave a manos de dragones, dracos, saurios y posiblemente "
"hannuk, o podemos ir a ese otro continente y enfrentar un peligro posible, "
"pero no seguro…"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:290
msgid ""
"Myra, know that, whichever path you choose, we Aragwaithi will follow you."
msgstr ""
"Myra, sabe que, elijas el camino que elijas, los aragwaithi te seguiremos."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:294
msgid "So will us Windsong!"
msgstr "¡Y nosotras las Hijas del Viento también!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:298
msgid "And the Hannuks!"
msgstr "¡Y los hannuk!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:302
msgid ""
"Och, we dwarves don't like the sea, but staying here will be useless, so "
"we're in as well!"
msgstr ""
"Och, a nosotros los enanos no nos gusta el mar, pero quedarnos aquí será "
"inútil, ¡así que también vamos!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:306
msgid ""
"Myra stared at each pair of eyes fixed on her, and felt her heart ache: she "
"had led them for so long, and had so far failed to give them a new and safe "
"land, as she had promised... The roar of the lizards echoed again, this time "
"closer, hastening her decision:"
msgstr ""
"Myra miró a cada par de ojos fijos en ella y sintió que se le encogía el "
"corazón: los había liderado durante tanto tiempo y hasta ahora había fallado "
"en darles una tierra nueva y segura, como había prometido… El rugido de los "
"lagartos resonó de nuevo, esta vez más cerca, apresurando su decisión:"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:310
msgid "Then to the east shall we go; to the land where the sun is born!"
msgstr "Entonces iremos al este; ¡a la tierra donde nace el sol!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:314
msgid ""
"In this case, we must start building ships immediately! We managed to "
"salvage the ship-building projects the Solariel elves gifted us from the "
"Library of Hiera'Shirsha, but we still need fine-quality wood..."
msgstr ""
"En ese caso, ¡debemos empezar a construir barcos inmediatamente! Por suerte "
"logramos salvar algunos planos de construcción naval de la Biblioteca de "
"Hiera’Shirsha, pero aún necesitamos madera de buena calidad…"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:318
msgid ""
"In this we can help. We use wood in nearly all of our tools and vehicles, so "
"we know well all kinds of tree in the realm."
msgstr ""
"En esto podemos ayudar. Usamos madera en casi todas nuestras herramientas y "
"vehículos, así que conocemos bien todos los tipos de árbol de la región."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:322
msgid "And our axes can chop them down in no time!"
msgstr "¡Y nuestros hachas pueden talarlos en un abrir y cerrar de ojos!"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:326
msgid "And our weavers can quickly fetch sails for the ships!"
msgstr ""
"¡Y nuestras tejedoras pueden conseguir velas para los barcos rápidamente!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:330
msgid ""
"Very well, we'll need every dwarf and every Hannuk chariot chopping down the "
"trees and bringing them here as quick as possible; the Aragwaithi women "
"shall make the sails, and I, the Windsong and the rest of the Hannuks and "
"the Aragwaith shall fight Khrakrahs' army. Now, move, people! While there's "
"still hope, we must not falter!"
msgstr ""
"Muy bien, necesitaremos a todos los enanos y todos los carros hannuk talando "
"árboles y trayéndolos aquí lo antes posible; las mujeres aragwaithi harán "
"las velas, y yo, las Hijas del Viento y el resto de hannuk y aragwaithi "
"lucharemos contra el ejército de Khrakrahs. ¡Ahora, moveos, gente! ¡Mientras "
"quede esperanza, no debemos flaquear!"

#. [message], speaker=Khrakrahs
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:334
msgid ""
"There they are, the disgusting, hairless apes who caused my father's "
"death... Strike them, Children of Morogor, and do not bother about taking "
"prisoners!"
msgstr ""
"Ahí están, los repugnantes monos sin pelo que causaron la muerte de mi "
"padre… ¡Atacadlos, Hijos de Morogor, y no os molestéis en hacer prisioneros!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:338
msgid ""
"(whispering) He talks about avenging his father only; apparently, he doesn't "
"know about the Soul's existence."
msgstr ""
"(susurrando) Solo habla de vengar a su padre; al parecer no sabe nada de la "
"existencia del Alma."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:342
msgid "So we don't need bother about being chased across the ocean."
msgstr ""
"Así que no tenemos que preocuparnos de que nos persigan al otro lado del "
"océano."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:346
msgid ""
"Because most of the dwarves and Hannuk charioteers are busy collecting wood, "
"Myra will not be able to recruit or recall any of axe-wielding dwarves or "
"the charioteers."
msgstr ""
"Debido a que la mayoría de los enanos y los aurigas hannuk están ocupados "
"recogiendo madera, Myra no podrá reclutar ni reincorporar enanos con hacha "
"ni aurigas."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:400
msgid ""
"We have the wood, now we must make the planks, the wheel, and whatever else "
"these vessels need..."
msgstr ""
"Tenemos la madera, ahora hay que hacer las tablas, las ruedas y todo lo que "
"necesiten estos barcos…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:404
msgid ""
"One of our sisters will guide your work, since you don't know how to make "
"ships."
msgstr ""
"Una de nuestras hermanas guiará vuestro trabajo, ya que no sabéis construir "
"barcos."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:408
msgid ""
"You may now recruit or recall Hannuk Charioteers and their advancements, but "
"the dwarves are still working."
msgstr ""
"Ahora puedes reclutar o reincorporar aurigas hannuk y sus avances, pero los "
"enanos siguen trabajando."

#. [unit], id=Ryujin, type=Merman Javelineer
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:428
msgid "Ryujin"
msgstr "Ryujin"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:434
msgid "Oh no, please don't tell me that's another enemy coming from the sea!"
msgstr "¡Oh no, por favor no me digáis que es otro enemigo que viene del mar!"

#. [message], speaker=Ryujin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:438
msgid ""
"My, my, we've got quite a commotion on this shore today... Come, warriors, "
"let the humans and those lizards settle their scores in peace, we shall "
"return to rest when they're done with each other."
msgstr ""
"Vaya, vaya, qué alboroto tenemos hoy en esta playa… Venid, guerreros, "
"dejemos que los humanos y esos lagartos arreglen sus cuentas en paz, "
"volveremos a descansar cuando terminen entre ellos."

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:442
msgid ""
"I don't think so, cousin, they're just passing by... Still, I wonder what "
"kind of creatures they are; I've never seen anything like them."
msgstr ""
"No lo creo, primo, solo están pasando de largo… Aun así, me pregunto qué "
"clase de criaturas serán; nunca he visto nada parecido."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:446
msgid ""
"I know those beings, they're merfolk! They're known for being quite "
"friendly, maybe they will help us... Wait! Er, listen, I know that we're "
"complete strangers to you, but could you please lend us a hand? We just want "
"to leave this land in peace, but these wicked drakes are seeking to "
"tyrannize us!"
msgstr ""
"Conozco a esos seres, ¡son sirenidos! Son conocidos por ser bastante "
"amistosos, quizá nos ayuden… ¡Espera! Eh, escuchad, sé que somos completos "
"desconocidos para vosotros, pero ¿podríais echarnos una mano? Solo queremos "
"abandonar esta tierra en paz, ¡pero estos malvados dracos buscan "
"tiranizarnos!"

#. [message], speaker=Ryujin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:450
msgid ""
"Um... I confess that I'm feeling inclined to help a pretty lady such as you, "
"but I'd like something more in return than a mere 'thank you' from your "
"enticing lips..."
msgstr ""
"Eh… Confieso que me inclino a ayudar a una dama tan hermosa como tú, pero me "
"gustaría algo más a cambio que un simple «gracias» de tus atractivos labios…"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:454
msgid ""
"(angry) Impudent fish-man, I will introduce you to my axe in an instant..."
msgstr "(enfadado) ¡Pez insolente, te presentaré a mi hacha en un instante…!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:458
msgid ""
"(whisper) Dvalin, wait! (normal voice) Noble merman, I hope you understand "
"that we're all respectable ladies, and that we can't..."
msgstr ""
"(susurro) ¡Dvalin, espera! (voz normal) Noble sirenido, espero que entiendas "
"que somos todas damas respetables y que no podemos…"

#. [message], speaker=Ryujin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:462
msgid ""
"(laughing) Oh, no, please don't think me such a base creature! I meant that "
"I will help you, if you give me 250 gold; being land-dwellers, you certainly "
"have lots of this precious metal that is inexistent in the vast seas."
msgstr ""
"(riendo) ¡Oh, no, por favor no me consideréis una criatura tan vulgar! "
"Quería decir que os ayudaré si me dais 250 piezas de oro; siendo habitantes "
"de la tierra, seguro tenéis mucho de ese precioso metal que no existe en los "
"vastos mares."

#. [option]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:479
msgid ""
"We too are short of gold, but spending it to secure our lives is no waste."
msgstr ""
"Nosotros también andamos escasos de oro, pero gastarlo para asegurar "
"nuestras vidas no es desperdicio."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:483
msgid "Deal! Come warriors, we've got a new job!"
msgstr "¡Trato hecho! ¡Vamos guerreros, tenemos un nuevo trabajo!"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:487
msgid ""
"Myra, are you sure that we can trust mercenaries? If the dragons make a "
"better offer, who can guarantee that these mermen won't promptly turn "
"against us?"
msgstr ""
"Myra, ¿estás segura de que podemos confiar en mercenarios? Si los dragones "
"hacen una oferta mejor, ¿quién garantiza que estos sirenidos no se volverán "
"contra nosotros de inmediato?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:491
msgid ""
"Worry not, Ravyan, treachery by the merfolk is something unheard of. "
"Besides, I don't really think that he wishes to see me broken-hearted..."
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes, Ravyan, la traición de los sirenidos es algo inaudito. "
"Además, no creo que él quiera verme con el corazón roto…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:495
msgid "Pfff, she's so full of herself..."
msgstr "Pfff, qué engreída es…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:499
msgid ""
"(smirks) What can I do if I'm irresistible even to those not of my own "
"people?"
msgstr ""
"(sonríe con suficiencia) ¿Qué puedo hacer si soy irresistible incluso para "
"los que no son de mi propia gente?"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:503
msgid "(blushing) Hrumph!"
msgstr "(se sonroja) ¡Hrumph!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:507
msgid "(giggles)"
msgstr "(ríe)"

#. [option]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:522
msgid "Are you joking? It is us who should be asking for gold!"
msgstr "¿Estás de broma? ¡Somos nosotros los que deberíamos pedir oro!"

#. [message], speaker=Ryujin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:526
msgid ""
"Um, that's a pity... Anyway, wish you luck fighting these monsters; by the "
"look of things, you'll need it..."
msgstr ""
"Eh, qué lástima… En fin, os deseo suerte luchando contra estos monstruos; "
"por lo que veo, la necesitaréis…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:537
msgid ""
"Seems like your pretty face is less worthy than a handful of gold, Alenya."
msgstr "Parece que tu cara bonita vale menos que un puñado de oro, Alenya."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:541
msgid ""
"(offended) Tsc, not everyone has enough taste to appreciate me as I "
"deserve..."
msgstr ""
"(ofendida) Tsc, no todos tienen suficiente gusto para apreciarme como "
"merezco…"

#. [message], speaker=Ryujin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:556
msgid "Argh! Maybe I should have stayed out of this..."
msgstr "¡Argh! Quizá debería haberme mantenido al margen…"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:565
msgid ""
"All right, the pieces are done, so now let's finally build those ships! And "
"Myra, it is a good idea to keep those lizards away from the building sites!"
msgstr ""
"¡Muy bien, las piezas están listas, así que ahora construyamos por fin esos "
"barcos! ¡Y Myra, es buena idea mantener a esos lagartos lejos de los lugares "
"de construcción!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:569
msgid "Right!"
msgstr "¡De acuerdo!"

#. [message], speaker=Khrakrahs
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:573
msgid ""
"These apes' refusal to die is starting to get on my nerves... Call in "
"reinforcements!"
msgstr ""
"¡La negativa de estos monos a morir empieza a ponerme de los nervios… Llamad "
"refuerzos!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:619
msgid ""
"Take this cursed overgrown lizard out of there before it burns the wood or "
"the sails!"
msgstr ""
"¡Sacad a este lagarto maldito y crecido de ahí antes de que queme la madera "
"o las velas!"

#. [message], speaker=Khrakrahs
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:628
msgid ""
"Are they... building ships? So they are trying to flee this continent, huh? "
"We'll see about that: more reinforcements!"
msgstr ""
"¿Están… construyendo barcos? ¿Entonces intentan huir de este continente, eh? "
"¡Ya veremos eso: más refuerzos!"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:699
msgid "(panting) We... have... finished... them..."
msgstr "(jadeando) Los… hemos… terminado…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:703
msgid ""
"Wonderful dwarves, what would we have done without you! (kisses dwarf on the "
"cheek)"
msgstr ""
"¡Maravillosos enanos, qué habríamos hecho sin vosotros! (besa al enano en la "
"mejilla)"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:707
msgid ""
"(blushing violently) Now onboard all of you, and let's leave this damn "
"lizard-ridden continent once and for all!"
msgstr ""
"(se sonroja intensamente) ¡Ahora todos a bordo y dejemos de una vez por "
"todas este maldito continente plagado de lagartos!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:711
msgid "You know, we Hannuks have worked hard too..."
msgstr "Sabéis, nosotros los hannuk también hemos trabajado duro…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:715
msgid "Then you too deserve congratulations! (kisses Tarkyn on the cheek)"
msgstr ""
"¡Entonces tú también mereces felicitaciones! (besa a Tarkyn en la mejilla)"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:719
msgid "Hey, leave my father alone, you elven witch!"
msgstr "¡Eh, deja a mi padre en paz, bruja elfa!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:723
msgid "You can pull each other's hair onboard, now we must leave this place!"
msgstr ""
"¡Podéis tiraros del pelo a bordo, ahora tenemos que abandonar este lugar!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:727
msgid ""
"Right... I will ask my old water elementals to cover us as we leave the "
"shores, and also to propel the ships."
msgstr ""
"De acuerdo entonces, perdonad… Pediré a mis viejos elementales de agua que "
"nos cubran mientras abandonamos la costa y que también impulsen los barcos."

#. [message], speaker=Ryujin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:736
msgid ""
"Farewell, o fair traveller! I wish I could take you through the vast blue "
"oceans myself, but alas, I have other duties."
msgstr ""
"¡Adiós, bella viajera! Ojalá pudiera llevarte yo mismo por los vastos "
"océanos azules, pero ay, tengo otros deberes."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:740
msgid ""
"Farewell, noble merman! I wish you the best of luck! (whisper) My, my, I "
"begin to wish we had him accompanying us through the seas... In all of my "
"travels, never have I seen such muscles..."
msgstr ""
"¡Adiós, noble sirenido! ¡Te deseo la mejor de las suertes! (susurra) Vaya, "
"vaya, empiezo a desear que nos acompañara por los mares… En todos mis "
"viajes, nunca había visto unos músculos así…"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:744
msgid "(upset) Hrumph!"
msgstr "(molesto) ¡Hrumph!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:748
msgid "(smiling) Ah, it will be an interesting travel..."
msgstr "(sonriendo) Ah, será un viaje interesante…"

#. [message], speaker=Khrakrahs
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:767
msgid ""
"No! Don't get close to those water freaks, their cold touch is lethal for "
"us! AND YOU, ACCURSED APES, MAY YOU SINK INTO OBLIVION BEFORE YOU REACH ANY "
"SAFE SHORE!"
msgstr ""
"¡No! ¡No os acerquéis a esos monstruos acuáticos, su toque frío es letal "
"para nosotros! ¡Y VOSOTROS, MONOS MALDITOS, QUE OS HUNDÁIS EN EL OLVIDO "
"ANTES DE LLEGAR A NINGUNA COSTA SEGURA!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/19_Fires_Of_Hope.cfg:771
msgid "Farewell for you too, lizards!"
msgstr "¡Adiós también para vosotros, lagartos!"

#. [scenario], id=20_Ring_Of_Fire
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:4
msgid "Ring of Fire"
msgstr "Anillo de Fuego"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:31
msgid "Explore the island"
msgstr "Explorar la isla"

#. [objective], condition=lose
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:55
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:567
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:27
msgid "Death of Atargatis"
msgstr "Muerte de Atargatis"

#. [objectives]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:65
msgid "HINT: hurry to the centre of the island"
msgstr "PISTA: apresuraos hacia el centro de la isla"

#. [side]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:99
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:30
msgid "Temple Guardians"
msgstr "Guardianes del Templo"

#. [side], type=Naga Myrmidon
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:114
msgid "Axmail"
msgstr "Axmail"

#. [side], type=Naga Myrmidon
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:119
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:139
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:162
msgid "Naga"
msgstr "Naga"

#. [side], type=Naga Myrmidon
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:133
msgid "Mila"
msgstr "Mila"

#. [side], type=Naga Myrmidon
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:156
msgid "Sassalia"
msgstr "Sassalia"

#. [side]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:180
msgid "Monsters"
msgstr "Monstruos"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:272
msgid ""
"Ah, it is truly great to feel solid, steady ground beneath your feet "
"again... Who knows, we may even settle on this island; it seems big enough "
"for our people, at least for now, and when we become numerous again, we may "
"search for Netjer-Ta, or maybe even return to our native continent and "
"conquer new lands there."
msgstr ""
"Ah, qué maravilla volver a sentir tierra firme y estable bajo los pies… "
"Quién sabe, quizá nos instalemos en esta isla; parece lo bastante grande "
"para nuestro pueblo, al menos por ahora, y cuando volvamos a ser numerosos "
"podemos buscar Netjer-Ta o incluso regresar a nuestro continente natal y "
"conquistar nuevas tierras allí."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:276
msgid ""
"Spoke my thoughts, friend! And look, there are lots of mountains here; we "
"dwarves could build many cities there, and who knows what treasures we may "
"find within them..."
msgstr ""
"¡Has dicho lo que pensaba, amigo! Y mira, hay muchas montañas aquí; nosotros "
"los enanos podríamos construir muchas ciudades allí, y quién sabe qué "
"tesoros podríamos encontrar dentro…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:291
msgid "Whoa, what was that?"
msgstr "¡Vaya, qué ha sido eso?"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:295
msgid "The mountain... is it roaring?!"
msgstr "¡La montaña… está rugiendo?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:299
msgid ""
"Look, there is fire pouring from its top! Oh no, is this the island the "
"drakes talked so much about, Morogor?"
msgstr ""
"¡Mirad, está saliendo fuego de la cima! ¡Oh no, es esta la isla de la que "
"tanto hablaban los dracos, Morogor?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:303
msgid "(laughing) Calm down, it's just a volcano! Haven't you ever seen one?"
msgstr "(riendo) Tranquilos, ¡es solo un volcán! ¿Nunca habéis visto uno?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:307
msgid "If I had, I'm sure I would remember!"
msgstr "¡Si lo hubiera visto, estoy segura de que lo recordaría!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:311
msgid ""
"I see, there were no volcanoes amidst the Windy Mountains... Anyway, it is "
"merely a mountain which spits fire and lava, which is simply molten rock. It "
"won't do us any harm, as long as we stay away from it."
msgstr ""
"Ya veo, no había volcanes entre las Montañas Ventosas… En fin, es "
"simplemente una montaña que escupe fuego y lava, que no es más que roca "
"fundida. No nos hará daño mientras nos mantengamos alejados."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:315
msgid ""
"And look, there are more mountains spitting fire! I don't want to sound "
"fearful or anything, but I don't think this is a good place to live in, not "
"if we are to be constantly haunted by the menace of these volcanoes..."
msgstr ""
"¡Y mirad, hay más montañas escupiendo fuego! No quiero parecer miedosa ni "
"nada, pero no creo que sea buen lugar para vivir si vamos a estar siempre "
"acechados por la amenaza de estos volcanes…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:319
msgid ""
"You're right, but I still want to explore this island. I sense something "
"beyond those volcanoes... I'm not certain about what it is, but I know it is "
"something I must see. Let's start exploring then; it seems like there is no "
"intelligent race here, or our ships would have been sighted, but we may "
"still come across dangerous monsters, so beware. And beware these volcanoes, "
"I really don't like them. And stop laughing, Alenya..."
msgstr ""
"Tienes razón, pero aún así quiero explorar esta isla. Siento algo más allá "
"de esos volcanes… No estoy segura de qué es, pero sé que tengo que verlo. "
"Empecemos a explorar entonces; parece que no hay ninguna raza inteligente "
"aquí, o habrían visto nuestros barcos, pero podemos encontrarnos con "
"monstruos peligrosos, así que tened cuidado. Y cuidado con esos volcanes, no "
"me gustan nada. Y deja de reírte, Alenya…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:475
msgid ""
"Look, a native! It is... quite big and hairy, but has arms and legs like a "
"human. I wonder whether he's friendly..."
msgstr ""
"Mirad, ¡un nativo! Es… bastante grande y peludo, pero tiene brazos y piernas "
"como un humano. Me pregunto si será amistoso…"

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:479
msgid "Rruarrllgg!"
msgstr "¡Rruarrllgg!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:483
msgid "Well, I think that answers your question, Akashia."
msgstr "Bueno, creo que eso responde a tu pregunta, Akashia."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:487
msgid ""
"As I had foreseen, there are dangerous beasts here. Have caution, but "
"please, kill as few of them as possible; after all, we're the intruders here."
msgstr ""
"Tal como preví, hay bestias peligrosas aquí. Tened cuidado, pero por favor "
"matad a las menos posibles; al fin y al cabo, nosotros somos los intrusos."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:502
msgid "Hisssss! Humanss in the foresst! Humanss in the foresst!"
msgstr "¡Hisssss! ¡Humanosss en el bosssque! ¡Humanosss en el bosssque!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:506
msgid "And there goes the surprise element..."
msgstr "Y adiós al factor sorpresa…"

#. [message], speaker=Axmail
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:510
msgid ""
"What? Humanss you ssaid? Darn it, as if fighting these disssgusting ape-"
"fishes and their sparkly tridents weren't enough, now we'll have to fight "
"these curssed land apesss! And what are they doing here anyway?"
msgstr ""
"¿Qué? ¿Humanosss dices? ¡Maldición, como si pelear contra esos asquerosos "
"pez-monos y sus brillantes tridentes no fuera suficiente, ahora también "
"tendremos que luchar contra estos malditosss monosss de tierra! ¿Y qué hacen "
"aquí de todos modos?"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:514
msgid ""
"Am I the only one who has noticed that we're always being attacked by "
"reptilian peoples? Seriously, what is wrong with these guys?"
msgstr ""
"¿Soy el único que se ha dado cuenta de que siempre nos atacan pueblos "
"reptilianos? En serio, ¿qué les pasa a estos tipos?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:518
msgid ""
"I don't like the idea of fighting someone who hasn't provoked us, but I will "
"not go back, not when I'm so close to finding out what lies on this island..."
msgstr ""
"No me gusta la idea de luchar contra alguien que no nos ha provocado, pero "
"no doy la vuelta, no cuando estoy tan cerca de descubrir qué hay en esta "
"isla…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:522
msgid ""
"Just say the direction we must turn our swords, milady, and leave the rest "
"to us!"
msgstr ""
"¡Solo di hacia dónde debemos girar nuestras espadas, mi señora, y déjanos el "
"resto a nosotros!"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:526
msgid ""
"(whisper in the distance) I sense an unknown presence newly-arrived on our "
"shores... But they don't seem hostile. Rather, their leader... Her soul... "
"Could it be...? My people, keep fighting the naga, but do not point your "
"tridents towards these new people..."
msgstr ""
"(susurro a lo lejos) Siento una presencia desconocida recién llegada a "
"nuestras costas… Pero no parecen hostiles. Más bien, su líder… Su alma… "
"¿Podría ser…? Pueblo mío, seguid luchando contra los naga, pero no apuntéis "
"vuestros tridentes a esta nueva gente…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:530
msgid "And what was that just now?"
msgstr "¿Y eso qué ha sido ahora?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:534
msgid ""
"She claims to sense our presence, but I can't even sense hers... She must be "
"a formidable sorceress indeed."
msgstr ""
"Dice que siente nuestra presencia, pero yo ni siquiera siento la suya… Debe "
"de ser una hechicera formidable de verdad."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:538
msgid ""
"I'm certain we'll meet her face-to-face soon enough; for now, let's help her "
"fight off the naga."
msgstr ""
"Estoy segura de que nos encontraremos cara a cara muy pronto; por ahora, "
"ayudémosla a rechazar a los naga."

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:543
msgid "Defeat the naga invaders"
msgstr "Derrotar a los invasores naga"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:584
msgid ""
"That was a long and tiring battle, but at last we will be able to rest. That "
"is, if these mermen let us stay here. Now, let's meet this mermaid "
"sorceress..."
msgstr ""
"Ha sido una batalla larga y agotadora, pero por fin podremos descansar. Eso "
"si estos sirenios nos dejan quedarnos aquí. Ahora, conozcamos a esta "
"hechicera sirenio…"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:588
msgid "Please, let me examine you..."
msgstr "Por favor, déjame examinarte…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:605
msgid "Wait! Back off, fish-woman!"
msgstr "¡Espera! ¡Atrás, mujer-pez!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:609
msgid "No, let her be, Akashia! I sense no hostility in her..."
msgstr "No, déjala, Akashia. ¡No siento hostilidad en ella!"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:618
msgid ""
"Fascinating... I wasn't mistaken, you do have a small bit of His soul within "
"your own... But, I wonder <i>how</i> you came to absorb it..."
msgstr ""
"Fascinante… No me equivoqué, sí tienes un pequeño fragmento de Su alma "
"dentro de la tuya… Pero me pregunto <i>cómo</i> llegaste a absorberla…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:622
msgid "His soul? Are you... talking about the High Dragon of Water, Nitiballi?"
msgstr "¿Su alma? ¿Estás… hablando del Gran Dragón del Agua, Nitiballi?"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:626
msgid ""
" (awestruck) So you do know him! I... you... (bows to Myra and kisses her "
"skirt)"
msgstr ""
" (asombrada) ¡Así que lo conoces! Yo… tú… (se inclina ante Myra y le besa la "
"falda)"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:636
msgid "Holy Guardian! Why are you doing this?"
msgstr "¡Santo Guardián! ¿Por qué haces esto?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:640
msgid ""
"Yes, I too want to know that! Come, stop doing that, you're embarrassing "
"me...!"
msgstr ""
"¡Sí, yo también quiero saberlo! Vamos, para ya, ¡me estás poniendo en "
"vergüenza…!"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:644
msgid ""
"This young human, my people, has been touched by the great Water God! And "
"now, as prophesised, she has returned to claim her rightful heirloom!"
msgstr ""
"¡Esta joven humana, pueblo mío, ha sido tocada por el gran Dios del Agua! ¡Y "
"ahora, como fue profetizado, ha regresado a reclamar su legítima herencia!"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:648
msgid "She is...! Quick, you fools, show her your respect!"
msgstr "¡Ella es…! ¡Rápido, necios, mostradle vuestro respeto!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:652
msgid "My, my, you truly are one charismatic woman, aren't you, Myra?"
msgstr "Vaya, vaya, de verdad eres una mujer carismática, ¿eh, Myra?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:656
msgid ""
"All right, now this is definitely getting weird. Sorceress, listen: I am "
"Myra of Hiera'Shirsha, leader of the Windsong and of the Aragwaithi and "
"Hannuk refugees, and if you esteem me so much, you will tell me why you are "
"treating me like that, who this Water God is, and what this ‘rightful "
"heirloom' is. And, if that is not asking too much, I'd like to ask "
"permission to bring my people into this island, for they're tired after so "
"many days travelling amidst a storm."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, ahora sí que esto se está poniendo raro. Hechicera, escucha: soy Myra "
"de Hiera’Shirsha, líder de las Hijas del Viento y de los refugiados "
"aragwaithi y hannuk, y si tanto me estimas, me vas a contar por qué me "
"tratas así, quién es ese Dios del Agua y qué es esa «legítima herencia». Y, "
"si no es pedir demasiado, me gustaría pedir permiso para traer a mi pueblo a "
"esta isla, porque están cansados tras tantos días viajando en medio de una "
"tormenta."

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:660
msgid ""
"Of course, of course! My name is Atargatis Stella Maris, the Guardian of the "
"Water God Sanctum, and I say bring your folk here, where the trees will "
"shelter them from the rain, and where we shall give them food to replenish "
"their strength! And meanwhile, come with me to my abode, the Underwater "
"Temple; your friends, however, I must ask to wait here."
msgstr ""
"¡Claro, claro! Me llamo Atargatis Stella Maris, Guardiana del Santuario del "
"Dios del Agua, y digo que traigáis a vuestro pueblo aquí, donde los árboles "
"los protegerán de la lluvia y donde les daremos comida para que recuperen "
"fuerzas. Y mientras tanto, ven conmigo a mi morada, el Templo Submarino; a "
"tus amigos, sin embargo, debo pedirles que esperen aquí."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:664
msgid "Why can't we go with her? I don't like it, girl, I think we should..."
msgstr ""
"¿Por qué no podemos ir con ella? No me gusta, muchacha, creo que deberíamos…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:668
msgid ""
"Friends, please stay here, and watch over our people. I'll be fine by "
"myself, I'm not a little girl anymore. And Atargatis, I don't know whether "
"you're aware of that, but I can't breath underwater..."
msgstr ""
"Amigos, por favor quedaos aquí y vigilad a nuestra gente. Estaré bien sola, "
"ya no soy una niña pequeña. Y Atargatis, no sé si eres consciente, pero no "
"puedo respirar bajo el agua…"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:672
msgid ""
"Worry not, for the Temple's interior is full of air; we, the merfolk, may "
"live under the sea, but we too need air to survive. Now, hold onto me, that "
"I shall take you to where your heirloom awaits!"
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes, el interior del Templo está lleno de aire; nosotros, los "
"sirenios, vivimos bajo el mar, pero también necesitamos aire para "
"sobrevivir. Ahora, agárrate a mí, que te llevaré hasta donde te espera tu "
"herencia."

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:767
msgid ""
"The Holy Guardian is dead! This is a disaster! Merfolk, abandon this island "
"and retreat to the Aquamarine Fortress!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ha muerto la Santa Guardiana! ¡Es un desastre! ¡Sirenios, abandonad esta "
"isla y retrocedamos a la Fortaleza Aguamarina!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/20_Ring_Of_Fire.cfg:771
msgid ""
"The naga have taken over this island! We won't be able to stay here now, and "
"our warriors are too tired to fight that many enemies; what will we do "
"now...?"
msgstr ""
"¡Los naga han tomado la isla! No podremos quedarnos aquí ahora, y nuestros "
"guerreros están demasiado cansados para luchar contra tantos enemigos; ¿qué "
"haremos ahora…?"

#. [scenario], id=21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:4
msgid "The Will of the Naiad"
msgstr "La Voluntad de la Náyade"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:19
msgid "Find the chamber where the Trident of the Seas is hidden"
msgstr "Encuentra la cámara donde está oculto el Tridente de los Mares"

#. [side]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:58
msgid "Underwater Guardians"
msgstr "Guardianes Submarinos"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:128
msgid ""
"Yes, I feel it now... His presence... Nearly as strong as in the Fountain of "
"Life; it's as if Nitiballi himself was actually here..."
msgstr ""
"Sí, lo siento ahora… Su presencia… Casi tan fuerte como en la Fuente de la "
"Vida; es como si Nitiballi estuviera realmente aquí…"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:132
msgid ""
"This is the system of caves we know as the Heart of the Ocean; the "
"Underwater Temple was actually the 'guest room' of Nitiballi, where he "
"received his subjects, but this was where he actually dwelled, and so his "
"presence here is much stronger. Besides, this is where the Trident is."
msgstr ""
"Este es el sistema de cuevas que conocemos como el Corazón del Océano; el "
"Templo Submarino era en realidad la «sala de invitados» de Nitiballi, donde "
"recibía a sus súbditos, pero aquí es donde realmente vivía, por eso su "
"presencia es mucho más fuerte. Además, aquí es donde está el Tridente."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:136
msgid "And I must search it, right?"
msgstr "¿Y tengo que buscarlo, verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:140
msgid ""
"Please, don't misunderstand me, Myra. <i>You have a right</i> over it, but "
"you may leave it here, should you wish."
msgstr ""
"Por favor, no me malinterpretes, Myra. <i>Tú tienes derecho</i> sobre él, "
"pero puedes dejarlo aquí si así lo deseas."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:144
msgid ""
"I have to say, now I think this trident would be very useful. I'm currently "
"after a new land for my people, and this Trident would be useful if we're to "
"go on sailing the Stormy Ocean. But I'm also afraid you'll be weaker without "
"it..."
msgstr ""
"Admito que me gustaría tenerlo; en este momento busco una nueva tierra para "
"mi pueblo, y el Tridente sería muy útil si vamos a seguir navegando el "
"Océano Tempestuoso. Pero también me preocupa que quedéis más débiles sin él…"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:148
msgid ""
"Do not worry about us; we have survived for aeons without using the Trident "
"for ourselves. Besides, we own our own special weapons, which we call "
"Tridents of the Storm, and which, albeit much weaker than the original one, "
"have the advantage of being available to any merman."
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes por nosotros; hemos sobrevivido eones sin usar el Tridente "
"para nosotros mismos. Además, tenemos nuestras propias armas especiales, que "
"llamamos Tridentes de la Tormenta y que, aunque mucho más débiles que el "
"original, tienen la ventaja de que cualquier sirenio puede usarlas."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:152
msgid "If that is so, then I shall reclaim this 'heirloom'..."
msgstr "Si es así, entonces reclamaré esta «herencia»…"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:156
msgid ""
"As you wish. I will lead you to the chamber where it is hidden, but only you "
"may enter it. Ah, I forgot to tell: because of an ancient event in which a "
"Guardian (oh, shame!) tried to take the Trident for herself, we've placed "
"some obstacles here. They're mostly monsters, but there is also an "
"enchantment that nullifies any other spell used here. In other words, you "
"may not summon any of your elemental beasts. However, you may find some "
"ancient water elementals dwelling here; they will certainly follow the "
"chosen of Nitiballi."
msgstr ""
"De acuerdo. Te llevaré hasta la cámara donde está oculto, pero solo tú "
"puedes entrar. Ah, olvidé decirlo: por un antiguo incidente en que una "
"Guardiana (¡qué vergüenza!) intentó quedarse con el Tridente, hemos puesto "
"algunos obstáculos. Son sobre todo monstruos, pero también hay un "
"encantamiento que anula cualquier otro hechizo aquí. En otras palabras, no "
"podrás invocar a tus bestias elementales. Sin embargo, puedes encontrar "
"algunos antiguos elementales de agua que viven aquí; sin duda seguirán a la "
"elegida de Nitiballi."

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:180
msgid ""
"Just as I said, there are water elementals dwelling here that will gladly "
"escort you to where the trident is."
msgstr ""
"Como dije, hay elementales de agua viven aquí y te escoltarán encantados "
"hasta el tridente."

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:264
msgid ""
"Finally! Plunge into this maelstrom, Myra, and you will end in the chamber "
"where the Trident is hidden."
msgstr ""
"¡Por fin! Sumérgete en este remolino, Myra, y llegarás a la cámara donde "
"está oculto el Tridente."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:268
msgid "But... How will I return from this chamber? Is there any way out of it?"
msgstr "Pero… ¿cómo volveré de esa cámara? ¿Hay alguna salida?"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:272
msgid ""
"After you seize the Trident, deep water shall no longer be a frontier to "
"you. Now, go! I will wait for you here."
msgstr ""
"Una vez que tengas el Tridente, las aguas profundas ya no serán una frontera "
"para ti. ¡Ahora ve! Te esperaré aquí."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:311
msgid ""
"Ooofff! Air, air, blessed air... I think Atargatis has no idea of how hard "
"it is for humans to hold their breath underwater... Well, at least I have "
"reached this chamber; I sense this is exactly the place I was supposed to "
"find..."
msgstr ""
"¡Ufff! Aire, aire, bendito aire… Creo que Atargatis no tiene ni idea de lo "
"difícil que es para los humanos aguantar la respiración bajo el agua… Bueno, "
"al menos he llegado a esta cámara; siento que es exactamente el lugar que "
"debía encontrar…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:325
msgid ""
"The Trident! What a formidable artefact... even without touching it I can "
"feel its power; not even the Rod of Justice was like that... Now, I suppose "
"I must take it; I just hope it doesn't burn me, like the Rod does with "
"unworthy wielders..."
msgstr ""
"¡El Tridente! Qué artefacto tan formidable… incluso sin tocarlo ya siento su "
"poder; ni siquiera la Vara de la Justicia era así… Ahora supongo que debo "
"cogerlo; solo espero que no me queme, como hace la Vara con quien no es "
"digno…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:351
msgid ""
"What... what is that... I feel... I can't let go of the Trident...! What is "
"happening..."
msgstr ""
"Qué… qué es esto… siento… ¡no puedo soltar el Tridente…! ¿Qué está pasando…?"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:361
msgid "Calm down, my child. You shall not be hurt here."
msgstr "Tranquila, hija mía. Aquí no te haré daño."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:365
msgid ""
"Are you... the spirits of nature again? No, you feel different, you feel "
"like... coming from within me... You...!"
msgstr ""
"¿Eres… los espíritus de la naturaleza otra vez? No, te sientes distinto, "
"siento como si… vinieras de dentro de mí… ¡Tú…!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:370
msgid ""
"Yes; I am Nitiballi, or better, I am a small remnant of myself, one that was "
"lingering in my crystallized body in the Fountain, and consequently the "
"source of its lasting powers. "
msgstr ""
"Sí; soy Nitiballi, o mejor dicho, soy un pequeño resto de mí mismo que quedó "
"en mi cuerpo cristalizado de la Fuente y que, por tanto, es la fuente de sus "
"poderes duraderos."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:374
msgid ""
"But... I've never managed to talk to you; is it because I am in this place "
"that I'm doing it now, just like I managed to talk with nature's spirits at "
"the Fountain?"
msgstr ""
"Pero… nunca había logrado hablar contigo; ¿es porque estoy en este lugar que "
"lo consigo ahora, igual que hablé con los espíritus de la naturaleza en la "
"Fuente?"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:379
msgid ""
"Yes. I am your guardian spirit, bound to you just as any spirit of the Raw "
"is bound to common Windsong Weavers; however, in my current state I was too "
"weak to communicate with you other than through mere insights. But now I may "
"draw upon the energy that impregnates this place, and thus talk to you."
msgstr ""
"Sí. Soy tu espíritu guardián, ligado a ti como cualquier espíritu del Raw a "
"las tejedoras comunes de las Hijas del Viento; sin embargo, en mi estado "
"actual era demasiado débil para comunicarme contigo más allá de simples "
"intuiciones. Pero ahora puedo aprovechar la energía que impregna este lugar "
"y hablarte."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:383
msgid ""
"So that is why you brought me to your island. But what do you want to tell "
"me?"
msgstr "Entonces por eso me trajiste a tu isla. Pero ¿qué quieres decirme?"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:388
msgid ""
"You may ignore it, but I cannot: I sense that the constant influence of the "
"Sky Soul is affecting your power's development. I could have nullified "
"Svarballi's malice, and thus you'd be able to carry that jewel with you "
"forever and unaffected by it, but I was too weak for that. Thus, as we "
"crossed the ocean, I decided to lead you here, to my former home, and find "
"the trident I forged long ago."
msgstr ""
"Tú puedes ignorarlo, pero yo no: siento que la influencia constante del Alma "
"del Cielo está afectando el desarrollo de tu poder. Podría haber anulado la "
"malicia de Svarballi y así podrías llevar esa joya contigo para siempre sin "
"que te afectara, pero era demasiado débil para eso. Por eso, mientras "
"cruzábamos el océano, decidí guiarte hasta aquí, a mi antiguo hogar, y "
"encontrar el tridente que forjé hace tanto."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:392
msgid ""
"And once with the Trident, which is impregnated with your power, you'd get "
"stronger, right?"
msgstr ""
"Y una vez con el Tridente, que está impregnado de tu poder, te harías más "
"fuerte, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:397
msgid ""
"Precisely. As long as you have this artefact, I will draw upon its energy, "
"and counter the effect of the Soul's evil."
msgstr ""
"Exacto. Mientras tengas este artefacto, yo tomaré su energía y "
"contrarrestaré el efecto del mal del Alma."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:402
msgid ""
"There is also something else I wanted to do. I want to teach you some of my "
"own knowledge, and awaken your true power; for you are going to a savage "
"continent, plagued by dangers even I do not comprehend well."
msgstr ""
"También hay otra cosa que quería hacer. Quiero enseñarte parte de mi propio "
"conocimiento y despertar tu verdadero poder; porque vas a un continente "
"salvaje, plagado de peligros que ni siquiera yo comprendo bien."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:406
msgid ""
"Then I'm taking my people to the wrong place! Maybe I should just stay here, "
"and..."
msgstr ""
"¡Entonces estoy llevando a mi gente al lugar equivocado! Tal vez debería "
"quedarme aquí, y…"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:411
msgid ""
"Trust me, this island is much more dangerous. If the dragons find you again, "
"you will have nowhere to run. Besides, the volcanoes that encircle this "
"island often cover it entirely in lava; the merfolk only manage to survive "
"here because they live underwater. No, you must go to the continent you call "
"Netjer-Ta; as you said yourself, the possibility of danger is still not as "
"bad as the certainty of one."
msgstr ""
"Confía en mí, esta isla es mucho más peligrosa. Si los dragones te "
"encuentran de nuevo, no tendrás dónde huir. Además, los volcanes que rodean "
"esta isla muchas veces la cubren por completo de lava; los sirenios solo "
"sobreviven aquí porque viven bajo el agua. No, debes ir al continente que "
"llamas Netjer-Ta; como tú misma dijiste, la posibilidad de peligro aún no es "
"tan mala como la certeza de uno."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:415
msgid ""
"I understand... Now, I think this Trident belongs to me, right? Should we "
"return to surface?"
msgstr ""
"Entiendo… Ahora, creo que este Tridente me pertenece, ¿verdad? ¿Volvemos a "
"la superficie?"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:420
msgid ""
"Not yet. Now, I wish to begin your training. It will not take long: I will "
"just purge the Soul's evil that has already infected you, and then 'give a "
"push' to your power, to help it grow again. Be warned, though, that it may "
"hurt; having your soul purged is never a nice experience."
msgstr ""
"Todavía no. Ahora quiero empezar tu entrenamiento. No llevará mucho: solo "
"purgaré el mal del Alma que ya te ha infectado y luego «daré un empujón» a "
"tu poder para que vuelva a crecer. Pero te aviso, puede doler; purgar un "
"alma nunca es agradable."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:424
msgid "Bring it..."
msgstr "Adelante…"

#. [message], speaker=Atargatis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad.cfg:461
msgid ""
"How can I, the Holy Guardian, die at the temple I'm supposed to guard...?"
msgstr ""
"¿Cómo puedo yo, el Guardián Sagrado, morir en el templo que debo proteger…?"

#. [scenario], id=21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:4
msgid "The Will of the Naiad, part 2"
msgstr "La Voluntad de la Náyade, parte 2"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:92
msgid "Come on, Myra, why are you taking so much time to return...?"
msgstr "Vamos, Myra, ¿por qué tardas tanto en volver…?"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:96
msgid ""
"(whispering) I told ye, these fish-men can't be trusted. They're "
"treacherous, just like the sea! That is why we dwarves keep away from them "
"both."
msgstr ""
"(susurrando) Ya te lo dije, a estos hombres-pez no se les puede confiar. "
"¡Son traicioneros, como el mar! ¡Por eso nosotros los enanos nos mantenemos "
"lejos de ambos!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:100
msgid ""
"I don't think the mermen would trick us like that, but I too begin to worry "
"about her. It's been hours since she dived with Atargatis, and we haven't "
"received a word from them..."
msgstr ""
"No creo que los sirenidos nos engañen así, pero yo también empiezo a "
"preocuparme por ella. Han pasado horas desde que se sumergió con Atargatis y "
"no hemos tenido noticias…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:104
msgid ""
"You know what? I may have grown in the Meadows, but I'm a good swimmer. I am "
"going down there and find this Underwater Temple..."
msgstr ""
"¿Sabéis qué? Puede que haya crecido en los Prados, pero soy buen nadador. "
"¡Voy a bajar ahí y encontraré ese Templo Submarino…!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:108
msgid ""
"Wait for me, Jevyan! I too have had enough of just sitting here, I'm going "
"with you!"
msgstr ""
"¡Espera, Jevyan! ¡Yo también estoy harta de quedarme aquí sentada, voy "
"contigo!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:112
msgid ""
"Wait... Sit down, both of you! I think... No, I am sensing Myra returning! "
"But..."
msgstr ""
"¡Esperad… Sentad, los dos! Creo… No, ¡siento que Myra está volviendo! Pero…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:116
msgid "But what?"
msgstr "¿Pero qué?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:120
msgid ""
"There is something... different... about her. Not a bad thing, though, "
"actually it's quite the opposite..."
msgstr ""
"Hay algo… diferente… en ella. No es algo malo, de hecho es todo lo contrario…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:124
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/utils/intros.cfg:226
msgid "What do you mean?"
msgstr "¿Qué quieres decir?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:128
msgid "She's... overflowing with power..."
msgstr "Está… rebosante de poder…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:216
msgid "Myra, you..."
msgstr "Myra, tú…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:220
msgid "What has happened to you?!"
msgstr "¡¿Qué te ha pasado?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/21_The_Will_Of_The_Naiad_b.cfg:224
msgid ""
"Worry not, friends, for I haven't felt so well in ages. I'll explain "
"everything later, but now I want to feast, that I haven't felt so hungry in "
"ages either!"
msgstr ""
"No os preocupéis, amigos, porque no me había sentido tan bien en años. Os lo "
"explicaré todo después, ¡pero ahora quiero comer, que tampoco tenía tanta "
"hambre en años!"

#. [scenario], id=22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:4
msgid "Where the Sun is Born"
msgstr "Donde Nace el Sol"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:23
msgid "Explore the New Continent"
msgstr "Explorar el Nuevo Continente"

#. [side]
#. [side], type=Minotaur Executioner
#. [side], type=Minotaur Elder
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:91
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:132
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:79
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:147
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/27_The_Rise_Of_MaatKare.cfg:92
msgid "Minotaurs"
msgstr "Minotauros"

#. [side]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:107
msgid "Carapaces"
msgstr "Carapaces"

#. [side]
#. [side], type=Orcish Warlord
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:127
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:90
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/28_Embers_Of_War.cfg:72
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:60
msgid "Uldrol"
msgstr "Uldrol"

#. [side]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:143
msgid "Hagash's Hordes"
msgstr "Hordas de Hagash"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:229
msgid ""
"Let the civilians play on the beach, they deserve it. As for us, we must "
"scout the region. I hope we are able to spend our first night in this new "
"land here, but if we find too many enemies around, we'll have to stay on the "
"ships. Akashia, do the scrolls have anything to say about this region in "
"particular?"
msgstr ""
"Dejad que los civiles jueguen en la playa, se lo merecen. En cuanto a "
"nosotros, debemos explorar la región. Espero que podamos pasar nuestra "
"primera noche en esta nueva tierra aquí, pero si encontramos demasiados "
"enemigos alrededor, tendremos que quedarnos en los barcos. Akashia, ¿los "
"pergaminos dicen algo sobre esta región en particular?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:233
msgid ""
"Well, the old maps claim this coast was uninhabited in the past, but that "
"means nothing; who knows what may have been built here in the meantime."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, los mapas antiguos dicen que esta costa estaba deshabitada en el "
"pasado, pero eso no significa nada; quién sabe qué se habrá construido aquí "
"mientras tanto."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:237
msgid ""
"But, even if we stay here this night, where will we go afterwards? You must "
"build a provisory settlement here, and explore further inland before "
"building our first settlement."
msgstr ""
"Pero, aunque nos quedemos aquí esta noche, ¿adónde iremos después? Debes "
"construir un asentamiento provisional aquí y explorar más hacia el interior "
"antes de construir nuestro primer asentamiento."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:241
msgid "Are you lecturing me?"
msgstr "¿Me estás dando lecciones?"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:245
msgid ""
"Yes; don't go around thinking that just because you started walking with "
"this huge trident I will treat you differently."
msgstr ""
"Sí; no vayas por ahí pensando que solo porque empezaste a caminar con este "
"enorme tridente voy a tratarte diferente."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:249
msgid ""
"(chuckling) Right... Well, you're right on this, father. In our first days "
"in this new land, we'll have to count on the Hannuks' nomad knowledge to "
"survive, until we find a fertile and safe area to build our first village."
msgstr ""
"(riendo) De acuerdo… Bueno, tienes razón en eso, padre. En nuestros primeros "
"días en esta nueva tierra, tendremos que contar con el conocimiento nómada "
"de los hannuk para sobrevivir, hasta que encontremos un área fértil y segura "
"para construir nuestro primer pueblo."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:253
msgid "First? How many do you intend on building?"
msgstr "¿Primero? ¿Cuántos pretendes construir?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:257
msgid ""
"In our lifetime, two, maybe three; and I want to live long enough to see at "
"least one of them becoming a thriving city. But let's leave the future for "
"later; now we must concentrate on exploring the region."
msgstr ""
"En nuestra vida, dos, quizá tres; y quiero vivir lo suficiente para ver al "
"menos una de ellas convertirse en una ciudad próspera. Pero dejemos el "
"futuro para después; ahora debemos concentrarnos en explorar la región."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:261
msgid ""
"Myra may now recruit elementals again. Additionally, the Trident's power "
"enables her to recruit Undines."
msgstr ""
"Myra ya puede reclutar elementales otra vez. Además, el poder del Tridente "
"le permite reclutar undinas."

#. [unit], id=Labrys, type=Minotaur Overlord
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:280
msgid "Labrys"
msgstr "Labrys"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:292
msgid ""
"You know, I kind of expected a new world, but this land seems quite similar "
"to the Great Continent. It has trees, grass, rocks, deer, rivers... I know I "
"shouldn't be saying this, but I'll be disappointed if we don't find any real "
"challenge here."
msgstr ""
"Sabes, esperaba un mundo completamente nuevo, pero esta tierra parece "
"bastante parecida al Gran Continente. Tiene árboles, hierba, rocas, ciervos, "
"ríos... Sé que no debería decirlo, pero me decepcionaría si no encontramos "
"ningún verdadero desafío aquí."

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:301
msgid ""
"Cousin, your timing couldn't have been more perfect. Now what on Irdya was "
"that?"
msgstr ""
"Primo, tu tiempo no pudo ser más oportuno. ¡Ahora qué demonios fue eso!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:305
msgid ""
"I have hunted game on many fields of the Hannuk Steppes, but I've never "
"heard such sound. Though I bet it's not something that will be glad for "
"seeing us..."
msgstr ""
"He cazado en muchas llanuras de las Estepas Hannuk, pero nunca había oído un "
"sonido así. Aunque apuesto a que no es algo que se alegre de vernos..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:325
msgid ""
"To think we'd travel as far as aunt Deni herself did... I can almost hear "
"her congratulating us for 'getting out and seeing the wide green world'."
msgstr ""
"Pensar que hemos viajado tan lejos como la propia tía Deni... Casi puedo "
"oírla felicitándonos por «salir y ver el ancho mundo verde»."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:329
msgid ""
"Well, <i>I</i> can almost hear her laughing at us for taking so long just to "
"cross an ocean."
msgstr ""
"Pues <i>yo</i> casi la oigo reírse de nosotras por tardar tanto solo en "
"cruzar un océano."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:333
msgid ""
"Yes, that is more like her. And then she'd mock mother because two neophytes "
"like us, without teleporting ciphers, got to visit Netjer-Ta before she did."
msgstr ""
"Sí, eso suena más a ella. Y luego se burlaría de mamá porque dos novatas "
"como nosotras, sin cifrados de teletransporte, llegamos a Netjer-Ta antes "
"que ella."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:337
msgid ""
"(chuckles) She did have a rivalry with those who use teleport ciphers, "
"didn't she..."
msgstr ""
"(risita) Sí que tenía rivalidad con los que usaban cifrados de "
"teletransporte, ¿verdad...?"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:341
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/utils/intros.cfg:179
msgid "<i>Silence...</i>"
msgstr "<i>Silencio...</i>"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:345
msgid ""
"(wiping away tears) Argh, ignore this. I guess setting foot on dry land "
"after so long made me sentimental..."
msgstr ""
"(secándose las lágrimas) Argh, no hagan caso. Supongo que pisar tierra firme "
"después de tanto tiempo me puso sentimental..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:349
msgid "Not just any land, but land that aunt Deni set foot on, right?"
msgstr ""
"No es cualquier tierra, sino la tierra donde pisó la tía Deni, ¿cierto?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:353
msgid ""
"If it wasn't for her stories, I wouldn't have known about Netjer-Ta, and I "
"would never have suggested coming here. Hells, if she hadn't led that "
"expedition here we would still remember this continent as one wrecked by "
"war, and no way our savants would've agreed coming here. She's always been "
"with us on this journey, and not just in memories. But to be here... to be "
"standing on this land... It feels like a part of her is already here, "
"waiting to greet us."
msgstr ""
"Si no fuera por sus historias, no habría sabido de Netjer-Ta y nunca habría "
"propuesto venir aquí. Diablos, si ella no hubiera liderado aquella "
"expedición aún recordaríamos este continente como uno arrasado por la "
"guerra, y de ninguna manera nuestros sabios habrían aceptado venir. Ella "
"siempre ha estado con nosotras en este viaje, y no solo en los recuerdos. "
"Pero estar aquí... pisar esta tierra... Se siente como si una parte de ella "
"ya estuviera aquí, esperándonos para darnos la bienvenida."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:357
msgid ""
"Damn right, sis. When we build our new Foundation, I say we adorn our Great "
"Hall with a statue of her."
msgstr ""
"Tienes toda la razón, hermana. Cuando construyamos nuestra nueva Fundación, "
"propongo que adornemos el Gran Salón con una estatua suya."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:361
msgid ""
"Place it on the Eyrie instead, so she can look beyond the eastern horizons."
msgstr ""
"Ponla en el Nido Águila, para que pueda mirar más allá de los horizontes del "
"este."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:365
msgid "Didn't she prefer looking at the sunset, though?"
msgstr "Aunque a ella le gustaba más mirar la puesta de sol, ¿no?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:369
msgid ""
"She liked looking towards the lands where Hathor was born. In Hiera'Shirsha, "
"that meant looking west, but we're on the other side of the world now."
msgstr ""
"Le gustaba mirar hacia las tierras donde nació Hathor. En Hiera'Shirsha eso "
"significaba mirar al oeste, pero ahora estamos al otro lado del mundo."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:373
msgid "I see..."
msgstr "Entiendo..."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:377
msgid ""
"And commission the dwarves to craft her statue. She'd want no lesser crafter "
"to be in charge of chiselling her semblance out of stone."
msgstr ""
"Y que sean los enanos quienes la esculpan. Ella no querría que nadie menor "
"que el mejor tallara su semblante en piedra."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:381
msgid ""
"(smiling) Say no more. Dvalin will be mad at me if I request anyone other "
"than himself to carve that statue."
msgstr ""
"(sonriendo) No digas más. Dvalin se enfadaría conmigo si le pido a otro que "
"no sea él quien esculpa esa estatua."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:410
msgid ""
"It has just dawned on me... I left the forests of Lintanir to cross the "
"Great Continent all the way to its utmost east, then crossed the world's "
"widest ocean to set foot in that which, in my people's maps, is the "
"westernmost of all lands. I've almost completed a full circle around Irdya "
"itself!"
msgstr ""
"Acaba de ocurrírseme... Dejé los bosques de Lintanir, crucé todo el Gran "
"Continente hasta su extremo oriental, luego crucé el océano más ancho del "
"mundo para pisar lo que en los mapas de mi pueblo es la tierra más "
"occidental de todas. ¡Casi he dado una vuelta completa al propio Irdya!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:414
msgid "Not so soon, princess. You still need to visit Arajunna."
msgstr "Todavía no, princesa. Aún te falta visitar Arajunna."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:418
msgid ""
"I... think I might pass. I always loved Lady Sunna's tales of faraway lands; "
"it was one reason I volunteered to carry the King-in-the-Forest's message "
"all the way to Esthiel, in fact. But I may have had my fill of roaming the "
"world; soon it'll be time to find a soil for my roots to take hold."
msgstr ""
"Creo... que voy a pasar. Siempre amé los cuentos de Lady Sunna sobre tierras "
"lejanas; de hecho, esa fue una de las razones por las que me ofrecí a llevar "
"el mensaje del Rey del Bosque hasta Esthiel. Pero creo que ya tuve "
"suficiente de vagar por el mundo; pronto será hora de encontrar una tierra "
"donde echar raíces."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:422
msgid "So... you're not returning home?"
msgstr "Entonces... ¿no vas a volver a casa?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:426
msgid ""
"As Lady Sunna used to teach, home is where those you love are. And after all "
"we've been through... Let's say my home just might be here after all, in "
"this westernmost of all lands."
msgstr ""
"Como solía enseñar Lady Sunna, el hogar está donde están aquellos a quienes "
"amas. Y después de todo lo que hemos pasado... Digamos que mi hogar bien "
"podría estar aquí después de todo, en la tierra más occidental de todas."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:450
msgid "Master Takyn, I hope your horse is faring better?"
msgstr "Maestro Takyn, espero que tu caballo esté mejor?"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:454
msgid ""
"She is indeed. Your treatment worked wonders; not bad... for an Aragwaithi."
msgstr ""
"En efecto lo está. Tu tratamiento hizo maravillas; no está mal... para un "
"aragwaithi."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:458
msgid ""
"We may have a lesser bond with horses than you Hannuks, but we treat ours "
"well too. Besides... I may have learned a thing or two with the Windsong."
msgstr ""
"Tal vez tengamos un vínculo menor con los caballos que ustedes los hannuk, "
"pero también tratamos bien a los nuestros. Además... puede que haya "
"aprendido una o dos cosas con las Hijas del Viento."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:462
msgid "With my daughter, you mean?"
msgstr "¿Con mi hija, quieres decir?"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:466
msgid "(blushes) Yes, I mean..."
msgstr "(se sonroja) Sí, quiero decir..."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:470
msgid ""
"Among the Hannuks, all fathers worry that their daughters find someone who "
"treats them fairly and with respect, and who protects them from the dangers "
"of the steppe. But this new land may have dangers beyond anything that "
"stalks the steppes. Do you think you can protect my daughter from them?"
msgstr ""
"Entre los hannuk, todos los padres se preocupan porque sus hijas encuentren "
"a alguien que las trate con justicia y respeto, y que las proteja de los "
"peligros de la estepa. Pero esta nueva tierra puede tener peligros mayores "
"que cualquiera que aceche en las estepas. ¿Crees que puedes proteger a mi "
"hija de ellos?"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:474
msgid ""
"With respect, Master Tarkyn, your daughter needs no protection... But if she "
"ever needs someone to lean on, whenever she needs, no matter what, I will be "
"there for her, constant as a mountain."
msgstr ""
"Con el debido respeto, maestro Tarkyn, su hija no necesita protección... "
"Pero si alguna vez necesita alguien en quien apoyarse, cuando sea, pase lo "
"que pase, yo estaré ahí para ella, constante como una montaña."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:478
msgid "Hrmmm..."
msgstr "Hrmmm..."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:482
msgid "Well spoken, lad."
msgstr "Bien dicho, muchacho."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:497
msgid "Whoa, watch out everyone, these look quite dangerous..."
msgstr "¡Cuidado todos, estos parecen bastante peligrosos...!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:501
msgid "Akashia, do the scrolls tell anything about these beings?"
msgstr "Akashia, ¿los pergaminos dicen algo sobre estos seres?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:505
msgid ""
"Well, they look very like the descriptions of minotaurs. They're an "
"intelligent people, but a very belligerent one as well; not counting that "
"they're very strong and resilient."
msgstr ""
"Pues se parecen mucho a las descripciones de los minotauros. Son un pueblo "
"inteligente, pero muy beligerante también; sin contar que son muy fuertes y "
"resistentes."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:509
msgid ""
"Pah, we used to brawl with trolls and drakes, I doubt these oxen will be "
"much of a match for us! C'mon boys, let's introduce them to our axes!"
msgstr ""
"¡Bah, antes nos peleábamos con troles y dracos, dudo que estos bueyes sean "
"gran cosa para nosotros! ¡Vamos muchachos, vamos a presentarles nuestras "
"hachas!"

#. [unit], id=Arkarm, type=Warrior Carapace
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:528
msgid "Arkarm"
msgstr "Arkarm"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:540
msgid ""
"Aww, look at that turtle! It has been so long since I last saw one, I think "
"I'll take one of these as my pet; who knows, with its size it could even be "
"my mount when I tire of floating around..."
msgstr ""
"¡Aww, miren esa tortuga! Hace tanto que no veía una... Creo que me llevaré "
"una de estas como mascota; quién sabe, con su tamaño hasta podría ser mi "
"montura cuando me canse de flotar por ahí..."

#. [message], speaker=Arkarm
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:544
msgid "Chisssss!!!"
msgstr "¡Chisssss!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:548
msgid "Aaaaiiieeee!!!"
msgstr "¡Aaaaiiieeee!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:552
msgid "(laughing) I think it has rejected you, Alenya..."
msgstr "(riendo) Creo que te rechazó, Alenya..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:556
msgid ""
"This continent sure has different beings... These turtle-like creatures "
"don't seem aggressive, so we could just avoid them."
msgstr ""
"Este continente sí que tiene seres diferentes... Estas criaturas parecidas a "
"tortugas no parecen agresivas, así que podríamos simplemente evitarlas."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:572
msgid ""
"What a beautiful beach! It was really lucky that I found it amidst this "
"dense forest and hills... Would that I could spend the entire afternoon "
"here, just relaxing and staring at the sea, now I must return to battle. But "
"I think I'll really come back here when work's done..."
msgstr ""
"¡Qué playa tan hermosa! Tuve mucha suerte de encontrarla entre este bosque "
"denso y las colinas... Ojalá pudiera pasar toda la tarde aquí, solo "
"relajándome y mirando el mar, pero ahora debo volver al combate. Creo que "
"realmente volveré aquí cuando termine el trabajo..."

#. [unit], id=Bagrar, type=Orcish Warlord
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:601
msgid "Bagrar"
msgstr "Bagrar"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:648
msgid "Uh-oh, this is not good..."
msgstr "Uh-oh, esto no pinta bien..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:652
msgid ""
"Get down everyone, lest they'll spot us! (whispering) Akashia, have you read "
"anything in the scrolls describing these beings?"
msgstr ""
"¡Todos al suelo, que no nos vean! (susurrando) Akashia, ¿has leído algo en "
"los pergaminos que describa a estos seres?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:656
msgid "Well, by their look..."
msgstr "Pues, por su aspecto..."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:660
msgid ""
"(screaming) You puny smug, if you really want to keep sucking up to that "
"loser of my brother, then I shall kill you and use your skull to adorn my "
"castle's gates!"
msgstr ""
"(gritando) ¡Pedazo de lamebotas insignificante, si tanto quieres seguir "
"lamiéndole las botas a ese perdedor de mi hermano, te mataré y usaré tu "
"cráneo para adornar las puertas de mi castillo!"

#. [message], speaker=Bagrar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:664
msgid ""
"(shouting) You are nothing more than a braggart, you weakling idiot! The "
"great Hagash hasn't even bothered to attack you himself, and only sent a "
"small fraction of his magnificent army to wave you aside!"
msgstr ""
"(gritando) ¡No eres más que un fanfarrón, idiota débil! ¡El gran Hagash ni "
"siquiera se ha molestado en atacarte él mismo, y solo envió una pequeña "
"parte de su magnífico ejército para apartarte de su camino!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:668
msgid ""
"...and by their behaviour, I'm pretty sure they're orcs. The scrolls claim "
"they were the most dangerous of all races in this continent, albeit not as "
"aggressive as those minotaurs we've encountered, so we could try and parlay "
"with them after they finish their battle..."
msgstr ""
"...y por su comportamiento, estoy casi segura de que son orcos. Los "
"pergaminos dicen que eran la raza más peligrosa de este continente, aunque "
"no tan agresivos como los minotauros que hemos encontrado, así que podríamos "
"intentar negociar con ellos cuando terminen su batalla..."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:672
msgid ""
"Uh wait, what is that? Ships docked on the northern beaches and... vampires "
"coming out of them? Since when do those blood-sucking pests venture in the "
"sea?"
msgstr ""
"Un momento, ¿qué es eso? ¿Barcos atracados en las playas del norte y... "
"vampiros saliendo de ellos? ¿Desde cuándo esos parásitos chupasangre se "
"aventuran en el mar?"

#. [message], speaker=Bagrar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:676
msgid ""
"They're not vampires, you idiot! Just look at their skin colour! Maybe they "
"are another bunch of those southern freaks..."
msgstr ""
"¡No son vampiros, idiota! ¡Mira el color de su piel! Tal vez sean otro grupo "
"de esos monstruos del sur..."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:680
msgid "Vampires? What are they talking about?"
msgstr "¿Vampiros? ¿De qué están hablando?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:684
msgid ""
"We can worry about that later. (screaming) Noble orcs, I am Myra of "
"Hiera'Shirsha, leader of this group of refugees from across-the-ocean! We "
"come in peace, as people who only seek a piece of safe, uninhabited land to "
"rebuild our..."
msgstr ""
"Ya nos preocuparemos por eso después. (gritando) ¡Nobles orcos, soy Myra de "
"Hiera'Shirsha, líder de este grupo de refugiados del otro lado del océano! "
"¡Venimos en paz, como gente que solo busca un pedazo de tierra segura y "
"deshabitada para reconstruir nuestras..."

#. [message], speaker=Bagrar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:688
msgid ""
"So, vermin, do I have your word that you won't backstab me while we kill off "
"these new weaklings?"
msgstr ""
"Entonces, alimañas, ¿tengo tu palabra de que no me apuñalarán por la espalda "
"mientras acabamos con estos nuevos debiluchos?"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:692
msgid "Bah! How dare you doubt me? Unlike my brother, I'm an orc with honour."
msgstr ""
"¡Bah! ¿Cómo te atreves a dudar de mí? A diferencia de mi hermano, yo soy un "
"orco con honor."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:696
msgid "...and here I am, speaking to the winds..."
msgstr "...y aquí estoy, hablando con el viento..."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:700
msgid ""
"Just as I'd read: the orcs are difficult to parlay with. None of our "
"predecessors managed to pacify them, and so we must not waste our time "
"trying. But we won't have to fight them all: apparently, if we just kill "
"their leaders, they'll be reduced to a bunch of isolated tribes squabbling "
"amongst themselves."
msgstr ""
"Tal como leí: con los orcos es difícil negociar. Ninguno de nuestros "
"predecesores logró pacificarlos, así que no debemos perder tiempo "
"intentándolo. Pero no tendremos que pelear contra todos: al parecer, si "
"matamos a sus líderes, quedarán reducidos a un montón de tribus aisladas "
"peleando entre sí."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:704
msgid ""
"But these two armies alone are quite huge; we won't manage to vanquish them "
"so easily. But, maybe we don't have to fight them both... (shouting) Hey, "
"you whom is called Ogesh!"
msgstr ""
"Pero solo estos dos ejércitos ya son bastante grandes; no podremos vencerlos "
"tan fácilmente. Pero, tal vez no tengamos que pelear contra ambos... "
"(gritando) ¡Oye, tú que te llamas Ogesh!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:708
msgid "What do you want, weakling?"
msgstr "¿Qué quieres, débil?"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:712
msgid ""
"Judging from what I've just heard, this orc called Bagrar is one of your "
"brother's commanders, right? May I ask you why are two brothers fighting "
"each other like this?"
msgstr ""
"Por lo que acabo de oír, este orco llamado Bagrar es uno de los comandantes "
"de tu hermano, ¿verdad? ¿Puedo preguntarte por qué dos hermanos se pelean "
"así?"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:716
msgid ""
"Because he's an idiot who's envious of my wealth and virility and influence "
"among our kind, and wants to usurp my rightful place as the sovereign of orc-"
"kind!"
msgstr ""
"¡Porque es un idiota que envidia mi riqueza, mi virilidad y mi influencia "
"entre los nuestros, y quiere usurpar mi legítimo lugar como soberano de los "
"orcos!"

#. [message], speaker=Bagrar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:720
msgid ""
"You helpless idiot, why did you say you're an orc sovereign? Everyone knows "
"that killing orc sovereigns is our weakness!"
msgstr ""
"¡Idiota inútil, por qué dijiste que eres un soberano orco! ¡Todos saben que "
"matar soberanos orcos es nuestra debilidad!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:724
msgid ""
"Don't worry, o great emperor, we intend not on usurping your throne. But "
"tell me something else: this Bagrar seems quite dedicated to his master, "
"your brother, right?"
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes, oh gran emperador, no pretendemos usurpar tu trono. Pero "
"dime otra cosa: este Bagrar parece bastante leal a su amo, tu hermano, "
"¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:728
msgid "Well, yes, he does, but what does it have to do with you?"
msgstr "Bueno, sí, lo es, pero ¿qué tiene eso que ver contigo?"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:732
msgid ""
"Doesn't it seem likely to you that, while you're busy fighting us, he'll try "
"and kill you? Thus he'd fall in your brother's graces like no other before "
"him."
msgstr ""
"¿No te parece probable que, mientras estás ocupado peleando contra nosotros, "
"él intente matarte? Así caería en gracia con tu hermano como nadie antes."

#. [message], speaker=Bagrar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:736
msgid ""
"Shut the hell up, you rat! He's just trying to trick you, Ogesh! Show that "
"you're not the dumb-ass you've always seemed to be and ignore him!"
msgstr ""
"¡Cállate de una vez, rata! ¡Solo está tratando de engañarte, Ogesh! "
"¡Demuestra que no eres el idiota que siempre has parecido y hazle caso omiso!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:740
msgid ""
"I assure you we have absolutely no reason to attack you, Lord Ogesh; as I've "
"just said, we're just a peaceful refugee people seeking a safe, unoccupied "
"land. We want no quarrels for ourselves. On the other hand, this Bagrar "
"seems eager to rip off your head..."
msgstr ""
"Te aseguro que no tenemos absolutamente ninguna razón para atacarte, señor "
"Ogesh; como acabo de decir, somos solo un pueblo de refugiados pacíficos que "
"busca una tierra segura y deshabitada. No queremos problemas. En cambio, "
"este Bagrar parece ansioso por arrancarte la cabeza..."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:744
msgid ""
"Well, you do make sense... And you really don't look like vampires, not even "
"like those southern freaks... So, if I let you be, do you promise you won't "
"backstab me?"
msgstr ""
"Pues... tienes razón... Y realmente no parecen vampiros, ni siquiera como "
"esos monstruos del sur... Entonces, si los dejo en paz, ¿prometen no "
"apuñalarme por la espalda?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:748
msgid "I was actually going to ask you if you wanted our aid..."
msgstr "En realidad iba a preguntarte si querías nuestra ayuda..."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:752
msgid "Bah, I think I can deal with this low-life myself, thanks!"
msgstr "¡Bah, creo que puedo lidiar con este desgraciado yo solo, gracias!"

#. [message], speaker=Bagrar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:756
msgid ""
"Stupid, no-good Ogesh, I'll make you regret not surrendering when you had "
"the chance! Call in the reinforcements, I want his city razed to the ground "
"before next sunset!"
msgstr ""
"¡Estúpido y inútil Ogesh, te haré arrepentir de no rendirte cuando tuviste "
"la oportunidad! ¡Llamen a los refuerzos, quiero su ciudad arrasada antes de "
"la próxima puesta de sol!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:760
msgid ""
"Where the hell did he pull so many armies from?! Listen, you ra... I mean, "
"you girl, I say we should help each other: help me defeating that "
"treacherous scumbag, and I will help you however you want."
msgstr ""
"¡¿De dónde demonios sacó tantos ejércitos?! Escucha, tú chi... digo, tú "
"chica, digo que deberíamos ayudarnos: ayúdame a derrotar a ese traidor "
"desgraciado, y yo te ayudaré en lo que quieras."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:764
msgid ""
"Deal! Friends, now we have a real battle to fight! Let's show them the might "
"of the people of the Great Continent!"
msgstr ""
"¡Trato hecho! ¡Amigos, ahora sí tenemos una verdadera batalla que librar! "
"¡Mostrémosles el poder del pueblo del Gran Continente!"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:770
msgid "Defeat Bagrar"
msgstr "Derrotar a Bagrar"

#. [objective], condition=lose
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:802
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:53
msgid "Death of Ogesh"
msgstr "Muerte de Ogesh"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:821
msgid ""
"I don't know who you are, but you do fight well. You said you are a refugee "
"people, aren't you? Tell me, where are you from, what made you flee your "
"land, and are you being followed by anyone else?"
msgstr ""
"No sé quiénes son, pero pelean bien. Dijeron que son un pueblo de "
"refugiados, ¿verdad? Díganme, ¿de dónde vienen, qué los hizo huir de su "
"tierra, y alguien más los está siguiendo?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:825
msgid ""
"We come from the west, from a continent beyond this vast ocean. We are a "
"group of humans and dwarves who had our homes destroyed by dragons and their "
"vassals, the drakes and the saurians; after being persecuted by them, we saw "
"no alternative but to search for this continent, guided by the lore "
"collected by the Windsong. And no, we're not being followed by anyone."
msgstr ""
"Venimos del oeste, de un continente más allá de este vasto océano. Somos un "
"grupo de humanos y enanos cuyos hogares fueron destruidos por dragones y sus "
"vasallos, los dracos y los saurianos; tras ser perseguidos por ellos, no "
"vimos otra alternativa que buscar este continente, guiados por el saber "
"recopilado por las Hijas del Viento. Y no, nadie nos está siguiendo."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:829
msgid ""
"Windsong? You mean the human females who brought those blood-sucking "
"aberrations?"
msgstr ""
"¿Hijas del Viento? ¿Te refieres a las humanas que trajeron a esas "
"aberraciones chupasangre?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:833
msgid "Er, I'm afraid I don't know what you're talking about..."
msgstr "Eh, me temo que no sé de qué estás hablando..."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:837
msgid ""
"Worry not, milady, this is something that only Arbiters, Librarians or "
"guardians like myself know. In the past, our sisters... well... conducted "
"experiments of magic and medicine on other humans, but something went "
"terribly wrong, and the result was a virus that turned the infected victims "
"into blood-thirsty, darkness-loving creatures. There's very little "
"information on them, but I know the infected individuals were taken to "
"Netjer-Ta, since the then head of our order didn't want to sacrifice them."
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes, mi señora, esto es algo que solo saben los Árbitros, "
"Bibliotecarios o guardianes como yo. En el pasado, nuestras hermanas... "
"bueno... realizaron experimentos de magia y medicina con otros humanos, pero "
"algo salió terriblemente mal, y el resultado fue un virus que convirtió a "
"las víctimas infectadas en criaturas sedientas de sangre y amantes de la "
"oscuridad. Hay muy poca información sobre ellos, pero sé que los infectados "
"fueron traídos a Netjer-Ta, porque la entonces cabeza de nuestra orden no "
"quiso sacrificarlos."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:841
msgid ""
"And I thought Ashura was the only blemish in our History... Listen, Lord "
"Ogesh, I am also the current Ascendant of the Windsong; I acknowledge our "
"predecessors may have done horrible things against your people, but I assure "
"you we have changed, and we'll do anything to compensate your people for "
"past aggressions..."
msgstr ""
"Y yo que pensaba que Ashura era la única mancha en nuestra historia... "
"Escucha, señor Ogesh, yo soy también la actual Ascendiente de las Hijas del "
"Viento; reconozco que nuestras predecesoras pudieron haber hecho cosas "
"horribles contra tu pueblo, pero te aseguro que hemos cambiado, y haremos lo "
"que sea para compensar a tu pueblo por las agresiones del pasado..."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:845
msgid ""
"The past is the past; just leave the dead to their rest. Now, bring the rest "
"of your people to my city, they must be exhausted. As for you, come to my "
"castle; I will give you information on the nations and geography of this "
"continent, as a further reward for helping me."
msgstr ""
"El pasado es el pasado; dejen a los muertos descansar en paz. Ahora, traigan "
"al resto de su gente a mi ciudad, deben estar agotados. En cuanto a ustedes, "
"vengan a mi castillo; les daré información sobre las naciones y la geografía "
"de este continente, como recompensa adicional por ayudarme."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:849
msgid ""
"Thank you very much, Lord Ogesh. But please, tell me one more thing: have "
"you orcs ever met giant, fire-breathing reptiles in this continent?"
msgstr ""
"Muchas gracias, señor Ogesh. Pero por favor, dime una cosa más: ¿alguna vez "
"ustedes los orcos se han encontrado con reptiles gigantes que escupen fuego "
"en este continente?"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:853
msgid "No, we haven't met anything like that... why?"
msgstr "No, nunca nos hemos encontrado con algo así... ¿por qué?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:857
msgid "Nothing important, it's just that we really hate reptiles."
msgstr "Nada importante, es solo que realmente odiamos a los reptiles."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:973
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:519
msgid "Aaarrghh! How could I fall to this lackey?!"
msgstr "¡Aaarrghh! ¡Cómo pude caer ante este lacayo?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:977
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:523
msgid ""
"Ogesh would have been an invaluable ally for us! Without him, we'll be at "
"the mercy of the enemy orcish hordes!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ogesh habría sido un aliado invaluable para nosotros! ¡Sin él, quedaremos a "
"merced de las hordas orcas enemigas!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/22_Where_The_Sun_Is_Born.cfg:988
msgid ""
"We have wasted too much time exploring this new realm, and for all this time "
"our people was left barely protected on the beach; I fear some ill may have "
"afflicted them..."
msgstr ""
"Hemos perdido demasiado tiempo explorando este nuevo reino, y durante todo "
"este tiempo nuestra gente quedó apenas protegida en la playa; me temo que "
"algo malo les haya sucedido..."

#. [scenario], id=23_Holy_Fire
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:4
msgid "Holy Fire"
msgstr "Fuego Sagrado"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:21
msgid "Defeat Liliel"
msgstr "Derrotar a Liliel"

#. [side]
#. [side], type=Celestial Herald
#. [side], type=Sage
#. [terrain_type]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:106
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:93
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:29
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:87
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:93
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:72
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/terrain/terrain-definitions.cfg:69
msgid "Crystal Tower"
msgstr "Torre de Cristal"

#. [side], type=Minotaur Executioner
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:127
msgid "Minos"
msgstr "Minos"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:187
msgid ""
"Who is it now? Has my unworthy brother finally got enough guts to face me "
"himself?"
msgstr ""
"¿Y ahora quién es? ¿Acaso mi indigno hermano por fin reunió el valor para "
"enfrentarme él mismo?"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:195
msgid ""
"I don't think it's him, chief. I can't see it with this fog, but, by the "
"sound of the trumpets they blew some minutes ago, I think it's those weird "
"southerners..."
msgstr ""
"No creo que sea él, jefe. Con esta niebla no puedo ver, pero por el sonido "
"de las trompetas que tocaron hace unos minutos, creo que son esos sureños "
"raros..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:199
msgid ""
"So they're the humans you talked about, Lord Ogesh. However, there is "
"something strange about them... And I'm not even referring to their wings..."
msgstr ""
"Entonces son los humanos de los que hablabas, señor Ogesh. Sin embargo, hay "
"algo extraño en ellos... Y ni siquiera me refiero a sus alas..."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:203
msgid ""
"Hail, orc sovereign! I am Liliel, and I am here on behalf of the Crystal "
"Tower!"
msgstr ""
"¡Salve, soberano orco! ¡Soy Liliel y vengo en nombre de la Torre de Cristal!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:207
msgid "What do you want here, bird-girl?"
msgstr "¿Qué quieres aquí, pájara?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:211
msgid ""
"Beware thy speech, orc; I am not one of thy lackeys for thee to use such low "
"language on me."
msgstr ""
"Cuida tu lengua, orco; no soy uno de tus lacayos para que me hables con tan "
"baja lenguaje."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:215
msgid ""
"AND JUST WHO DO YOU THINK YOU ARE TO COME HERE AND TELL ME HOW I SHOULD..."
msgstr ""
"¡¿Y TÚ QUIÉN TE CREES QUE ERES PARA VENIR AQUÍ Y DECIRME CÓMO DEBO "
"HABLAR...?!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:219
msgid ""
"I have been sent by the great Seraphin Lords; they have sensed that a great "
"evil has descended on our troubled, but dear continent, and that it has "
"arrived near thy capital. I ask thee, has any unknown faction set foot on "
"thy shores?"
msgstr ""
"He sido enviada por los grandes Señores Serafines; han percibido que un gran "
"mal ha descendido sobre nuestro continente atribulado pero querido, y que ha "
"llegado cerca de tu capital. Te pregunto, ¿alguna facción desconocida ha "
"puesto pie en tus costas?"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:223
msgid ""
"(fuming) No kidding, I swear I'm going to pluck every feather from her "
"wings, one by one, and..."
msgstr ""
"(furioso) Sin broma, juro que le voy a arrancar todas las plumas de las "
"alas, una por una, y..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:227
msgid ""
"Lord Ogesh, allow me. Liliel, I am Myra of Hiera'Shirsha, and I lead the "
"refugees from a distant war. I have arrived here just yesterday, and I "
"wonder whether this 'evil' you talk about refers to us; and if so, why do "
"you consider us an 'evil'?"
msgstr ""
"Señor Ogesh, cálmese. (gritando) Liliel, soy Myra de Hiera’Shirsha y lidero "
"a los refugiados de una guerra lejana. Llegué aquí apenas ayer, y me "
"pregunto si ese «mal» del que hablas se refiere a nosotros; y de ser así, "
"por qué nos consideras un «mal»."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:231
msgid ""
"So you are the one the Lords saw! Verily do I tell you that I'm impressed by "
"how innocent you look, o stranger, but think not that I will have mercy on "
"thee, nor that I will spare thee the righteous punishment sentenced by the "
"Great Lords of the Crystal Tower, from whose mouths pour the holy will of "
"the Great Gods! Now, grab thy weapon, and face thy fate at the edge of my "
"blessed blade!"
msgstr ""
"¡Así que tú eres la que vieron los Señores! En verdad te digo que estoy "
"impresionada por lo inocente que pareces, extranjera, ¡pero no creas que "
"tendré piedad de ti, ni que te libraré del justo castigo dictado por los "
"Grandes Señores de la Torre de Cristal, de cuyas bocas fluye la santa "
"voluntad de los Grandes Dioses! ¡Ahora toma tu arma y enfrenta tu destino al "
"filo de mi espada bendita!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:235
msgid "My, my, and I thought <i>I</i> was pedantic..."
msgstr "Vaya, vaya, y yo que pensaba que <i>yo</i> era la pedante..."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:239
msgid ""
"Who the hell is that pest? Let's just destroy her, and then march on this "
"'Crystal Tower' and empty it! I'm sure it will make us a fine outpost..."
msgstr ""
"¿Quién demonios es esa plaga? ¡Vamos a destruirla y luego marchamos a esa "
"«Torre de Cristal» y la vaciamos! Seguro que nos servirá de excelente puesto "
"avanzado..."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:243
msgid ""
"(whispering) You're talking about her, but did you notice what she said? I "
"bet all my horses that this 'evil' she babbles about is actually our gem."
msgstr ""
"(susurrando) Hablas de ella, pero ¿escuchaste lo que dijo? Apuesto todos mis "
"caballos a que ese «mal» del que habla es en realidad nuestra gema."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:247
msgid ""
"(whispering) You spoke my thoughts, father. Listen, Liliel, I think I "
"understand what you are talking about; but know that we're just guarding it, "
"so that it won't fall into the wrong hands!"
msgstr ""
"(susurrando) Dijiste lo que pensaba, padre. (gritando) Escucha, Liliel, creo "
"que entiendo de qué hablas; ¡pero sabe que solo la estamos protegiendo para "
"que no caiga en malas manos!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:251
msgid ""
"In that case, thou shall quietly yield me the evil source thou carries and I "
"shall deliver it to the Seraphin Lords; then they may even permit thee an "
"audience with them, and be granted a place on our lands to live as our loyal "
"vassals."
msgstr ""
"En ese caso, entrégame tranquilamente la fuente del mal que llevas y yo la "
"entregaré a los Señores Serafines; entonces tal vez te permitan una "
"audiencia con ellos y te concedan un lugar en nuestras tierras para vivir "
"como vasallos leales."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:255
msgid "(moaning) Myra, I beg you, let me loose on her..."
msgstr "(gimoteando) Myra, te lo suplico, déjame acabar con ella..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:259
msgid ""
"I'm sorry, but we won't yield it to anyone; we have fought too hard and lost "
"too many of our own to do that."
msgstr ""
"(gritando) Lo siento, pero no se la entregaremos a nadie; hemos luchado "
"demasiado y perdido a demasiados de los nuestros como para rendirla así."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:263
msgid "Then you leave me no choice."
msgstr "Entonces no me dejas otra opción."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:270
msgid ""
"Come on, Myra, let me help you; there is a heavy price to pay for waking the "
"Orc Sovereign so early in the morning with such nonsense."
msgstr ""
"Vamos, Myra, déjame ayudarte; hay un precio muy alto que pagar por despertar "
"al Soberano Orco tan temprano con semejante tontería."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:290
msgid ""
"Lo, there comes a band of those smelly beasts! Seek no quarrel with them, "
"holy warriors, but do not hesitate in smiting them should they stand on our "
"path."
msgstr ""
"¡He aquí que viene una banda de esas bestias apestosas! No busquen pelea con "
"ellos, guerreros santos, pero no duden en aniquilarlos si se interponen en "
"nuestro camino."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:294
msgid ""
"This minotaur band isn't very strong, so we can take on them as well. And "
"don't kill Liliel; I want to have a few more words with her..."
msgstr ""
"Esta banda de minotauros no es muy fuerte, así que también podemos con "
"ellos. Y no maten a Liliel; quiero tener unas palabras más con ella..."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:306
msgid ""
"How... How can I be bested by these evildoers?! O Heavenly Lords, haven't I "
"been faithful enough?"
msgstr ""
"¡¿Cómo... cómo puedo ser derrotada por estos malhechores?! ¡Oh Señores "
"Celestiales, ¿acaso no he sido lo bastante fiel?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:310
msgid ""
"Cease your babbling and listen! We could kill you right here and now, but "
"we're not the evildoers you deem us to be! Now tell me, is this 'Crystal "
"Tower' the place where your leaders seat?"
msgstr ""
"¡Deja de balbucear y escucha! Podríamos matarte aquí y ahora, ¡pero no somos "
"los malhechores que crees! Ahora dime, ¿esa «Torre de Cristal» es donde "
"residen tus líderes?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:314
msgid "It... It is so..."
msgstr "Sí... así es..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:318
msgid ""
"Then you will take me there, so that I may talk to them myself. If your "
"people wishes this continent good so much, then there is no reason we can't "
"be friends."
msgstr ""
"Entonces me llevarás allí, para que pueda hablar con ellos personalmente. Si "
"tu pueblo desea tanto el bien de este continente, no hay razón para que no "
"podamos ser amigos."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:322
msgid ""
"Thou... Thou wills me to lead thee to where our dear lords live, so that "
"thou may treacherously strike them down!"
msgstr ""
"¡Tú... me obligas a llevarte donde viven nuestros queridos señores para que "
"los traiciones y los mates!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:326
msgid ""
"(eyes rolling) Myra, give up arguing with her, now stand aside, that my arm "
"is itching to let this sword fall on that pretty neck of hers..."
msgstr ""
"(poniendo los ojos en blanco) Myra, deja de discutir con ella, ahora "
"apártate, ¡que me pica el brazo por dejar caer esta espada sobre ese lindo "
"cuello suyo...!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:330
msgid "Akashia, at least <i>try</i> to help!"
msgstr "¡Akashia, al menos <i>intenta</i> ayudar!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:334
msgid ""
"But thy plot shall fail, evildoer! Thou may have bested me, a mere claimant, "
"but the Seraphin Lords are far above thy rank! I will take thee there, just "
"so that they may obliterate thee for good!"
msgstr ""
"¡Pero tu plan fallará, malhechora! Puede que me hayas vencido a mí, una "
"simple pretendiente, ¡pero los Señores Serafines están muy por encima de tu "
"nivel! Te llevaré allí, ¡solo para que te aniquilen de una vez por todas!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:338
msgid ""
"(sighing) Then take me there, so that your lords may strike me down with "
"their righteous strength..."
msgstr ""
"(suspirando) Entonces llévame allí, para que tus señores me derriben con su "
"justa fuerza..."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:342
msgid "I hope you're aware that we're not letting you go alone, right?"
msgstr "Espero que sepas que no te vamos a dejar ir sola, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:346
msgid ""
"(smiling) Do I have any choice? I will go to this Crystal Tower, but I want "
"Ravyan and my father here with the Aragwaithi and the Hannuk. That is, if "
"Lord Ogesh allows them to stay at his city a little longer?"
msgstr ""
"(sonriendo) ¿Acaso tengo opción? Iré a esta Torre de Cristal, pero quiero "
"que Ravyan y mi padre se queden aquí con los aragwaithi y los hannuk. Eso, "
"si el señor Ogesh permite que se queden en su ciudad un poco más."

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:350
msgid "You have my permission."
msgstr "Tienen mi permiso."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:354
msgid ""
"Thank you again, Lord Ogesh. Dvalin, come with us, along with your dwarves; "
"if we find the Motsoghnir Clan along the way, we'll need you by our side to "
"convince them we're friendly. Tell me, Liliel, what path will you lead us "
"through?"
msgstr ""
"Gracias otra vez, señor Ogesh. Dvalin, ven con nosotros junto a tus enanos; "
"si encontramos al Clan Motsoghnir en el camino, te necesitaremos a nuestro "
"lado para convencerlos de que somos amigos. Dime, Liliel, ¿por qué camino "
"nos guiarás?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:358
msgid ""
"Certainly the most dangerous one, so that she may betray us on the way and "
"leave us in dire straits..."
msgstr ""
"Seguro que el más peligroso, para traicionarnos en el camino y dejarnos en "
"la estacada..."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:362
msgid ""
"I am not a lowly evildoer like thee, mindless warmonger. I shall take thee "
"through the Sun Path until the Dark Island, and then go south, to the Silent "
"Desert, where the Crystal Tower rises. This is the safest route I can think "
"of, but be warned that we may still be attacked by vampires, wargs or "
"minotaurs."
msgstr ""
"No soy una vil malhechora como tú, belicista sin cerebro. Te llevaré por el "
"Sendero del Sol hasta la Isla Oscura, y luego al sur, al Desierto "
"Silencioso, donde se alza la Torre de Cristal. Es la ruta más segura que se "
"me ocurre, pero ten en cuenta que aún podemos ser atacados por vampiros, "
"huargos o minotauros."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:366
msgid "Good. Let's leave as soon as possible."
msgstr "Bien. Vámonos lo antes posible."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:370
msgid "(whispering) What about the Soul? Will you take it with you?"
msgstr "(susurrando) ¿Y el Alma? ¿La llevarás contigo?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:374
msgid ""
"(whispering) Of course I will. But rest assured that I will keep an eye on "
"it; Liliel may talk harshly about treachery, but who knows what she may do "
"in the name of what she thinks is right."
msgstr ""
"(susurrando) Claro que sí. Pero estén tranquilos, la vigilaré; Liliel puede "
"hablar mucho de traición, pero quién sabe qué podría hacer en nombre de lo "
"que ella cree que es correcto."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:490
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:943
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:643
msgid "I can't fall, milady needs me...!"
msgstr "¡No puedo caer, mi señora me necesita…!"

#. [message], speaker=Ogesh
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:535
msgid ""
"What is that large stain on the horizon...? Oh damn it, it's another huge "
"army sent by that loser of my brother!"
msgstr ""
"¿Qué es esa mancha enorme en el horizonte...? ¡Maldición, es otro ejército "
"enorme enviado por ese perdedor de mi hermano!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/23_Holy_Fire.cfg:539
msgid ""
"We should have defeated our enemies when we could; now, we won't be able to "
"fight so many of them at once..."
msgstr ""
"Deberíamos haber derrotado a nuestros enemigos cuando pudimos; ahora no "
"podremos con tantos a la vez..."

#. [scenario], id=24_The_Sun_Path
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:4
msgid "The Sun Path"
msgstr "El Sendero del Sol"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:24
msgid "Firstly, search for the Dark Island in the east"
msgstr "Primero, buscar la Isla Oscura en el este"

#. [objective], condition=lose
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:48
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:724
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:849
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:52
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:414
msgid "Death of Liliel"
msgstr "Muerte de Liliel"

#. [side]
#. [side], type=Methusalem
#. [side], type=Twilight Walker
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:97
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:113
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:170
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/27_The_Rise_Of_MaatKare.cfg:111
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:73
msgid "Vampires"
msgstr "Vampiros"

#. [side]
#. [side], type=Dwarvish Lord
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:129
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:32
msgid "Motsoghnir Dwarves"
msgstr "Enanos Motsoghnir"

#. [side]
#. [side], type=Garou
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:145
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:71
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:110
msgid "Wargs"
msgstr "Huargos"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:196
msgid ""
"Dvalin, tell me more about this Motsoghnir Clan; how did they reach this "
"continent, if you dwarves don't sail?"
msgstr ""
"Dvalin, cuéntame más sobre este Clan Motsoghnir; ¿cómo llegaron a este "
"continente si los enanos no navegan?"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:200
msgid ""
"Legend has it that they dug deeper and deeper into the earth, always going "
"eastwards, until they were below the sea. However, one day part of their "
"tunnels collapsed, and so they were never seen again. Explorers like me were "
"always told their legend as a lesson of the dangers of exploring too much, "
"but it seems like the Motsoghnir dwarves actually survived. I hope we get to "
"meet them."
msgstr ""
"La leyenda dice que cavaron cada vez más profundo en la tierra, siempre "
"hacia el este, hasta que quedaron debajo del mar. Sin embargo, un día parte "
"de sus túneles se derrumbaron, y nunca más se les volvió a ver. A "
"exploradores como yo siempre nos contaban su leyenda como lección sobre los "
"peligros de explorar demasiado, pero parece que los enanos Motsoghnir "
"realmente sobrevivieron. Espero poder conocerlos."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:204
msgid ""
"So do I, it would be good to have more dwarvish allies here. Do you know any "
"tale about elves travelling east across the ocean, Alenya?"
msgstr ""
"Yo también, sería bueno tener más aliados enanos aquí. ¿Conoces alguna "
"historia sobre elfos viajando al este a través del océano, Alenya?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:208
msgid ""
"I'm afraid not, Myra; we elves are quite a sedentary people, we seldom leave "
"our forests to wander about the world... And what are you snickering about, "
"Dvalin?"
msgstr ""
"Me temo que no, Myra; nosotros los elfos somos bastante sedentarios, rara "
"vez dejamos nuestros bosques para vagar por el mundo... ¿Y de qué te ríes, "
"Dvalin?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:212
msgid ""
"I have met these dwarves you talk about before; they staunchly refuse to let "
"us enlighten them, but at least sit quietly at their cavernous corner."
msgstr ""
"Ya he conocido a esos enanos de los que hablan; se niegan rotundamente a que "
"los iluminemos, pero al menos se quedan calladitos en su rincón cavernoso."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:216
msgid ""
"And you should stay quietly at your corner, bird-girl, before I roast you."
msgstr ""
"Y tú deberías quedarte calladita en tu rincón, pájara, antes de que te ase."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:220
msgid ""
"Girls, please... Now Liliel, show us the way; and don't forget that, if you "
"try anything weird, you'll be duly punished."
msgstr ""
"Chicas, por favor... Ahora Liliel, muéstranos el camino; y no olvides que, "
"si intentas algo raro, serás debidamente castigada."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:224
msgid "(sulking) Just follow me, sinners..."
msgstr "(refunfuñando) Solo síganme, pecadores..."

#. [unit], id=Taurius, type=Minotaur Elder
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:243
msgid "Taurius"
msgstr "Taurius"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:255
msgid ""
"A minotaur settlement... I know you'd prefer avoiding them, milady, but they "
"may gather more warriors later, and it would be unwise to leave a large "
"force on our rear."
msgstr ""
"Un asentamiento de minotauros... Sé que preferirías evitarlos, mi señora, "
"pero pueden reunir más guerreros después, y sería imprudente dejar una gran "
"fuerza a nuestras espaldas."

#. [unit], id=Vlad, type=Half Blood
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:278
msgid "Vlad"
msgstr "Vlad"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:299
msgid "Was that a human?"
msgstr "¿Eso era un humano?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:303
msgid ""
"No, it was a vampire. Now that it has seen you, it has gone tell its "
"comrades. Be prepared..."
msgstr ""
"No, era un vampiro. Ahora que los vio, fue a avisar a sus camaradas. "
"Prepárense..."

#. [message], speaker=Vlad
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:318
msgid ""
"So it is true: a patrol group of dwarves alongside a southern freak and... "
"the cursed Windsong. Our kind has waited for so long, but we finally have a "
"chance to have our revenge on them..."
msgstr ""
"Entonces es cierto: un grupo de patrulla de enanos junto a un monstruo del "
"sur y... las malditas Hijas del Viento. Nuestra raza ha esperado tanto, pero "
"por fin tenemos la oportunidad de vengarnos de ellas..."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:322
msgid "(shouting) You know, they are the last of their order..."
msgstr "(gritando) ¡Sepan que son las últimas de su orden...!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:326
msgid "(furious) What have you done, you idiot...!"
msgstr "(furiosa) ¡Qué has hecho, idiota…!"

#. [message], speaker=Vlad
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:330
msgid ""
"If that is true, then I must quickly take the news to Lord Vrykos! Armand, "
"go to the Red Pinnacle as fast as you can; I'll stay here and capture them."
msgstr ""
"¡Si eso es cierto, debo llevar la noticia al señor Vrykos de inmediato! "
"Armand, ve al Pináculo Rojo lo más rápido que puedas; yo me quedaré aquí y "
"los capturaré."

#. [message], speaker=Armand
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:334
msgid "As you wish, my liege."
msgstr "Como desees, mi señor."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:345
msgid "Well, you have been warned... Cipher of Silence!"
msgstr "Bueno, fuiste advertida... ¡Cifrado de Silencio!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:354
msgid "Gahh...!"
msgstr "¡Gahh...!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:358
msgid "Don't worry, you have just been temporarily silenced. Now, onwards!"
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes, solo has sido silenciada temporalmente. ¡Ahora, adelante!"

#. [unit], id=Abel, type=Twilight Walker
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:376
msgid "Abel"
msgstr "Abel"

#. [unit], id=Rayne, type=Sword Dancer, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:386
msgid "Rayne"
msgstr "Rayne"

#. [unit], id=Sumnor, type=Flesh Artisan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:395
msgid "Sumnor"
msgstr "Sumnor"

#. [message], speaker=Abel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:423
msgid ""
"So that hapless Armand was right after all: the Windsong have returned to "
"this continent... And they seem to be giving our dear Vlad a very hard time, "
"don't they?"
msgstr ""
"Entonces el pobre Armand tenía razón después de todo: las Hijas del Viento "
"han regresado a este continente... Y parece que le están dando muy duro a "
"nuestro querido Vlad, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Vlad
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:427
msgid "Stay out of this, Abel! They are my prey!"
msgstr "¡Quédate fuera de esto, Abel! ¡Son mi presa!"

#. [message], speaker=Abel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:431
msgid ""
"Oh, don't be so greedy! It will be better to live and share the glory of "
"capturing the witches with me than dying at their hands and having no glory "
"at all, don't you agree?"
msgstr ""
"¡Oh, no seas tan avaricioso! Es mejor vivir y compartir la gloria de "
"capturar a las brujas conmigo que morir a sus manos y no tener gloria "
"alguna, ¿no crees?"

#. [message], speaker=Vlad
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:435
msgid ""
"Well... You... Argh! You may join me then, but I want you to send out all "
"your vassals! I won't take the brunt of their attack alone."
msgstr ""
"Bueno... Tú... ¡Argh! Puedes unirte entonces, ¡pero quiero que envíes a "
"todos tus vasallos! ¡No voy a recibir todo el ataque yo solo!"

#. [unit], id=Alcatas, type=Dwarvish Steelclad
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:453
msgid "Alcatas"
msgstr "Alcatas"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:465
msgid "Dvalin, look! Can those dwarves be from the Motsoghnir Clan?"
msgstr "¡Dvalin, mira! ¿Esos enanos serán del Clan Motsoghnir?"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:469
msgid ""
"They can't be anyone else! (shouting) Hey, fellow dwarves from the "
"Motsoghnir Clan! We come from your old home, the Windy Mountains in the "
"Great Continent! Please help us against these pesky blood-suckers, for we "
"are seriously outnumbered!"
msgstr ""
"¡No pueden ser otros! (gritando) ¡Oigan, compañeros enanos del Clan "
"Motsoghnir! ¡Venimos de su antiguo hogar, las Montañas Ventosas del Gran "
"Continente! ¡Por favor ayúdennos contra estos molestos chupasangre, que "
"estamos en seria desventaja numérica!"

#. [message], speaker=Alcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:473
msgid ""
"Och, I came here expecting to find another vampire raiding group threatening "
"our frontiers, and I find our kinsmen from the Old Realm; even though "
"they're accompanied by Windsong-looking humans, by a southern freak, and "
"worse, by an elf, it is a joyful sight indeed. Just leave some of these "
"blood-suckers for my boys, kinsman!"
msgstr ""
"¡Och, vine aquí esperando encontrar otro grupo de saqueo vampírico "
"amenazando nuestras fronteras, y encuentro a nuestros parientes del Reino "
"Antiguo; aunque vengan acompañados por humanos que parecen Hijas del Viento, "
"por un monstruo del sur, y peor aún, por una elfa, es una vista alegre de "
"verdad. ¡Solo dejen algunos de estos chupasangre para mis muchachos, "
"pariente!"

#. [message], speaker=Alcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:495
msgid ""
"Ah, it is always good to smash some blood-suckers under our hammers! I'm "
"Alcatas of the Motsoghnir Clan, friends! Tell me, is it true that you come "
"from the faraway Windy Mountains?"
msgstr ""
"¡Ah, siempre es bueno aplastar chupasangre bajo nuestros martillos! ¡Soy "
"Alcatas del Clan Motsoghnir, amigos! Díganme, ¿es cierto que vienen de las "
"lejanas Montañas Ventosas?"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:499
msgid ""
"I am Dvalin of the Aigathol Clan, and yes, it is true. Unfortunately, "
"though, we are refugees, forced out of our home by an endless horde of "
"drakes and saurians led by fire dragons; alongside our human friends, we "
"have crossed the Stormy Ocean and reached the shores of this continent, "
"where we were aided by the orc king Ogesh, whom we have helped in a battle "
"against his brother's troops..."
msgstr ""
"Soy Dvalin del Clan Aigathol, y sí, es cierto. Desafortunadamente, somos "
"refugiados, expulsados de nuestro hogar por una horda interminable de dracos "
"y saurianos liderados por dragones de fuego; junto a nuestros amigos "
"humanos, cruzamos el Oceáno Tempestuoso y llegamos a las costas de este "
"continente, donde fuimos ayudados por el rey orco Ogesh, a quien ayudamos en "
"una batalla contra las tropas de su hermano..."

#. [message], speaker=Alcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:503
msgid "Wait a minute, you are friends of the orcs?!"
msgstr "¡Un momento, son amigos de los orcos?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:507
msgid "Of Ogesh, yes; is he your enemy?"
msgstr "De Ogesh, sí; ¿es tu enemigo?"

#. [message], speaker=Alcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:511
msgid ""
"Och, not exactly; his lands are far from our mountains, though we often "
"fight his brother's armies. But it doesn't matter, does it? An orc is an "
"orc, and cannot be trusted."
msgstr ""
"Och, no exactamente; sus tierras están lejos de nuestras montañas, aunque a "
"menudo peleamos contra los ejércitos de su hermano. Pero eso no importa, "
"¿verdad? Un orco es un orco, y no se puede confiar en ellos."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:515
msgid ""
"With all due respect, Alcatas, Ogesh has been nothing short of honourable "
"and helpful to us. He has welcomed my people, and Dvalin's, for the aid we "
"gave him."
msgstr ""
"Con el debido respeto, Alcatas, Ogesh ha sido nada menos que honorable y "
"útil con nosotros. Ha dado la bienvenida a mi pueblo, y al de Dvalin, por la "
"ayuda que le dimos."

#. [message], speaker=Alcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:519
msgid ""
"Well, you will pardon me, but I find it hard to trust people who do business "
"with orcs, especially if these people are Windsong, and especially if there "
"is an elf amongst these people..."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, me perdonarán, pero me cuesta confiar en gente que hace tratos con "
"orcos, especialmente si esa gente son Hijas del Viento, y especialmente si "
"hay una elfa entre ellos..."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:523
msgid ""
"(angry) You may be a kinsman, Alcatas, but watch out how you speak about "
"this elf! She's my... friend, and has been of great aid to all of us since "
"we began this journey!"
msgstr ""
"(enojado) Puede que seas un pariente, Alcatas, ¡pero cuidado con cómo hablas "
"de esta elfa! ¡Es mi... amiga, y ha sido de gran ayuda para todos nosotros "
"desde que comenzamos este viaje!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:527
msgid "Oh, Dvalin...!"
msgstr "¡Oh, Dvalin...!"

#. [message], speaker=Alcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:531
msgid ""
"Och, friend, if you say so, then I apologize, for I meant no offence... "
"Anyway, why don't you come in our caves and rest? I may take Dvalin there to "
"speak with our King Dulcatas, but the rest of you must wait in one of our "
"fringe villages until the king summons you."
msgstr ""
"Och, amigo, si tú lo dices, entonces me disculpo, no quise ofender... De "
"todos modos, ¿por qué no vienen a nuestras cuevas a descansar? Puedo llevar "
"a Dvalin a hablar con nuestro rey Dulcatas, pero el resto de ustedes debe "
"esperar en una de nuestras aldeas periféricas hasta que el rey los llame."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:535
msgid ""
"I thank your invitation, and I really want to speak with your king, but "
"right now we're in a quest to the Crystal Tower. But Dvalin, if you wish to "
"follow Alcatas, then you should go."
msgstr ""
"Agradezco tu invitación, y realmente quiero hablar con tu rey, pero ahora "
"mismo estamos en una misión hacia la Torre de Cristal. Pero Dvalin, si "
"deseas seguir a Alcatas, deberías hacerlo."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:539
msgid ""
"Well, I think I will; dwarves don't fare well in sandy or swampy terrains "
"anyway..."
msgstr ""
"Pues, creo que lo haré; de todos modos los enanos no nos va bien en terrenos "
"arenosos o pantanosos..."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:543
msgid ""
"Well, I... (looks indecisive) Well, I think I would only slow you dwarves "
"down if I follow you into the caves, so I'll stay with Myra..."
msgstr ""
"Pues, yo... (mira indecisa) Bueno, creo que solo los retrasaría si los sigo "
"a las cuevas, así que me quedaré con Myra..."

#. [message], speaker=Alcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:547
msgid ""
"(raising eyebrows) So, let's go into the tunnels of Idavellir, the kingdom "
"of the Motsoghnir!"
msgstr ""
"(alzando las cejas) Entonces, ¡vamos a los túneles de Idavellir, el reino de "
"los Motsoghnir!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:592
msgid "(blushing) W-why are you looking at me like this?"
msgstr "(sonrojada) ¿P-por qué me miras así?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:596
msgid "Ah, it's nothing, really. Come, we still have a long way to go."
msgstr "Ah, no es nada, de verdad. Ven, todavía nos queda un largo camino."

#. [unit], id=Garmo, type=Moon Blade
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:615
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:76
msgid "Garmo"
msgstr "Garmo"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:627
msgid "Mmmhrrffmm..."
msgstr "Mmmhrrffmm..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:631
msgid "Well, I think that is enough for you; Dispel Cipher!"
msgstr "Bueno, creo que ya es suficiente para ti; ¡Disipar Cifrado!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:635
msgid ""
"*cough cough* Argh... Tis' the Central Lake, amidst which the Dark Island, "
"hidden beneath the thick canopy, is found. Soon we shall see a river going "
"southwards; this will be the next part of our journey. But henceforth we "
"must be doubly careful, for we are entering the territory of the savage "
"wargs."
msgstr ""
"*tos tos* Argh... Es el Lago Central, en medio del cual se encuentra la Isla "
"Oscura, oculta bajo el espeso dosel. Pronto veremos un río que va hacia el "
"sur; esa será la siguiente parte de nuestro viaje. Pero de ahora en adelante "
"debemos ser doblemente cuidadosos, porque estamos entrando en el territorio "
"de los salvajes huargos."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:639
msgid "What are these wargs, exactly?"
msgstr "¿Qué son exactamente estos huargos?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:643
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, I have read about them in the same scrolls that told of the "
"vampires' genesis. The wargs are the result of shapeshifting experiments "
"conducted by the Windsong of old. They were originally normal humans whom we "
"managed to turn into wolf-like creatures, but we couldn't turn them back to "
"normal, and so the shapeshifting experience was considered a failure. Since "
"the wargs were violent and indomitable, we exiled them in this continent as "
"well."
msgstr ""
"Desafortunadamente, leí sobre ellos en los mismos pergaminos que contaban el "
"origen de los vampiros. Los huargos son el resultado de experimentos de "
"metamorfosis realizados por las antiguas Hijas del Viento. Originalmente "
"eran humanos normales a los que logramos convertir en criaturas parecidas a "
"lobos, pero no pudimos devolverlos a su forma normal, y por eso el "
"experimento se consideró un fracaso. Como los huargos eran violentos e "
"indomables, también los exiliamos en este continente."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:647
msgid ""
"That is the price you pay for meddling in what is not of your concern; only "
"the Great Gods have the right to play with the gears of life and creation."
msgstr ""
"Ese es el precio que pagan por entrometerse en lo que no les concierne; solo "
"los Grandes Dioses tienen derecho a jugar con los engranajes de la vida y la "
"creación."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:651
msgid ""
"Only fools and idiots cower before the darkness of ignorance; we must all "
"search for knowledge to become better, wiser and stronger people: this is "
"real enlightenment."
msgstr ""
"Solo los tontos e idiotas se acobardan ante la oscuridad de la ignorancia; "
"todos debemos buscar el conocimiento para convertirnos en personas mejores, "
"más sabias y más fuertes: eso es la verdadera iluminación."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:655
msgid ""
"Girls, it's not the time to quarrel. Even the slightest noise echoes "
"tremendously in these windswept mountains, and we don't know what we may "
"still find ahead of us."
msgstr ""
"Chicas, no es momento de pelear. Hasta el menor ruido resuena tremendamente "
"en estas montañas azotadas por el viento, y no sabemos qué podemos encontrar "
"más adelante."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:670
msgid ""
"sniff sniff... I smell humans nearby, but they have a different scent from "
"those of the south... But I recognize their clothing; they're Windsong!"
msgstr ""
"sniff sniff... Huelo humanos cerca, pero tienen un olor diferente al de los "
"del sur... ¡Pero reconozco su ropa; son Hijas del Viento!"

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:674
msgid ""
"Windsong! The monsters who have abandoned us in this infernal continent have "
"finally returned! Quick boys, get them before they escape!"
msgstr ""
"¡Hijas del Viento! ¡Los monstruos que nos abandonaron en este continente "
"infernal por fin han regresado! ¡Rápido muchachos, atrápenlas antes de que "
"escapen!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:678
msgid "By the Gods, does everyone on this continent hate you Windsong?!"
msgstr ""
"¡Por los dioses, todo el mundo en este continente odia a las Hijas del "
"Viento?!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:682
msgid "Well..."
msgstr "Bueno..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:686
msgid ""
"Wargs, I know our predecessors may have done you great harm, but if you give "
"us time, we would like to..."
msgstr ""
"Huargos, sé que nuestras predecesoras pudieron haberles hecho mucho daño, "
"pero si nos dan tiempo, nos gustaría..."

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:690
msgid ""
"Why am I still hearing their voice? Hurry up, boys, before the minotaurs or "
"those darn blood-suckers get to her first!"
msgstr ""
"¿Por qué sigo oyendo su voz? ¡Apúrense muchachos, antes de que los "
"minotauros o esos malditos chupasangre lleguen primero!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:694
msgid "Well, I think that's it for diplomacy..."
msgstr "Bueno, creo que eso es todo en cuanto a diplomacia..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:698
msgid ""
"(sighing) If we have no choice, then we must fight them too. But I'd really "
"like to convince the wargs that we're friendly. They may seem savage, but, "
"unlike the vampires, I sense no malice in them... Fight the other wargs, "
"warriors, but leave their leader for me; I think I may still talk with him."
msgstr ""
"(suspirando) Si no tenemos otra opción, entonces también tendremos que "
"pelear contra ellos. Pero realmente me gustaría convencer a los huargos de "
"que somos amigos. Pueden parecer salvajes, pero, a diferencia de los "
"vampiros, no siento malicia en ellos... Peleen contra los otros huargos, "
"guerreros, pero dejen a su líder para mí; creo que todavía puedo hablar con "
"él."

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:704
msgid "Defeat Garmo with Myra"
msgstr "Derrotar a Garmo con Myra"

#. [objective], condition=lose
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:728
msgid "Garmo killed by anyone other than Myra"
msgstr "Garmo muerto por cualquiera excepto Myra"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:752
msgid "No! We shouldn't have killed him!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡No deberíamos haberlo matado!"

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:769
msgid ""
"You... I always thought the Windsong were cruel, heartless creatures, but "
"your eyes are so placid, even kind... And these spirits that follow you, "
"they have about them the same energy of the dryads' natural magic..."
msgstr ""
"Tú... Siempre pensé que las Hijas del Viento eran criaturas crueles y sin "
"corazón, pero tus ojos son tan tranquilos, incluso bondadosos... Y estos "
"espíritus que te siguen tienen la misma energía que la magia natural de las "
"dríadas..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:773
msgid ""
"As I told you, I'm not here to harm you; and I'm willing to do anything in "
"my power to compensate our predecessors' atrocities. As for my elementals, I "
"don't know who these dryads are, but I do have power over the spirits of "
"nature."
msgstr ""
"Como te dije, no estoy aquí para hacerte daño; y estoy dispuesta a hacer "
"todo lo que esté en mi poder para compensar las atrocidades de nuestras "
"predecesoras. En cuanto a mis elementales, no sé quiénes son esas dríadas, "
"pero sí tengo poder sobre los espíritus de la naturaleza."

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:777
msgid ""
"Then you must be a friend of nature, just like us wargs! I now regret having "
"let my anger take over my reasoning; we wargs have learned to think and to "
"speak from the dryads and the dwarves, but we still find it hard to control "
"our deepest instincts..."
msgstr ""
"¡Entonces debes ser amiga de la naturaleza, igual que nosotros los huargos! "
"Ahora me arrepiento de haber dejado que la ira nublara mi razón; nosotros "
"los huargos aprendimos a pensar y a hablar de las dríadas y los enanos, pero "
"todavía nos cuesta controlar nuestros instintos más profundos..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:781
msgid ""
"For this you must not apologise, since you're not the one to be blamed for "
"what was done to you by the old Windsong. But I give you my word that we are "
"not what you think of us, and that we'll be more than happy to be your "
"friends; and, after finding an uninhabited land where we can rebuild our "
"civilization, even allies."
msgstr ""
"Por eso no tienes que disculparte, porque no eres tú el culpable de lo que "
"te hicieron las antiguas Hijas del Viento. Pero te doy mi palabra de que no "
"somos lo que piensas, y que estaremos más que felices de ser tus amigos; y, "
"una vez encontremos una tierra deshabitada donde reconstruir nuestra "
"civilización, incluso aliados."

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:785
msgid ""
"There is no uninhabited land in this continent, but, if you wish to claim "
"the Land's End Peninsula, we wargs would be happy to let you cross our lands "
"towards it; for that peninsula is populated by our mortal enemies, the "
"minotaurs and the vampires. I will call the other pack leaders to a "
"gathering at this island, and I will introduce you to them."
msgstr ""
"No hay tierra deshabitada en este continente, pero, si deseas reclamar la "
"Península del Fin de la Tierra, nosotros los huargos estaremos encantados de "
"dejar que crucen nuestras tierras para llegar a ella; porque esa península "
"está poblada por nuestros enemigos mortales, los minotauros y los vampiros. "
"Convocaré a los otros líderes de manada a una reunión en esta isla, y te los "
"presentaré."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:789
msgid ""
"I am truly interested in meeting them, but unfortunately I'm currently going "
"to the Sacred Desert to meet the Seraphin Lords, with whom I also want to "
"speak. But after I'm done with them, I shall visit you again."
msgstr ""
"Me interesa mucho conocerlos, pero lamentablemente ahora mismo voy al "
"Desierto Sagrado para reunirme con los Señores Serafines, con quienes "
"también quiero hablar. Pero cuando termine con ellos, los visitaré de nuevo."

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:793
msgid ""
"It is well; but I must warn you, tread lightly near them, and do not lower "
"your guard: for they are as shrewd as they are unpredictable."
msgstr ""
"Está bien; pero debo advertirte, ve con cuidado cerca de ellos y no bajes la "
"guardia: son tan astutos como impredecibles."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:797
msgid "How dare a savage such as you talk like this about..."
msgstr "¿Cómo se atreve un salvaje como tú a hablar así de...?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:801
msgid "Cipher of Silence..."
msgstr "¡Cifrado de Silencio...!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:810
msgid "Not ag-ggaahhh...!"
msgstr "¡No otra ve-ggaahhh...!"

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:814
msgid ""
"There is a river nearby that comes from the south; follow it, and you will "
"infallibly reach the Sacred Desert."
msgstr ""
"Hay un río cerca que viene del sur; síganlo y llegarán infaliblemente al "
"Desierto Sagrado."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:818
msgid "Thank you, noble Garmo."
msgstr "Gracias, noble Garmo."

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:829
msgid "Reach the end of the river that runs southwards"
msgstr "Llegar al final del río que corre hacia el sur"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:877
msgid ""
"This is the river Garmo talked about; let's follow its course, and find this "
"Crystal Tower..."
msgstr ""
"Este es el río del que habló Garmo; sigamos su curso y encontremos esa Torre "
"de Cristal..."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:886
msgid "Wait, we should first find the Motsoghnir dwarves!"
msgstr "¡Espera, primero deberíamos encontrar a los enanos Motsoghnir!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:978
msgid "No! Without her, we won't be able to reach the Crystal Tower!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡Sin ella no podremos llegar a la Torre de Cristal!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/24_The_Sun_Path.cfg:990
msgid ""
"We are taking far too much time only to cross the Sun Path, if we continue "
"like this we'll never reach the Crystal Tower!"
msgstr ""
"¡Estamos tardando demasiado solo en cruzar el Sendero del Sol, si seguimos "
"así nunca llegaremos a la Torre de Cristal!"

#. [scenario], id=25_Wings_Of_Rebellion
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:4
msgid "Wings of Rebellion"
msgstr "Alas de la Rebelión"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:23
msgid "Kill the rebel Zaal"
msgstr "Matar al rebelde Zaal"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:27
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:389
msgid "Kill the orcish leaders"
msgstr "Matar a los líderes orcos"

#. [objective], condition=lose
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:56
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:418
msgid "Death of Atron"
msgstr "Muerte de Atron"

#. [side], type=Celestial Herald
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:88
msgid "Atron"
msgstr "Atron"

#. [side], type=Celestial Herald
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:107
msgid "Zaal"
msgstr "Zaal"

#. [side], type=Celestial Herald
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:112
msgid "Rebels"
msgstr "Rebeldes"

#. [side], type=Orcish Sovereign
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:136
msgid "Hogar"
msgstr "Hogar"

#. [side], type=Orcish Sovereign
#. [side], type=Orcish Warlord
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:141
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:166
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:185
msgid "Orcs"
msgstr "Orcos"

#. [side], type=Orcish Warlord
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:161
msgid "Garag"
msgstr "Garag"

#. [side], type=Orcish Warlord
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:180
msgid "Erudush"
msgstr "Erudush"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:245
msgid ""
"Behold the glory and might of the Crystal Tower! Be honoured, foreigners, "
"for seldom has... Wait... What are those armies doing here?!"
msgstr ""
"¡Contemplad la gloria y el poder de la Torre de Cristal! Sienteos honrados, "
"extranjeros, porque pocas veces… Esperad… ¡¿Qué hacen esos ejércitos aquí?!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:269
msgid ""
"Seems like your 'glorious and mighty' tower is being besieged by a horde of "
"orcs..."
msgstr ""
"Parece que tu «gloriosa y poderosa» torre está siendo sitiada por una horda "
"de orcos…"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:273
msgid ""
"But... but... How dare they attack the Crystal Tower?! They shall be smitten "
"and sent to the deepest pits of the Underworld for this sacrilege! But look, "
"yonder comes more of our legions, led by my brother, Atron, and his good "
"friend Zaal!"
msgstr ""
"Pero… pero… ¡¿Cómo se atreven a atacar la Torre de Cristal?! ¡Serán "
"aniquilados y enviados a los más profundos abismos del Inframundo por este "
"sacrilegio! Pero mirad, allá vienen más de nuestras legiones, dirigidas por "
"mi hermano Atron y su buen amigo Zaal!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:277
msgid ""
"Are you sure that those legions are fighting on the same side...? Because "
"the soldiers of your comrade Zaal seem to be fighting those of your "
"brother..."
msgstr ""
"¿Estás segura de que esas legiones luchan en el mismo bando…? Porque los "
"soldados de tu camarada Zaal parecen estar luchando contra los de tu hermano…"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:281
msgid ""
"Cease thy blasphemous nonsense! How can you possibly think that Zaal, a "
"herald, would turn his blade against..."
msgstr ""
"¡Cesa con esa blasfemia! ¿Cómo puedes siquiera pensar que Zaal, un heraldo, "
"volvería su espada contra…"

#. [message], speaker=Atron
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:285
msgid ""
"Zaal, please listen to the voice of reason! Give up now and repent, and you "
"may still be forgiven! And look, an orcish horde comes from the east, taking "
"advantage of our inner conflict! Would you honestly see our beloved Crystal "
"Tower crumble?"
msgstr ""
"¡Zaal, escucha la voz de la razón! ¡Ríndete ahora y arrepiéntete, y aún "
"puedes ser perdonado! ¡Y mira, una horda orca viene del este aprovechando "
"nuestro conflicto interno! ¿De verdad quieres ver cómo se derrumba nuestra "
"amada Torre de Cristal?"

#. [message], speaker=Zaal
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:289
msgid ""
"I would see it so, my brother, for I have seen the truth about our order. It "
"pains me terribly, to turn my blade against the place I have always called "
"home, and against the people I counted as my friends, but I will not allow "
"this evil to take hold of this continent, not anymore."
msgstr ""
"Sí lo vería, hermano, porque he visto la verdad sobre nuestra orden. Me "
"duele terriblemente volver mi espada contra el lugar que siempre llamé hogar "
"y contra la gente que consideraba mis amigos, pero no permitiré que este mal "
"siga apoderándose de este continente, ya no más."

#. [message], speaker=Atron
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:293
msgid ""
"Zaal, Zaal, what has happened to you?... I will try to spare your life, "
"brother, to give you one further chance to repent, but I shall not let your "
"madness continue to plague our order!"
msgstr ""
"Zaal, Zaal, ¿qué te ha pasado…? Intentaré perdonarte la vida, hermano, para "
"dar una última oportunidad de arrepientas, ¡pero no dejaré que tu locura "
"siga asolando nuestra orden!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:297
msgid ""
"No... No! How can Zaal attack the Crystal Tower like this, with this orc "
"army threatening it...?"
msgstr ""
"No… ¡No! ¿Cómo puede Zaal atacar la Torre de Cristal así, con este ejército "
"orco amenazándola…?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:301
msgid ""
"Well, if your precious Lords are as powerful as you say, they will simply "
"swoop down on your enemies and kill them all, right?"
msgstr ""
"Bueno, si tus preciosos Señores son tan poderosos como dices, simplemente "
"bajarán en picado sobre vuestros enemigos y los matarán a todos, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:305
msgid ""
"(kneeling) Myra, I humbly beg you, help us break this siege, and I warrant "
"you we'll be forever indebted to you!"
msgstr ""
"(arrodillándose) Myra, te lo suplico humildemente, ayúdanos a romper este "
"asedio, ¡y te juro que estaremos en deuda contigo para siempre!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:309
msgid ""
"We shall help you then, as a further proof of our willingness to be your "
"friends and allies."
msgstr ""
"Entonces os ayudaremos, como prueba adicional de nuestra voluntad de ser "
"vuestros amigos y aliados."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:313
msgid "Well, so be it then... (sigh)"
msgstr "Bueno, pues que así sea… (suspira)"

#. [message], speaker=Atron
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:331
msgid ""
"The Lords' trials are endless! Yet another enemy approach from the north-"
msgstr ""
"¡Las pruebas de los Señores son interminables! ¡Otro enemigo se acerca desde "
"el norte-!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:335
msgid ""
"Hold, brother! Point not your troops at these people, for they come in peace!"
msgstr ""
"¡Detente, hermano! ¡No apuntes tus tropas a esta gente, porque vienen en son "
"de paz!"

#. [message], speaker=Atron
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:339
msgid ""
"My dear sister, finally you have returned! But who are those coming "
"alongside you?"
msgstr ""
"¡Querida hermana, por fin has vuelto! Pero ¿quiénes son los que vienen "
"contigo?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:343
msgid ""
"They're... They're the newcomers seen by the Seraphin Lords. For the moment "
"they have shown themselves honourable, and have pledged themselves to help "
"us break this siege!"
msgstr ""
"Son… Son los recién llegados que vieron los Señores Serafines. De momento se "
"han mostrado honorables y se han comprometido a ayudarnos a romper este "
"asedio!"

#. [message], speaker=Atron
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:347
msgid ""
"If you say so, sister, then I shall trust them, but only because it is you "
"who says so."
msgstr ""
"Si tú lo dices, hermana, entonces confiaré en ellos, pero solo porque eres "
"tú quien lo dice."

#. [message], speaker=Zaal
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:351
msgid ""
"I shall destroy anyone who complies with the corruption of the Crystal Tower."
msgstr ""
"Destruiré a cualquiera que se someta a la corrupción de la Torre de Cristal."

#. [message], speaker=Hogar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:355
msgid "And we will destroy anyone and anything that stands on our way!"
msgstr ""
"¡Y nosotros destruiremos a cualquiera y cualquier cosa que se interponga en "
"nuestro camino!"

#. [message], speaker=Zaal
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:367
msgid ""
"You, foreigner... Do not forget my words: you don't know who you are dealing "
"with..."
msgstr ""
"Tú, extranjera… No olvides mis palabras: no sabes con quién te estás "
"metiendo…"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:371
msgid "(sobbing) Why... why did you do this, Zaal?"
msgstr "(sollozando) ¿Por qué… por qué hiciste esto, Zaal?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:375
msgid ""
"If you wish, Liliel, you may withdraw from battle; you shouldn't go on "
"fighting like this..."
msgstr ""
"Si quieres, Liliel, puedes retirarte del combate; no deberías seguir "
"luchando así…"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:379
msgid ""
"No, I will not flee the battlefield; rather, I shall channel my sadness and "
"anger through my blade, and deliver these orcish barbarians righteous "
"justice!"
msgstr ""
"¡No, no huiré del campo de batalla! Al contrario, canalizaré mi tristeza y "
"mi rabia a través de mi espada y haré justicia a estos bárbaros orcos."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:383
msgid "Do as you wish..."
msgstr "Haz lo que quieras…"

#. [message], speaker=Hogar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:445
msgid ""
"Darn it! I was so close to finally destroying these pesky bird-people! But I "
"will not let this chance escape: I will give it everything I have got!"
msgstr ""
"¡Maldición! ¡Estuve tan cerca de destruir de una vez por todas a esta gente-"
"pájaro molesta! ¡Pero no dejaré pasar esta oportunidad: ¡lo daré todo!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:455
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:519
msgid "Uh-oh, he's called reinforcements, and lots of them!"
msgstr "¡Uy! ¡Ha llamado refuerzos, y muchos!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:459
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:523
msgid ""
"Let them come; the more orcish troops we defeat, the more these 'Seraphin "
"Lords' will be indebted to us!"
msgstr ""
"Que vengan; cuantos más orcos derrotemos, más nos deberán estos «Señores "
"Serafines»."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:463
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:527
msgid ""
"Myra, I don't like the idea of fleeing, but should we really keep fighting a "
"battle that is not even ours?"
msgstr ""
"Myra, no me gusta la idea de huir, pero ¿de verdad debemos seguir luchando "
"en una batalla que ni siquiera es nuestra?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:467
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:531
msgid ""
"Even if we left the battlefield, the orcs would catch up with us: they know "
"the land better than we do, and we don't move well across this sandy "
"terrain..."
msgstr ""
"Aunque abandonáramos el campo de batalla, los orcos nos alcanzarían: conocen "
"el terreno mejor que nosotros y no nos movemos bien por este terreno arenoso…"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:471
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:535
msgid ""
"Fear not, foreigners! Keep fighting bravely, that the Gods of Light will not "
"let us die like this!"
msgstr ""
"¡No temáis, extranjeros! ¡Seguid luchando con valor, que los Dioses de la "
"Luz no permitirán que muramos así!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:475
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:539
msgid ""
"Yeah, that is exactly what we need right now: that a god descends from the "
"Heavens to fight for us. Even then I'm not quite sure we'll solve this "
"situation. Myra, I'm telling you, if I die because I was ordered to defend "
"these bird-guys, I will kill you!"
msgstr ""
"Sí, eso es exactamente lo que necesitamos ahora: que un dios baje del Cielo "
"a a luchar por nosotros. Aun así no estoy segura de que solucionemos esto. "
"Myra, te lo digo, ¡si muero porque me ordenaron defender a estos tipos-"
"pájaro, te mataré!"

#. [message], speaker=Hogar
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:501
msgid ""
"I am running short of patience; let's just send out all our forces and stamp "
"out these pesky bird-people once and for all!"
msgstr ""
"Se me está acabando la paciencia; ¡enviemos todas nuestras fuerzas y "
"acabemos de una vez con esta gente-pájaro molesta!"

#. [message], speaker=Atron
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:549
msgid ""
"It was a long and arduous battle, but we have prevailed! In the name of the "
"Crystal Tower, I thank your aid, outsiders."
msgstr ""
"Fue una batalla larga y dura, ¡pero hemos vencido! En nombre de la Torre de "
"Cristal, agradezco vuestra ayuda, extranjeros."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:560
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:694
msgid "What was that?"
msgstr "¿Qué ha sido eso?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:564
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:698
msgid "The Celestial Trumpets! The Lords are coming!"
msgstr "¡Las Trompetas Celestiales! ¡Vienen los Señores!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:624
msgid ""
"So these are the Seraphin Lords? I thought Liliel was exagerating when she "
"spoke of their power, but I admit I was wrong; the mere energy they emanate "
"is overwhelming."
msgstr ""
"¿Así que estos son los Señores Serafines? Pensé que Liliel exageraba cuando "
"hablaba de su poder, pero admito que me equivocaba; la mera energía que "
"emanan es abrumadora."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:628
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:809
msgid ""
"It's unlike anything I have ever felt: it's not malicious like Svarballi's, "
"but it's not benign and kind like Nitiballi's either. It is..."
msgstr ""
"Es diferente a todo lo que he sentido nunca: no es maliciosa como la de "
"Svarballi, pero tampoco benigna y amable como la de Nitiballi. Es…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:632
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:813
msgid "...like a ruthless and killer force of good..."
msgstr "…como una fuerza del bien implacable y asesina…"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:636
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:824
msgid ""
"We have been watching you from above, Atron, as you faced this trial that we "
"have laid before you. And we have not found you lacking."
msgstr ""
"Hemos estado observándote desde lo alto, Atron, mientras enfrentabas la "
"prueba que te hemos impuesto. Y no te hemos encontrado falto."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:640
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:828
msgid "So <i>you</i> brought all those orcs here to fight your own people?!"
msgstr ""
"¡¿Entonces <i>fueron ustedes</i> quienes trajeron a todos esos orcos aquí "
"para que lucharan contra su propia gente?!"

#. [message], speaker=Ouranis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:644
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:832
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, the same cannot be said of thy sister, Liliel, whom we have "
"sent to deal with the strangers, and who brought them here instead..."
msgstr ""
"Desgraciadamente, no puede decirse lo mismo de tu hermana Liliel, a quien "
"enviamos a tratar con los extranjeros y que en cambio los trajo aquí…"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:648
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:836
msgid "M-my Lords, I..."
msgstr "M-mis Señores, yo…"

#. [message], speaker=Pius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:652
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:840
msgid ""
"But we must not judge her harshly; for even we had not foreseen this "
"stranger wielded such immense power."
msgstr ""
"Pero no debemos juzgarla con dureza; pues ni siquiera nosotros previmos que "
"esta extranjera tuviera tanto poder."

#. [message], speaker=Luces
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:656
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:844
msgid ""
"Furthermore, we must not forget the truthfulness and assistance shown by "
"this foreign young woman."
msgstr ""
"Además, no debemos olvidar la sinceridad y la ayuda mostrada por esta joven "
"extranjera."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:660
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:848
msgid ""
"Great Lords, I am Myra of Hiera'Shirsha, and I lead a group of refugees from "
"a war in a faraway land. We have come to this continent searching for a land "
"where we could live in peace, and thus we seek no quarrel with any of our "
"future neighbours. For this reason I have come here, to prove to you that "
"our intentions are the best..."
msgstr ""
"Grandes Señores, soy Myra de Hiera’Shirsha y lidero a un grupo de refugiados "
"de una guerra en una tierra lejana. Hemos venido a este continente en busca "
"de una tierra donde podamos vivir en paz, y por eso no buscamos pelea con "
"ninguno de nuestros futuros vecinos. Por eso he venido aquí, para "
"demostrarles que nuestras intenciones son las mejores…"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:664
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:852
msgid ""
"We shall see about that; now, Atron, I commission thee to repair the damages "
"suffered by our fortress in this battle, and to tend to the wounded. Myra of "
"Hiera'Shirsha and her companions, meet us at the Celestial Hall; Liliel, you "
"must come as well."
msgstr ""
"Ya veremos; ahora, Atron, te encargo reparar los daños sufridos por nuestra "
"fortaleza en esta batalla y atender a los heridos. Myra de Hiera’Shirsha y "
"sus compañeros, encuéntrennos en el Salón Celestial; Liliel, tú también "
"debes venir."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:668
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:856
msgid "A-as you wish, my Lords..."
msgstr "C-como deseen, mis Señores…"

#. [message], speaker=Atron
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:690
msgid "Finally, our prayers have been attended!"
msgstr "¡Por fin han escuchado nuestras plegarias!"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:737
msgid ""
"Thou hast dared turn thy unworthy eyes to the holy Crystal Tower, and for "
"this blasphemy thou hast received the fitting punishment!"
msgstr ""
"¡Osasteis alzar vuestros ojos indignos hacia la santa Torre, y por esta "
"blasfemia habéis recibido el castigo merecido!"

#. [message], speaker=Ouranis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:781
msgid "WITNESS THE POWER OF THE HEAVENS!"
msgstr "¡CONTEMPLAD EL PODER DE LOS CIELOS!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:805
msgid "Incredible... So this is the power of the Seraphin Lords?"
msgstr "Increíble… ¿Así que este es el poder de los Señores Serafines?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:817
msgid ""
"I wonder why they let so many of us, including their own, die fighting the "
"orcs, when they could have smitten them all whenever they wanted..."
msgstr ""
"Me pregunto por qué dejaron morir a tantos de nosotros, incluidos los suyos, "
"luchando contra los orcos, cuando podrían haberlos aniquilado cuando "
"quisieran…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:971
msgid ""
"No! Without her intervention, I doubt the Seraphin Lords will be willing to "
"talk with us!"
msgstr ""
"¡No! ¡Sin su intervención, dudo que los Señores Serafines quieran hablar con "
"nosotros!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion.cfg:985
msgid ""
"NO! You let my brother die, treacherous foreigners! Now I do everything in "
"my power to convince the Lords to smite you!"
msgstr ""
"¡NO! ¡Dejasteis morir a mi hermano, extranjeros traidores! ¡Ahora haré todo "
"lo que esté en mi poder para convencer a los Señores de que os aniquilen!"

#. [scenario], id=25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:4
msgid "Wings of Rebellion: the Celestial Hall"
msgstr "Alas de Rebelión: la Sala Celestial"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:80
msgid ""
"Let the thirty-thousandth, nine-hundredth, seventy-seventh audience at the "
"Celestial Hall begin. Know that this is the first time in centuries that a "
"foreigner is graced with an audience with the Lords of the Crystal Tower; I "
"myself was but a young Herald when such thing happened."
msgstr ""
"Que comience la audiencia número treinta mil novecientos setenta y siete en "
"la Sala Celestial. Sabed que es la primera vez en siglos que un extranjero "
"recibe audiencia con los Señores de la Torre de Cristal; yo mismo era solo "
"un joven Heraldo cuando ocurrió algo así."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:84
msgid ""
"We are indeed honoured, Seraphin Lords, but I must say I feel at "
"disadvantage here, for you know who I am, but I still don't know who you are."
msgstr ""
"Estamos en verdad honrados, Señores Serafines, pero debo decir que me siento "
"que estoy en desventaja aquí, porque vosotros sabéis quién soy, pero yo aún "
"no sé quiénes sois."

#. [message], speaker=Luces
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:88
msgid ""
"Fair enough. I am Luces, and these are Lords Grigorius, Pius and Ouranis. We "
"command the Celestials, the Chosen People of the Creator, and we have lived "
"in this continent since the Ancient Ones ceased to walk on Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Justo es. Yo soy Luces y estos son los señores Grigorius, Pius y Ouranis. "
"Comandamos a los celestiales, el Pueblo Elegido del Creador, y hemos vivido "
"en este continente desde que los Antiguos dejaron de caminar por Irdya."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:92
msgid ""
"Ancient Ones, you say? I have heard of them, weren't they the creators of "
"the High Dragons?"
msgstr ""
"¿Antiguos, decís… He oído hablar de ellos, ¿no fueron los creadores de los "
"Dragones Supremos?"

#. [message], speaker=Ouranis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:96
msgid ""
"The tale of the High Dragons is but one of the stories regarding the Ancient "
"Ones. My brothers, should we tell these foreigners more about our history...?"
msgstr ""
"La historia de los Dragones Supremos es solo una de las leyendas sobre los "
"Antiguos. Hermanos míos, ¿deberíamos contar a estos extranjeros más sobre "
"nuestra historia…?"

#. [message], speaker=Pius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:100
msgid ""
"I find no argument against it; after all, it is always a good thing to throw "
"some of the light of truth over the ignorant."
msgstr ""
"No encuentro argumento en contra; al fin y al cabo, siempre es bueno arrojar "
"algo de luz de la verdad sobre los ignorantes."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:104
msgid "Argh, they're so..."
msgstr "Argh, son tan…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:108
msgid ""
"Psst! (turning to the Seraphins) Indeed, I am very interested in learning "
"more about them."
msgstr ""
"¡Psst! (volviéndose hacia los serafines) En efecto, estoy muy interesada en "
"saber más sobre ellos."

#. [message], speaker=Luces
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:112
msgid ""
"The Ancient Ones are beings of incommensurable power and wisdom who have "
"been aeons ago. Not only did they create this universe and everything that "
"exists in it, but they also watched over it for most of its existence. "
"Millennia ago, they decided to leave Irdya thriving on its own, leaving, in "
"their place, the famous High Dragons; however, the servants of the Creator - "
"who gave birth to the Ancient Ones - were not satisfied with the draconic "
"wardens, and asked to stay here as well, to make sure the work of the "
"Ancient Ones was preserved as it was meant to be."
msgstr ""
"Los Antiguos son seres de poder y sabiduría inconmensurables que existieron "
"eones atrás. No solo crearon este universo y todo lo que existe en él, sino "
"que también lo vigilaron durante la mayor parte de su existencia. Hace "
"milenios decidieron dejar que Irdya prosperara por sí sola, dejando en su "
"lugar a los famosos Dragones Supremos; sin embargo, los servidores del "
"Creador —que dio origen a los Antiguos— no estaban satisfechos con los "
"guardianes dracónicos y pidieron quedarse aquí también, para asegurarse de "
"que la obra de los Antiguos se preservara tal como estaba destinada."

#. [message], speaker=Luces
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:116
msgid ""
"These servants were beings of great power, like lesser Gods, but they were "
"mortal like any child of this earth. To make sure their work outlasted their "
"lifespan, they mingled with human men and women, thus creating a new breed "
"of mighty humans: they gave origin to us, the Celestials. Since then, we "
"have combated evil and corruption on Irdya as we could, especially after the "
"fall of the Sky Dragon. As Lord Agniballi already watched over the Great "
"Continent and the Vast Sea, we limited our jurisdiction to this continent, "
"helping maintain the balance of power between the many native races, and "
"trying - regretfully with little success - to enlighten them with the "
"message of order and harmony of the Creator."
msgstr ""
"Estos servidores eran seres de gran poder, como dioses menores, pero eran "
"mortales como cualquier ser vivo. Para asegurarse de que su obra perdurara "
"más allá de su vida, se mezclaron con mujeres humanas, creando así una nueva "
"raza de humanos poderosos: nos dieron origen a nosotros, los celestiales. "
"Desde entonces hemos combatido el mal y la corrupción en Irdya como hemos "
"podido, especialmente después de la caída del Dragón del Cielo. Como lord "
"Agniballi ya vigilaba el Gran Continente y el Mar Inmenso, limitamos nuestra "
"jurisdicción a este continente, ayudando a mantener el equilibrio de poder "
"entre las muchas razas nativas e intentando —lamentablemente con poco éxito— "
"iluminarlos con el mensaje de orden y armonía del Creador."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:120
msgid ""
"It is an interesting story indeed... What's more interesting, you say the "
"High Dragons were created by the same beings from whom you claim descent; he "
"too based his actions on 'order and harmony'... Even if his understanding of "
"these concepts was rather twisted."
msgstr ""
"Es una historia interesante en verdad… Lo más interesante es que decís que "
"los Dragones Supremos fueron creados por los mismos seres de los que "
"afirmáis descender; él también basó sus acciones en «orden y armonía»… "
"Aunque su comprensión de esos conceptos estaba bastante retorcida."

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:124
msgid "So you are survivors from that war in the Great Continent...?"
msgstr "¿Así que sois supervivientes de esa guerra en el Gran Continente…?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:128
msgid "Yes... Do you know of it?"
msgstr "Sí… ¿Sabéis de ella?"

#. [message], speaker=Luces
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:132
msgid ""
"Lord Grigorius, with his far-reaching sight, was able to notice a grave "
"disturbance at the heart of the Great Continent. He was also capable of "
"learning of Lord Agniballi's death, and the awakening of the Sky Dragon. So "
"it is true that Svarballi was defeated?"
msgstr ""
"Lord Grigorius, con su vista de largo alcance, pudo notar una grave "
"perturbación en el corazón del Gran Continente. También fue capaz de saber "
"de la muerte de lord Agniballi y del despertar del Dragón del Cielo. "
"¿Entonces es cierto que Svarballi fue derrotado?"

#. [message], speaker=Ouranis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:136
msgid ""
"And how could mere mortals have defeated the noble Sky Dragon, who was once "
"called the Heir of the Creator herself?"
msgstr ""
"¿Y cómo pudieron simples mortales derrotar al noble Dragón del Cielo, que "
"una vez fue llamado el Heredero de la propia Creadora?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:140
msgid "<i>Noble Sky Dragon</i>? How can you talk of that monster like this?"
msgstr ""
"¿<i>Noble Dragón del Cielo</i>? ¿Cómo podéis hablar de ese monstruo así?"

#. [message], speaker=Pius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:144
msgid "How dare <i>you</i> talk like this to the Seraphin Lords?!"
msgstr "¡¿Cómo te atreves <i>tú</i> a hablar así a los Señores Serafines?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:148
msgid ""
"You will forgive us, Lords; Akashia may speak brashly, but she's right when "
"she calls Svarballi a monster. He caused the deaths of thousands of "
"innocents-"
msgstr ""
"Nos perdonaréis, señores; Akashia puede hablar con brusquedad, pero tiene "
"razón al llamar monstruo a Svarballi. Causó la muerte de miles de inocentes-"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:152
msgid ""
"Not a single being on this planet is truly innocent, young girl, everyone is "
"flawed to a greater or lesser extent, and every soul is marred by a long "
"list of sins. As for the Sky Dragon, he came directly out of the hands of "
"the Creator; I acknowledge he might have forgotten his original duty, but I "
"warrant you that we would have reminded him of that, had we just had an "
"opportunity to speak with him."
msgstr ""
"Ningún ser en este planeta es verdaderamente inocente, muchacha, todos están "
"manchados en mayor o menor medida, y cada alma lleva una larga lista de "
"pecados. En cuanto al Dragón del Cielo, salió directamente de las manos del "
"Creador; reconozco que pudo haber olvidado su deber original, pero os "
"aseguro que le habríamos recordado cuál era, si hubiéramos tenido la "
"oportunidad de hablar con él."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:156
msgid ""
"I... I will not discuss this, not when there are more urgent matters at "
"hand..."
msgstr "Yo… No discutiré esto, no cuando hay asuntos más urgentes entre manos…"

#. [message], speaker=Luces
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:160
msgid ""
"Wise words. All of us have sensed two great powers reach our continent some "
"days ago; one belonged to you and was friendly and kind, but the other was "
"evil, and even greater than yours. We want to know what the latter is."
msgstr ""
"Palabras sabias. Todos hemos sentido que dos grandes poderes llegaron a "
"nuestro continente hace algunos días; uno os pertenecía a vos y era amistoso "
"y bondadoso, pero el otro era maligno y aún mayor que el vuestro. Queremos "
"saber qué es este último."

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:164
msgid ""
"Furthermore, I want to know how can a mere human have such tremendous power "
"within her own body?"
msgstr ""
"Además, quiero saber cómo puede una simple humana tener tanto poder tremendo "
"dentro de su propio cuerpo."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:168
msgid ""
"My power comes from my connection to the spirits of nature. Besides, I have "
"recently acquired this trident, forged by the Water Dragon Nitiballi, and "
"which augments my power even more."
msgstr ""
"Mi poder viene de mi conexión con los espíritus de la naturaleza. Además, "
"recientemente adquirí este tridente, forjado por el Dragón del Agua "
"Nitiballi, y que aumenta aún más mi poder."

#. [message], speaker=Ouranis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:172
msgid ""
"A wielder of the heretic natural arts, you say? It is all too known to us "
"how the Creator looked down on the spirits of nature, who dare call "
"themselves the 'true wardens of Irdya'..."
msgstr ""
"¿Una usuaria de las herejes artes naturales, dices? Nos es bien conocido "
"cómo el Creador despreciaba a los espíritus de la naturaleza, que se atreven "
"a llamarse los «verdaderos guardianes de Irdya»…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:176
msgid ""
"Yet it were the spirits of nature and thousand others who helped stop "
"Svarballi's insanity, not your precious Creator!"
msgstr ""
"¡Y sin embargo fueron los espíritus de la naturaleza y miles más los que "
"ayudaron a detener la locura de Svarballi, ¡no vuestro precioso Creador!"

#. [message], speaker=Pius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:180
msgid ""
"Someone should really teach you to hold your tongue before your betters, "
"impudent human girl!"
msgstr ""
"¡Alguien debería enseñarte a controlar la lengua ante tus superiores, "
"insolente humana!"

#. [message], speaker=Luces
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:184
msgid ""
"Be merciful, my brothers, for she is merely a human. Now, you must tell us "
"about this evil artefact you carry with you, young Myra."
msgstr ""
"Sean misericordiosos, hermanos míos, pues solo es humana. Ahora, debes "
"contarnos sobre este artefacto maligno que llevas contigo, joven Myra."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:188
msgid ""
"It is a container of countless evil spirits who were defeated and locked by "
"my deceased foster-mother, High Ascendant Maat. She has entrusted me with "
"keeping it, lest it would fall into the wrong hands and be used to wreak "
"more chaos."
msgstr ""
"Es un contenedor de innumerables espíritus malignos que fueron derrotados y "
"encerrados por mi difunta madre adoptiva, la Gran Ascendente Maat. Me lo "
"confió para que lo guardara, no fuera a caer en malas manos y se usara para "
"causar más caos."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:192
msgid "*My goodness, I never thought she was such an unabashed liar...*"
msgstr "*Por todos los dioses, nunca pensé que fuera tan descarada mintiendo…*"

#. [message], speaker=Pius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:196
msgid ""
"And you brought it to our home, I see... Maybe we should keep it; as you "
"must have learned by now, we are against the powers of evil, and so we will "
"keep it safely away from evildoers. The Windsong, on the other hand, have a "
"history of using their own power in wrong, wrong ways..."
msgstr ""
"Y lo has traído a nuestra casa, ya veo… Quizá deberíamos quedárnoslo; como "
"habréis aprendido ya, nosotros estamos en contra de los poderes del mal, y "
"así lo mantendremos a salvo de malhechores. Las Hijas del Viento, en cambio, "
"tienen una historia de usar su propio poder de formas equivocadas, muy "
"equivocadas…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:200
msgid ""
"Hasn't everyone else? Trolls have tales of how the dwarves stole their "
"greatest artefact; elves still weep the curse brought upon one of their "
"kingdoms by an elven sage's lust for power; decades ago a power-hungry "
"Aragwaithi king nearly ruined his entire civilization; and even now the "
"Great Continent burns for the ambition of dragons. Even the legacy of the "
"Ancient Ones is not flawless, as the Sky Dragon's rampage proves. Yet why is "
"it that the Windsong are constantly shamed and blamed for the mistakes of "
"some of us?"
msgstr ""
"¿Acaso no lo ha hecho todo el mundo? Los trolls tienen historias de cómo los "
"enanos robaron su artefacto más grande; los elfos aún lloran la maldición "
"que un sabio elfo trajo sobre uno de sus reinos por su ansia de poder; hace "
"décadas un rey aragwaithi hambriento de poder casi arruinó toda su "
"civilización; y ahora mismo el Gran Continente arde por la ambición de los "
"dragones. Incluso el legado de los Antiguos no es impecable, como demuestra "
"la masacre del Dragón del Cielo. ¿Y aun así por qué las Hijas del Viento "
"somos constantemente avergonzadas y culpadas por los errores de algunas de "
"nosotras?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:204
msgid ""
"I promise you that we are not careless like some of our predecessors. We "
"want to prove that by protecting this jewel; please, do not deny us that."
msgstr ""
"Os prometo que no somos descuidadas como algunos de nuestros predecesores. "
"Queremos demostrarlo protegiendo esta joya; por favor, no nos neguéis eso."

#. [message], speaker=Luces
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:208
msgid ""
"Perhaps she means well; perhaps she should be given a chance to prove "
"herself. What do you have to say, my brothers?"
msgstr ""
"Tal vez tenga buenas intenciones; tal vez debería dársele la oportunidad de "
"demostrarlo. ¿Qué tenéis que decir, hermanos míos?"

#. [message], speaker=Pius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:212
msgid ""
"This is a conflicting matter. That these foreigners count Windsong among "
"their numbers is but one of the reasons they should not be trusted, yet they "
"have showed our kinswoman Liliel mercy, and they have also fought for us in "
"Atron's trial. Maybe there can be peaceful coexistence between our peoples, "
"and so we will not stop you from settling here."
msgstr ""
"Es un asunto conflictivo. Que estos extranjeros cuenten con Hijas del Viento "
"entre sus filas es solo una de las razones por las que no deberían ser "
"confiables, sin embargo mostraron misericordia con nuestra pariente Liliel y "
"también lucharon por nosotros en el juicio de Atron. Tal vez pueda haber "
"coexistencia pacífica entre nuestros pueblos, y por eso no os impediremos "
"asentaros aquí."

#. [message], speaker=Ouranis
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:216
msgid ""
"But you must never forget that we will keep constant watch over you; if we "
"notice any sign that you are going to use this evil jewel, you shall see our "
"legions rising over your lands."
msgstr ""
"Pero nunca olvidéis que os vigilaremos constantemente; si notamos cualquier "
"señal de que vais a usar esta joya maligna, veréis nuestras legiones alzarse "
"sobre vuestras tierras."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:220
msgid "I thank your generosity, great lords."
msgstr "Agradezco vuestra generosidad, grandes señores."

#. [message], speaker=Luces
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:224
msgid ""
"You may leave; from now on, this audience will discuss Liliel's misdoings."
msgstr ""
"Podéis iros; de ahora en adelante, esta audiencia discutirá las fechorías de "
"Liliel."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:234
msgid "By all Nine Hells, they're unbelievably, appallingly arrogant!"
msgstr ""
"¡Por los Nueve Infiernos, son increíblemente, espantosamente arrogantes!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:238
msgid ""
"I too didn't like them in the least, but, just as Garmo said, we must tread "
"lightly with them; I'm sure you have noticed the vastness of their power."
msgstr ""
"A mí tampoco me gustaron nada, pero, como dijo Garmo, debemos andar con pies "
"de plomo con ellos; estoy segura de que habéis notado la inmensidad de su "
"poder."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:242
msgid ""
"I have, as I have noticed that Zaal has uncovered some dire secret involving "
"these Seraphins. I'm telling you, I'd happily trade half of all our "
"remaining scrolls just to know what made him rebel against these Seraphins..."
msgstr ""
"Lo he notado, como he notado que Zaal descubrió algún oscuro secreto "
"relacionado con estos serafines. Os lo digo, cambiaría gustoso la mitad de "
"todos nuestros pergaminos restantes solo por saber qué le hizo rebelarse "
"contra estos serafines…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:246
msgid ""
"As would I, but now we have other things to worry about; and, at least until "
"we're strong again, we'll have to accept the Celestials' supremacy."
msgstr ""
"Yo también, pero ahora tenemos otras cosas de qué preocuparnos; y, al menos "
"hasta que volvamos a ser fuertes, tendremos que aceptar la supremacía de los "
"celestiales."

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/25_Wings_Of_Rebellion_b.cfg:259
msgid ""
"*You may have cheated these short-sighted brothers of mine, Myra of "
"Hiera'Shirsha, but you haven't cheated me. I know exactly what lies within "
"this jewel, and I will not allow it to remain in your possession for long. I "
"will wait; and, when you least expect it, I shall take this jewel from you!*"
msgstr ""
"*Puede que hayas engañado a estos hermanos míos cortos de vista, Myra de "
"Hiera’Shirsha, pero a mí no me has engañado. Sé exactamente qué hay dentro "
"de esta joya y no permitiré que siga en tu posesión mucho tiempo. Esperaré; "
"y, cuando menos te lo esperes, te arrebataré esta joya.*"

#. [scenario], id=26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:4
msgid "The Promise of the Rising Sun"
msgstr "La Promesa del Sol Naciente"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:21
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:408
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/27_The_Rise_Of_MaatKare.cfg:21
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/28_Embers_Of_War.cfg:21
msgid "Defeat all enemy leaders"
msgstr "Derrotar a todos los líderes enemigos"

#. [unit], id=Yara, type=Water Nymph
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:84
msgid "Yara"
msgstr "Yara"

#. [unit], id=Dulcatol, type=Warrior Warg
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:98
msgid "Dulcatol"
msgstr "Dulcatol"

#. [unit], id=Aldrol, type=Warrior Warg
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:112
msgid "Aldrol"
msgstr "Aldrol"

#. [unit], id=Ignis, type=Flame Spirit
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:127
msgid "Ignis"
msgstr "Ignis"

#. [side], type=Minotaur Elder
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:142
msgid "Adebaran"
msgstr "Adebaran"

#. [side], type=Methusalem
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:165
msgid "Aleron"
msgstr "Aleron"

#. [side], type=Warrior Carapace
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:191
msgid "Kurmak"
msgstr "Kurmak"

#. [side], type=Warrior Carapace
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:196
msgid "Carapces"
msgstr "Carapaces"

#. [side]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:217
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:99
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:111
msgid "Dwarves"
msgstr "Enanos"

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:274
msgid ""
"It took us a few more days than I expected, but we have finally reached the "
"Land's End Peninsula. It is a large region, and you will find other bands of "
"vampires, gnolls, carapaces and minotaurs all over it; but this is where "
"their largest settlements are. Destroy them, and many other smaller "
"settlements will probably move somewhere else."
msgstr ""
"Nos llevó unos días más de lo que esperaba, pero finalmente hemos llegado a "
"la Península del Fin de la Tierra. Es una región grande y encontraréis "
"bandas de vampiros, gnolls, carapaces y minotauros por todas partes; pero "
"aquí es donde están sus asentamientos más grandes. Destruidlos y muchos "
"otros asentamientos menores probablemente se mudarán a otro lugar."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:278
msgid "They live quite close to each other; are they allies or what?"
msgstr "Viven bastante cerca unos de otros; ¿son aliados o qué?"

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:282
msgid ""
"We don't know much about them, but it seems like they have managed to build "
"some sort of symbiosis: they help and defend each other, venting their own "
"rage and violence towards other bands of minotaurs, vampires and also wargs. "
"It will be no easy battle for us, be warned."
msgstr ""
"No sabemos mucho de ellos, pero parece que han logrado crear algún tipo de "
"simbiosis: se ayudan y se defienden entre sí, descargando su propia rabia y "
"violencia contra otras bandas de minotauros, vampiros y también huargos. No "
"será una batalla fácil para nosotros, estad advertidos."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:286
msgid "Then we won't face anything we haven't already."
msgstr "Entonces no enfrentaremos nada que no hayamos enfrentado ya."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:290
msgid "Indeed we won't..."
msgstr "En efecto no lo haremos…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:294
msgid ""
"(turning to her people) Aragwaithi, Windsong and Hannuks! For years we have "
"wandered the world, from the Aragwaith Meadows to this continent across the "
"vast ocean; we faced danger after danger, we lost many of our own and we "
"gained new friends and allies. All of our trials, all of our battles have "
"led us to this region that stretches before your eyes: the Land's End "
"peninsula! This is our reward, my people; this is the land I promised to you "
"on the ruins of the great Garet-Desh; this is where we rebuild our "
"civilisation, just as my mother, the High Ascendant Maat, dreamed! So, my "
"people, do not falter now; for the next time we sing our victory song, we "
"sing it on the soil of our new home!"
msgstr ""
"(volviéndose hacia su gente) ¡Aragwaithi, Hijas del Viento y hannuk! Durante "
"años hemos vagado por el mundo, desde los Prados Aragwaithi hasta este "
"continente al otro lado del vasto océano; enfrentamos peligro tras peligro, "
"perdimos a muchos de los nuestros y ganamos nuevos amigos y aliados. Todas "
"nuestras pruebas, todas nuestras batallas nos han traído a esta región que "
"se extiende ante vuestros ojos: ¡la península del Fin de la Tierra! ¡Esta es "
"nuestra recompensa, pueblo mío; esta es la tierra que os prometí sobre las "
"ruinas del gran Garet-Desh; aquí es donde reconstruiremos nuestra "
"civilización, tal como soñó mi madre, la Gran Ascendente Maat! ¡Así que, "
"pueblo mío, no flaqueéis ahora; porque la próxima vez que cantemos nuestra "
"canción de victoria, la cantaremos sobre el suelo de nuestro nuevo hogar!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:298
msgid "You have heard our Ascendant, Windsong! Now, CHARGE!"
msgstr "¡Habéis oído a nuestra Ascendente, Hijas del Viento! ¡Ahora, CARGA!"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:302
msgid "For the glory of the Meadows!"
msgstr "¡Por la gloria de los Prados!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:306
msgid "For the fortitude of the steppes!"
msgstr "¡Por la fortaleza de las estepas!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:310
msgid "For the fallen heroes of the Last War!"
msgstr "¡Por los héroes caídos de la Última Guerra!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:314
msgid "For our friends and loved ones!"
msgstr "¡Por nuestros amigos y seres queridos!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:318
msgid "FOR OUR FUTURE! ATTACK!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡POR NUESTRO FUTURO! ¡ATAQUE!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:382
msgid "Dvalin! How did you know we were here?"
msgstr "¡Dvalin! ¿Cómo sabías que estábamos aquí?"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:386
msgid ""
"Och, some of those impossibly fast girls of yours have found us and told us "
"everything."
msgstr ""
"Och, algunas de esas chicas vuestras imposibles de rápidas nos encontraron y "
"nos lo contaron todo."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:390
msgid ""
"But you have already found a home for your people, you didn't need to risk "
"more dwarvish lives coming here..."
msgstr ""
"Pero ya habéis encontrado un hogar para vuestro pueblo, no necesitabais "
"arriesgar más vidas enanas viniendo aquí…"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:394
msgid ""
"We have been fighting side by side for half of Irdya, and I have been "
"fighting by your side for a longer time than either Alenya, Ravyan or "
"Jevyan, did you really think I would not partake of this last battle? I just "
"apologise for being late; you know, I can't change the fact that my legs are "
"a bit short..."
msgstr ""
"Hemos estado luchando codo con codo por medio Irdya y yo he estado luchando "
"a tu lado más tiempo que Alenya, Ravyan o Jevyan, ¿de verdad creías que no "
"participaría en esta última batalla? Solo me disculpo por llegar tarde; "
"sabes, no puedo cambiar el hecho de que mis piernas son un poco cortas…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:398
msgid ""
"Wonderful Dvalin, it is I who should apologise for not inviting you to this "
"battle!"
msgstr ""
"¡Maravilloso Dvalin, soy yo quien debería disculparse por no invitarte a "
"esta batalla!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:402
msgid ""
"You can make amends by giving me some barrels of that wonderful Hannuk "
"beverage! Now boys, let's introduce these blood-suckers and bull-men to our "
"axes again!"
msgstr ""
"¡Puedes compensarlo dándome algunos barriles de esa maravillosa bebida "
"hannuk! ¡Ahora muchachos, volvamos a presentar a estos chupasangres y "
"hombres-toro a nuestras hachas!"

#. [objectives]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:444
msgid ""
"Note: The dwarves that once fought for Myra are now under Dvalin's command"
msgstr ""
"Nota: Los enanos que antes luchaban para Myra ahora están bajo el mando de "
"Dvalin"

#. [message], speaker=Garmo
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:461
msgid "Alas, I will not see your dream coming true, my friend..."
msgstr "Ay, no veré tu sueño hacerse realidad, amiga mía…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:465
msgid ""
"We have known each other for so little, but you were a loyal friend to us, "
"brave Garmo. You will live on in the memory of our people, and your name "
"will be engraved in our history forever."
msgstr ""
"Hemos estado juntos tan poco tiempo, pero fuiste un amigo leal para "
"nosotros, valiente Garmo. Vivirás en la memoria de nuestro pueblo y tu "
"nombre quedará grabado en nuestra historia para siempre."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:478
msgid "VICTORY IS OURS!"
msgstr "¡¡¡LA VICTORIA ES NUESTRA!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:482
msgid ""
"I can barely believe it... Our ordeal is over! We have found a new land!"
msgstr ""
"Apenas puedo creerlo… ¡Nuestra odisea ha terminado! ¡Hemos encontrado una "
"nueva tierra!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:486
msgid ""
"*Wherever you are now, Ysara, look to this land: this is where we shall "
"build the place we dreamed of, a place of respect and peace between Hannuks "
"and Aragwaithi...*"
msgstr ""
"*Dondequiera que estés ahora, Ysara, mira esta tierra: aquí es donde "
"construiremos el lugar con el que soñamos, un lugar de respeto y paz entre "
"hannuk y aragwaithi…*"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:490
msgid "We have succeeded, mother... We have finally succeeded..."
msgstr "Lo hemos logrado, madre… Por fin lo hemos logrado…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:494
msgid ""
"There is something still puzzling me, though: how will this new city be "
"called? Will its name be Aragwaithi or Hannuk?"
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, hay algo que aún me desconcierta: ¿cómo se llamará esta nueva "
"ciudad? ¿Será un nombre aragwaithi o hannuk?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:498
msgid ""
"I have been thinking of a name that is neither Aragwaithi nor Hannuk, and "
"which would please both peoples alike: the name of a woman who had no "
"homeland, but who was accepted, respected and loved by all, and who was "
"always willing to help people regardless of their background... I was "
"thinking about naming our new city Maat'Kare, which, in a tongue spoken by "
"the original Windsong, means 'Maat's Haven'."
msgstr ""
"He estado pensando en un nombre que no sea ni aragwaithi ni hannuk y que "
"agrade a ambos pueblos por igual: el nombre de una mujer que no tenía "
"patria, pero que fue aceptada, respetada y amada por todos y que siempre "
"estuvo dispuesta a ayudar a la gente sin importar su origen… Estaba pensando "
"en llamar a nuestra nueva ciudad Maat’Kare, que en una lengua hablada por "
"las Hijas del Viento originales significa «Refugio de Maat»."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:502
msgid ""
"(An approving murmur runs the ranks of the exhausted, but exhilarating "
"warriors)"
msgstr ""
"(Un murmullo de aprobación recorre las filas de los guerreros exhaustos pero "
"exultantes)"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:506
msgid "I really like it!"
msgstr "¡Me encanta!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:510
msgid ""
"A fine choice, daughter. Your mother would be proud of you: both of them!"
msgstr ""
"Una elección excelente, hija. Tu madre estaría orgullosa de ti: ¡las dos!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:514
msgid ""
"All hail Myra of Hiera'Shirsha, the heroine who has led us to a new home!"
msgstr ""
"¡Salve Myra de Hiera’Shirsha, la heroína que nos ha llevado a un nuevo hogar!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:518
msgid "HAIL! HAIL! HAIL! HAIL!"
msgstr "¡¡¡SALVE! ¡SALVE! ¡SALVE! ¡SALVE!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:573
msgid "To have crossed half of Irdya, only to die at our goal, o fate..."
msgstr ""
"Haber cruzado medio Irdya, solo para morir en nuestra meta, oh destino…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/26_The_Conquest_Of_The_Promised_Land.cfg:668
msgid ""
"We shouldn't have taken so much time to conquer this land, now there are "
"more vampire and minotaur bands coming, and we won't be able to fight them "
"all!"
msgstr ""
"No deberíamos haber tardado tanto en conquistar esta tierra, ¡ahora vienen "
"más bandas de vampiros y minotauros y no podremos luchar contra todos!"

#. [scenario], id=27_The_Rise_Of_MaatKare
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/27_The_Rise_Of_MaatKare.cfg:4
msgid "The Rise of Maat'Kare"
msgstr "El Ascenso de Maat'Kare"

#. [objectives]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/27_The_Rise_Of_MaatKare.cfg:47
msgid ""
"NOTE: In the next scenarios, you won't be able to recall your Hannuk, "
"Aragwaithi and Windsong veterans; in this scenario as well, the Windsong "
"veterans are not available. However, Myra's power growth allows her to "
"recruit level 2 elementals."
msgstr ""
"NOTA: En los próximos escenarios no podrás reincorporar a tus veteranos "
"hannuk, aragwaithi ni Hijas del Viento; en este escenario tampoco están "
"disponibles los veteranos Hijas del Viento. Sin embargo, el crecimiento de "
"poder de Myra le permite reclutar elementales de nivel 2."

#. [label]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/27_The_Rise_Of_MaatKare.cfg:59
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:16
msgid "The Academy"
msgstr "La Academia"

#. [label]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/27_The_Rise_Of_MaatKare.cfg:63
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:21
msgid "Veela's Garden"
msgstr "El Jardín de Veela"

#. [side], type=Child
#. [side]
#. [side], type=Orcish Warrior
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/27_The_Rise_Of_MaatKare.cfg:71
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/28_Embers_Of_War.cfg:58
