#. [side], type=Goblin Pillager
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:102
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:122
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:142
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:162
msgid "Goblins"
msgstr "Goblins"

#. [side], type=Goblin Knight
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:118
msgid "Hink"
msgstr "Hink"

#. [side], type=Goblin Knight
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:138
msgid "Pagor"
msgstr "Pagor"

#. [side], type=Goblin Pillager
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:158
msgid "Rolo"
msgstr "Rolo"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:188
msgid ""
"We have already managed to force ten chieftains to unite under our banner, "
"but these are the clans I want to bring to our side: the clans of the "
"Howling Hills."
msgstr ""
"Ya hemos conseguido que diez jefes se unan bajo nuestro estandarte, pero "
"estos son los clanes que quiero traer a nuestro lado: los clanes de las "
"Colinas Aulladoras."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:192
msgid ""
"I see, it would be good to have them as allies for a change, rather than "
"enemies..."
msgstr ""
"Ya veo, sería bueno tenerlos como aliados por una vez, en vez de como "
"enemigos…"

#. [message], speaker=Rark
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:196
msgid "I don't know them, are they really that strong?"
msgstr "No los conozco, ¿son realmente tan fuertes?"

#. [message], speaker=Hagdush
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:200
msgid ""
"How can you be an orc and not know their legend? I thought every orc child "
"heard stories of how Vishnak the Great tamed Fernir, the Red Wolf! Now, "
"guess why Fernir was called the Red Wolf? Because it was always covered in "
"the blood of its victims! But Vishnak overwhelmed it with his great "
"strength, and turned it into his mount! It was then that his clan started "
"taming wolves and training them as mounts!"
msgstr ""
"¿Cómo puedes ser un orco y no conocer su leyenda? ¡Pensaba que todos los "
"niños orcos oían historias de cómo Vishnak el Grande domó a Fernir, el Lobo "
"Rojo! ¡Ahora, adivina por qué Fernir era llamado el Lobo Rojo! ¡Porque "
"siempre estaba cubierto de la sangre de sus víctimas! ¡Pero Vishnak lo "
"dominó con su gran fuerza y lo convirtió en su montura! ¡Fue entonces cuando "
"su clan empezó a domar lobos y entrenarlos como monturas!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:204
msgid ""
"Weird, the version I know tells that Vishnak took care of Fernir when it was "
"a puppy, and that the animal later saved him from being killed by orcs; thus "
"they became friends, and together vanquished the warlord that enslaved his "
"people."
msgstr ""
"Raro, la versión que yo conozco cuenta que Vishnak cuidó de Fernir cuando "
"era un cachorro y que el animal después lo salvó de ser asesinado por orcos; "
"así se hicieron amigos y juntos vencieron al señor de la guerra que "
"esclavizaba a su pueblo."

#. [message], speaker=Hagdush
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:208
msgid ""
"No offence, ma'am, but Vishnak was a mighty orc, so huge he could shatter a "
"carapace's shell and tear apart minotaur behemoths with his bare hands! How "
"could he be bullied by others, even if by orcs?"
msgstr ""
"Sin ofender, señora, pero Vishnak era un orco poderoso, ¡tan enorme que "
"podía romper el caparazón de un carapacho y despedazar behemots minotauros "
"con sus propias manos! ¿Cómo podrían intimidarlo otros orc… incluso si eran "
"orcos?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:212
msgid "Because, you see, Vishnak's people and clan..."
msgstr "Porque, verás, el pueblo y el clan de Vishnak…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:245
msgid "...are actually goblins."
msgstr "…en realidad son goblins."

#. [message], speaker=Hagdush
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:249
msgid "What?! No, it... it can't be... If this is a joke, it's not funny!"
msgstr "¡¿Qué?! ¡No, no puede ser…! ¡Si esto es una broma, no tiene gracia!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:253
msgid "Why such reaction? I thought orcs and goblins were allies."
msgstr "¿Por qué tanta reacción? Pensaba que orcos y goblins eran aliados."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:257
msgid ""
"(amused) Well, not quite. Goblins are seen as an inferior breed of orcs, "
"smaller and weaker and, for this reason, despised and often exploited. "
"Vishnak was the first goblin who successfully broke free from an orc "
"master's domination; and, by showing how his fighting style was useful, he "
"gave all goblins a way of earning the respect of the orcs."
msgstr ""
"(divertida) Bueno, no exactamente. Los goblins son vistos como una raza "
"inferior de orcos, más pequeños y débiles y, por esa razón, despreciados y a "
"menudo explotados. Vishnak fue el primer goblin que logró liberarse con "
"éxito de la dominación de un maestro orco; y, al mostrar lo útil que era su "
"estilo de lucha, dio a todos los goblins una forma de ganarse el respeto de "
"los orcos."

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:262
msgid "Who comes there? Stop right where you are, or our wolves will..."
msgstr "¿Quién viene ahí? ¡Paraos donde estáis o nuestros lobos…!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:266
msgid "Oh, hi there! Long time no see, Ronak!"
msgstr "¡Oh, hola! ¡Cuánto tiempo sin verte, Ronak!"

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:271
msgid ""
"It's... it's... (gets paler) WHY HAVE YOU COME BACK, YOU CRUEL WITCH? WHY DO "
"YOU KEEP PLAGUING US? "
msgstr ""
"Es... es... (se pone más pálido) ¡¿POR QUÉ HAS VUELTO, BRUJA CRUEL?! ¡¿POR "
"QUÉ SIGUES AFLIGIÉNDONOS?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:275
msgid "Geez, Ronak, are you still mad at me for that... little accident?"
msgstr ""
"Vaya, Ronak, ¿todavía estás enfadado conmigo por aquel… pequeño accidente?"

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:280
msgid ""
"How can I not be, when every time I ride my dear she-wolf I am reminded of "
"that?!"
msgstr ""
"¡¿Cómo no voy a estarlo, cuando cada vez que monto a mi querida loba me lo "
"recuerda?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:284
msgid ""
"Come on, Ronak, you asked for that! I know I trespassed your frontiers once, "
"but you know I had then recently arrived at this continent! You could have "
"been reasonable, but nooo, you had to unleash your wolves on me and Jevyan, "
"and you had to do it every damn time you spotted us... And even you must "
"agree that your last assault on us was the last straw!"
msgstr ""
"¡Vamos, Ronak, tú te lo buscaste! ¡Sé que crucé vuestras fronteras una vez, "
"pero sabes que acababa de llegar a este continente! ¡Podrías haber sido "
"razonable, pero nooo, tenías que soltar a tus lobos contra mí y Jevyan, y "
"tenías que hacerlo cada maldita vez que nos veías…! ¡Y hasta tú tienes que "
"admitir que tu último asalto contra nosotros fue la gota que colmó el vaso!"

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:289
msgid ""
"(sobbing) Riding my she-wolf was delightful in the past, but now it is "
"almost a torture..."
msgstr ""
"(sollozando) Montar a mi loba era delicioso en el pasado, pero ahora es casi "
"una tortura…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:293
msgid ""
"Listen, Ronak, will you see me with better eyes if I tell you I killed your "
"hated Hagash?"
msgstr ""
"Escucha, Ronak, ¿me verás con mejores ojos si te digo que maté a tu odiado "
"Hagash?"

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:298
msgid ""
"You did...? Well, that makes little difference: I hated him just a little "
"bit more than I hate you."
msgstr ""
"¿Lo hiciste…? Bueno, eso cambia poco: lo odiaba solo un poquito más de lo "
"que te odio a ti."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:302
msgid ""
"Aaand what if I tell you I came here to warn you that his son is preparing "
"to launch a new offensive on the north-western orcish tribes?"
msgstr ""
"Yyyy ¿qué tal si te digo que he venido aquí para avisarte de que su hijo se "
"está preparando para lanzar una nueva ofensiva contra las tribus orcas del "
"noroeste?"

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:307
msgid "Is he...?"
msgstr "¿Lo está…?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:311
msgid ""
"Exactly. Eranak, the new boss at Uldrol now that Ogesh is dead, is planning "
"a counter-offensive, but unfortunately most of his allies deserted him, and "
"that includes you."
msgstr ""
"Exacto. Eranak, el nuevo jefe en Uldrol ahora que Ogesh está muerto, está "
"planeando una contraofensiva, pero desgraciadamente la mayoría de sus "
"aliados lo han abandonado, y eso te incluye a ti."

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:316
msgid ""
"Hrumph! You should know the orc ways better; I respected and pledged my "
"loyalty to Ogesh, not to his clan. If his successor proved himself a worthy "
"warrior, I might aid him, but I see he has sent you, who isn't even of his "
"own people, to do his job. And I'd have expected more from you, witch, "
"lowering yourself by being his errand girl."
msgstr ""
"¡Hrumph! Deberías conocer mejor las costumbres orcas; yo respetaba y juré "
"lealtad a Ogesh, no a su clan. Si su sucesor se hubiera demostrado un "
"guerrero digno, quizá lo ayudaría, pero veo que ha enviado a ti, que ni "
"siquiera eres de su gente, para hacer su trabajo. Y esperaba más de ti, "
"bruja, rebajándote a ser su recadera."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:320
msgid ""
"(menacingly) Mind your words, goblin. Do you want me to fry your bottom "
"again?"
msgstr ""
"(amenazante) Cuida tus palabras, goblin. ¿Quieres que te queme el trasero "
"otra vez?"

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:325
msgid ""
"Bah! You think I will accept your condescendence just because I'm a goblin? "
"Defeat me and my cousins in battle, and we will do whatever you tell us to "
"do. But know that we've had an awful lot of new recruits since our last "
"meeting!"
msgstr ""
"¡Bah! ¿Crees que aceptaré tu condescendencia solo porque soy goblin? "
"¡Derrotadme a mí y a mis primos en batalla y haremos lo que nos digáis! "
"¡Pero sabed que hemos tenido un montón de nuevos reclutas desde nuestro "
"último encuentro!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:329
msgid ""
"Then you will see an awful lot of wolves moaning across these hills. Grunts, "
"I want these goblin insects crushed before sunset! But let me deal with "
"Ronak myself; he's the main leader of the wolf riders, if we kill him the "
"goblins will be so weakened that there'll be no point in asking for their "
"aid anymore!"
msgstr ""
"Entonces veréis un montón de lobos gimiendo por estas colinas. ¡Grunts, "
"quiero a estos insectos goblin aplastados antes del atardecer! ¡Pero dejadme "
"a Ronak para mí; es el líder principal de los jinetes de lobo, si lo matamos "
"los goblins quedarán tan debilitados que ya no tendrá sentido pedir su ayuda!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:345
msgid ""
"No! I told you not to kill him! Eranak has just lost an invaluable ally!"
msgstr ""
"¡No! ¡Os dije que no lo matarais! ¡Eranak acaba de perder un aliado "
"inestimable!"

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:363
msgid "Argh, I hate you..."
msgstr "Argh, te odio…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:367
msgid ""
"I know you do, but now, you must keep your promise, as the worthy descendant "
"of Vishnak the Great that you are."
msgstr ""
"Lo sé, pero ahora debes cumplir tu promesa, como el digno descendiente del "
"gran Vishnak que eres."

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:372
msgid "I suppose you want me to fight for that stupid Eranak?"
msgstr "Supongo que quieres que luche por ese estúpido Eranak."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:376
msgid ""
"Yes; you shall follow his orders as if they came from the mouth of Ogesh "
"himself. Also, I want you to address him as 'chieftain', or 'boss', do you "
"understand?"
msgstr ""
"Sí; seguirás sus órdenes como si salieran de la boca del propio Ogesh. "
"Además, quiero que lo llames «jefe» o «amo», ¿entendido?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:385
msgid ""
"I will take that as a 'yes'. Now, I want you to prepare a feast for us, this "
"battle's made me hungry like I haven't been since my pregnancy!"
msgstr ""
"Lo tomaré como un «sí». Ahora quiero que prepares un banquete para nosotros, "
"¡esta batalla me ha dado un hambre que no tenía desde mi embarazo!"

#. [message], speaker=Ronak
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:390
msgid ""
"(grumbling) She comes to my land, kills my wolves, harms my cousins and "
"ravages my kitchen... And they call <i>us</i> barbarians..."
msgstr ""
"(refunfuñando) Viene a mi tierra, mata a mis lobos, hiere a mis primos y "
"saquea mi cocina… ¡Y nos llaman <i>a nosotros</i> bárbaros…!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/29_Forging_Allies.cfg:446
msgid ""
"We are taking too much time defeating the goblins! If we continue at this "
"pace, we'll never gather enough allies in time to face Hagor!"
msgstr ""
"¡Estamos tardando demasiado en derrotar a los goblins! ¡Si seguimos a este "
"ritmo, nunca reuniremos suficientes aliados a tiempo para enfrentar a Hagor!"

#. [scenario], id=30_Old_Friends
#. [scenario], id=30_Old_Friends_b
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:4
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:4
msgid "Old Friends"
msgstr "Viejos amigos"

#. [side], type=Dwarvish Lord
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:27
msgid "Dulcatas"
msgstr "Dulcatas"

#. [unit], id=Gomatol, type=Dwarvish Stalwart
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:39
msgid "Gomatol"
msgstr "Gomatol"

#. [unit], id=Nardras, type=Dwarvish Stalwart
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:47
msgid "Nardras"
msgstr "Nardras"

#. [side], type=Orcish Warlord
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:55
msgid "Prudish"
msgstr "Pudorosa"

#. [side], type=Garou
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:66
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:106
msgid "Mani"
msgstr "Mani"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:125
msgid ""
"Alenya, Dvalin, Akashia, it's so good to see you all together again! "
"Especially you, Akashia! Hiera'Laksha won't crumble to dust if you stop "
"working for just a few days while you visit your old friends! We've so much "
"catching up to do..."
msgstr ""
"¡Alenya, Dvalin, Akashia, qué alegría veros a todos juntos otra vez! ¡Sobre "
"todo a ti, Akashia! ¡Hiera'Laksha no se vendrá abajo si dejas de trabajar "
"unos pocos días para visitar a tus viejas amigas! ¡Tenemos tanto de que "
"ponernos al día..."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:129
msgid ""
"I doubt that. The last three times we saw each other, it was all 'Maat'Kare "
"this' and 'Aldrik that' and 'more babies being born' and 'isn't our city "
"growing just <i>wonderfully</i>'..."
msgstr ""
"Lo dudo. Las últimas tres veces que nos vimos fue todo «Maat'Kare esto» y "
"«Aldrik lo otro» y «más bebés naciendo» y «¿no está creciendo nuestra ciudad "
"<i>maravillosamente</i>»..."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:133
msgid ""
"Come on, Maat'Kare isn't boring, there's always something new to show you!"
msgstr ""
"¡Venga ya, Maat'Kare no es aburrida, siempre hay algo nuevo que enseñarte!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:137
msgid ""
"You're right. Now that you're hugging me, I can feel you've grown fatter."
msgstr "Tienes razón. Ahora que me estás abrazando noto que has engordado."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:141
msgid "You know what? It's you who's always the same difficult little brat!"
msgstr "¿Sabes qué? ¡Eres tú la que siempre es la misma mocosa insoportable!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:145
msgid ""
"Don't be mad for her saying the truth, you do look rounder - or maybe it's "
"just Aldrik's little brother on the way?"
msgstr ""
"No te enfades porque dice la verdad, sí que pareces más rellenita… ¿o será "
"que ya viene en camino el hermanito de Aldrik?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:149
msgid "You're one to talk... Have you been having much dwarvish stuff lately?"
msgstr ""
"Tú sí que hablas… ¿has estado comiendo mucho “producto enano” últimamente?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:153
msgid "(blushes violently) ...!!!"
msgstr "(se pone roja como un tomate) …!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:157
msgid ""
"(blushes even more violently) Och, girl, stop talking nonsense! 'Having "
"much'... Nonsense..."
msgstr ""
"(se pone aún más rojo) ¡Por los dioses, muchacha, deja de decir tonterías! "
"«Comer mucho»… ¡Tonterías…!"

#. [message], speaker=Nardras
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:161
msgid "(shakes head disapprovingly)"
msgstr "(niega con la cabeza, desaprobando)"

#. [message], speaker=Dulcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:165
msgid ""
"Ahem! If you friends have sated your longing for each other, I'd like to "
"begin our meeting."
msgstr ""
"¡Ejem! Si ya habéis terminado de saciar las ganas de veros, me gustaría "
"empezar la reunión."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:169
msgid "Certainly, Lord Dulcatas. (pulls Myra away)"
msgstr "Claro, señor Dulcatas. (tira de Myra para apartarla)"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:180
msgid ""
"(whispers) I really don't get it, why were they so scandalized when I called "
"her chubby for eating dwarvish food?"
msgstr ""
"(susurra) De verdad que no lo entiendo, ¿por qué se escandalizaron tanto "
"cuando dije que estaba gordita por comer tanto producto enano?"

#. [message], speaker=Dulcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:184
msgid ""
"I have summoned you to this meeting to discuss the recent events regarding "
"the vampires and Hagash's clan. Myra, you are the one who first raised "
"awareness to this fact; would you like to speak first?"
msgstr ""
"Os he convocado a esta reunión para tratar los recientes acontecimientos "
"relacionados con los vampiros y el clan de Hagash. Myra, tú fuiste la "
"primera en alertarnos; ¿quieres hablar primero?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:188
msgid ""
"I was initially summoned to Uldrol to help chieftain Ogesh fend off a joint "
"orcish and vampire attack; when I arrived there, he was dead, and his city "
"was on the verge of being destroyed by Hagash and his new allies. I helped "
"Eranak, Ogesh's right-hand warrior, to defeat them both, and he told me he "
"had seen a message coming from Hagash the day before, in which he boasted "
"his new alliance with Vrykos."
msgstr ""
"Me llamaron a Uldrol para ayudar al jefe Ogesh a rechazar un ataque conjunto "
"de orcos y vampiros; cuando llegué, él ya estaba muerto y su ciudad estaba a "
"punto de ser destruida por Hagash y sus nuevos aliados. Ayudé a Eranak, la "
"mano derecha de Ogesh, a derrotarlos a ambos, y me contó que había visto un "
"mensaje de Hagash del día anterior en el que presumía de su nueva alianza "
"con Vrykos."

#. [message], speaker=Mani
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:192
msgid ""
"The 'high and mighty' Vrykos, siding with orcs? Most likely your dumb orcish "
"friend misunderstood that message, Myra, if that message ever existed at "
"all..."
msgstr ""
"¿El «alto y poderoso» Vrykos aliándose con orcos? Lo más probable es que tu "
"amigo orco tonto malinterpretara ese mensaje, Myra, si es que el mensaje "
"existió alguna vez…"

#. [message], speaker=Prudish
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:196
msgid "You watch out how you talk of chief Eranak, you stinking furry!"
msgstr "¡Cuida cómo hablas del jefe Eranak, bola de pelo apestosa!"

#. [message], speaker=Dulcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:200
msgid ""
"And <i>you</i> watch out how you talk in the hall of my ancestors, both of "
"you!"
msgstr ""
"¡Y <i>tú</i> cuida cómo hablas en el salón de mis antepasados, ¡los dos!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:204
msgid "Friends, we came here to talk, not to fight..."
msgstr "Amigos, hemos venido a hablar, no a pelearnos…"

#. [message], speaker=Mani
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:208
msgid ""
"Fine, I apologise... In any case, if Hagash is dead, then we should not fear "
"his orcs anymore, am I right?"
msgstr ""
"Está bien, me disculpo… En cualquier caso, si Hagash está muerto, ya no "
"tenemos que temer a sus orcos, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:212
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, no. Hagash has been succeeded by his son Hagor, who has "
"already reasserted his clan's control over its vassals."
msgstr ""
"Por desgracia, no. Hagash tiene un hijo, Hagor, que ya ha vuelto a imponer "
"el control de su clan sobre sus vasallos."

#. [message], speaker=Dulcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:216
msgid ""
"Furthermore, my gryphon riders have scouted the south-western orcish lands, "
"and reported a major stirring there, with large armies of both seasoned and "
"newly-recruited warriors moving towards Borgath, Hagash's capital. What "
"about you, Lady Akashia? You said in your message that your girls would "
"scout the northern mountains; did they see anything unusual?"
msgstr ""
"Además, mis jinetes de grifo han explorado las tierras orcas del suroeste y "
"han informado de un gran movimiento: ejércitos numerosos de guerreros "
"veteranos y recién reclutados avanzan hacia Borgath, la capital de Hagash. "
"¿Y tú, señora Akashia? Dijiste en tu mensaje que tus chicas explorarían las "
"montañas del norte; ¿vieron algo fuera de lo normal?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:220
msgid ""
"Affirmative. In their reports, they claimed that they've noticed an unusual "
"movement between vampire fortresses; some hurried vampires, leading small "
"bands, have already attacked our Foundation, even Maat'Kare. That is normal, "
"for their standards: vampires have little control of themselves when they're "
"obsessed with something."
msgstr ""
"Afirmativo. En sus informes decían que habían notado un movimiento extraño "
"entre las fortalezas vampíricas; algunos vampiros apresurados, al mando de "
"pequeños grupos, ya han atacado nuestra Fundación e incluso Maat'Kare. Eso "
"es normal en ellos: los vampiros pierden el control cuando están "
"obsesionados con algo."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:224
msgid "And what would this 'something' be?"
msgstr "¿Y ese «algo» qué sería?"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:228
msgid ""
"All-out war against all other nations that have stood on the way of their "
"bid for continental power."
msgstr ""
"Una guerra total contra todas las naciones que se han interpuesto en su "
"camino hacia el dominio continental."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:232
msgid ""
"Och, that does make sense: alone they'd've never be much of a threat for our "
"alliance, but united..."
msgstr ""
"Vaya, eso tiene sentido: solos nunca habrían sido gran amenaza para nuestra "
"alianza, pero unidos…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:236
msgid ""
"Now, I have a question: why don't I see winged people here with us? Haven't "
"you invited them as well, King Dulcatas?"
msgstr ""
"Ahora yo tengo una pregunta: ¿por qué no veo aquí gente alada? ¿No los "
"invitaste también, rey Dulcatas?"

#. [message], speaker=Dulcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:240
msgid ""
"If you mean the Celestials, yes, I have, but they clearly chose not to "
"come..."
msgstr ""
"Si te refieres a los Celestiales, sí, los invité, pero claramente decidieron "
"no venir…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:244
msgid ""
"Arrogant bastards, they know that if we defend our own frontiers theirs will "
"be protected as well... I think we should all pay them a visit when we "
"finish Vrykos and Hagor, you know, just to show them how friendly we are..."
msgstr ""
"¡Malditos arrogantes! Saben que si defendemos nuestras fronteras las suyas "
"también quedarán protegidas… Creo que deberíamos hacerles una visita cuando "
"acabemos con Vrykos y Hagor, ya sabes, para demostrarles lo amigos que somos…"

#. [message], speaker=Dulcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:248
msgid ""
"That comment aside, we must coordinate our next moves well: we and the "
"Aigathol dwarves may hold back any orcish offensive on the mountains; we "
"also have great control over the Sun Path..."
msgstr ""
"Dejando ese comentario de lado, debemos coordinar bien nuestros próximos "
"pasos: los enanos Aigathol y nosotros podemos contener cualquier ofensiva "
"orca en las montañas; además tenemos buen control del Camino del Sol…"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:252
msgid ""
"Please, leave the Sun Path for us, and attack the vampire mountain "
"fortresses; dwarves will fare better than us on that terrain. Our forces "
"will cross the Path westwards, push back any orcish offensive there, and "
"will join the allied orcs and the dwarves in the western front."
msgstr ""
"Por favor, dejadnos a nosotros el Camino del Sol y atacad las fortalezas "
"vampíricas de las montañas; los enanos se desenvuelven mejor que nosotros en "
"ese terreno. Nuestras fuerzas cruzarán el Camino hacia el oeste, rechazarán "
"cualquier ofensiva orca allí y se unirán a los orcos aliados y a los enanos "
"en el frente occidental."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:256
msgid ""
"The dwarves will have problems fighting the vampires alone, so I will fight "
"there as well."
msgstr ""
"Los enanos tendrán problemas para luchar solos contra los vampiros, así que "
"yo también lucharé allí."

#. [message], speaker=Mani
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:260
msgid ""
"As for the wargs, we'll send two armies: one will follow the Maat'Karians "
"west, and the other shall accompany the dwarves north! We have many scores "
"to settle with those blood-suckers..."
msgstr ""
"En cuanto a los huargos, enviaremos dos ejércitos: uno seguirá a los "
"maat’karianos hacia el oeste, y el otro acompañará a los enanos al norte. "
"¡Tenemos muchas cuentas pendientes con esos chupasangres…!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:264
msgid "What about you, Akashia?"
msgstr "¿Y tú, Akashia?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:268
msgid ""
"(sigh) Do not misunderstand me; I may bear the title of Warmonger, but I "
"uphold our order's pacifist policies. The Windsong will remain in "
"Hiera'Laksha, faithfully watching over Maat'Kare, but avoiding faraway "
"conflicts."
msgstr ""
"(suspira) No me malinterpretéis; puede que lleve el título de Belicosa, pero "
"mantenemos las políticas pacifistas de nuestra orden. Las Hijas del Viento "
"permanecerán en Hiera'Laksha, vigilando fielmente Maat'Kare, pero evitando "
"conflictos lejanos."

#. [message], speaker=Dulcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:272
msgid ""
"(astonished) But... After all the tales of your bravery and strength  I "
"heard from Dvalin, I expected you to be the first to unsheathe your blade! "
"Will you simply cross your arms and avoid fighting? "
msgstr ""
"(asombrado) ¡Pero…! Después de todas las historias de tu valor y fuerza que "
"me contó Dvalin, ¡esperaba que fueras la primera en desenvainar! ¿De verdad "
"vas a quedarte de brazos cruzados y no luchar?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:276
msgid ""
"Dvalin said no lie, but yes, I will not send the Windsong to fight anywhere "
"else than either Hiera'Laksha or Maat'Kare."
msgstr ""
"Dvalin no mintió, pero sí, no enviaré a las Hijas del Viento a luchar a "
"ningún otro sitio que no sea Hiera'Laksha o Maat'Kare."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:280
msgid ""
"Friends, even by simply standing watch, the Order will play an invaluable "
"role: when Maat'Kare's troops leave for the west, the city's best defence "
"will be Hiera'Laksha! With the knowledge that the Windsong are protecting "
"their families, our soldiers will fight much better; after all, we are still "
"the weakest and most vulnerable member of this alliance!"
msgstr ""
"Amigos, aunque solo permanezcan vigilando, la Orden jugará un papel "
"inestimable: cuando las tropas de Maat’Kare partan al oeste, la mejor "
"defensa de la ciudad será Hiera’Laksha. ¡Sabiendo que las Hijas del Viento "
"protegen a sus familias, nuestros soldados lucharán mucho mejor! Al fin y al "
"cabo, seguimos siendo el miembro más débil y vulnerable de esta alianza."

#. [message], speaker=Dulcatas
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends.cfg:284
msgid ""
"Well, your arguments are sound... So we have defined our targets, but I "
"still want to discuss our strategy in deeper detail..."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, tus argumentos son sólidos… Ya hemos definido nuestros objetivos, "
"pero aún quiero discutir la estrategia con más detalle…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:48
msgid "It wasn't necessary to justify me back there, but thanks anyway."
msgstr ""
"No hacía falta que me defendieras allí atrás, pero gracias de todos modos."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:52
msgid ""
"Hey, Akashia, why such coldness? We haven't seen each other in years "
"already, and this is how you treat me?"
msgstr ""
"Oye, Akashia, ¿por qué tan fría? Ya hace años que no nos vemos, ¿y así me "
"tratas?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:56
msgid ""
"Don't get me wrong, Myra, I'm just... (sigh) Being Head of the Windsong does "
"take a toll on you. Yes, I know, you were our Head too, but I'm not an "
"Ascendant, not even a Herald; leave me on a battlefield and I'll know "
"exactly how to lead our sisters, but being the Order's Head... Even if I had "
"that famous Weaver foresight, this isn't where I'd ever have seen me."
msgstr ""
"No me malinterpretes, Myra, solo estoy… (suspira) Ser la Cabeza de las Hijas "
"del Viento pasa factura. Sí, lo sé, tú también fuiste nuestra Cabeza, pero "
"yo no soy Ascendente, ni siquiera Heraldo; déjame en un campo de batalla y "
"sabré exactamente cómo liderar a nuestras hermanas, pero ser la Cabeza de la "
"Orden… Aunque tuviera esa famosa previsión de Tejedoras, este no es el lugar "
"donde me habría imaginado."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:60
msgid ""
"You worry, yet every Windsong I've met these last years has had nothing but "
"enthusiastic words to describe you. And don't let your lack of Weaver powers "
"get to you; in case you've forgotten, I myself have little connection to the "
"Raw, as my powers are nature-based. I know I placed a burden you never asked "
"for-"
msgstr ""
"Te preocupas, pero todas las Hijas del Viento que he conocido estos últimos "
"años solo tienen palabras entusiastas para describirte. Y no dejes que la "
"falta de poderes de Tejedora te afecte; por si lo has olvidado, yo misma "
"tengo poca conexión con el Raw, porque mis poderes son de la naturaleza. Sé "
"que te puse una carga que nunca pediste-"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:64
msgid ""
"If you want to make me feel better, Myra, patronising isn't the way. I "
"willingly accepted being the Windsong's Head; if I sounded like I was "
"regretting that, then it was my mistake."
msgstr ""
"Si quieres hacerme sentir mejor, Myra, no me trates con condescendencia. "
"Acepté voluntariamente ser la Cabeza de las Hijas del Viento; si sonó como "
"si me arrepintiera, fue error mío."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:68
msgid ""
"Then from one leader of the Windsong to another, do take some time to visit "
"us, if only to grace Maat'Kare with an official visit. I'd go visit you "
"myself, but-"
msgstr ""
"Entonces, de una líder de las Hijas del Viento a otra, ven a visitarnos "
"alguna vez, aunque solo sea para honrar Maat’Kare con una visita oficial. Yo "
"misma iría a verte, pero-"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:72
msgid ""
"-The last time you did, our sisters kept interrupting us, I know. Fine, I'll "
"see what I can do."
msgstr ""
"-La última vez que lo hiciste, nuestras hermanas no paraban de "
"interrumpirnos, lo sé. De acuerdo, veré qué puedo hacer."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:76
msgid "I'll hold you to that..."
msgstr "Te tomaré la palabra…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:83
msgid ""
"Listen, Akashia, there is something else I want to ask you, something more "
"serious, I'm afraid... It regards the Sky Soul."
msgstr ""
"Escucha, Akashia, hay otra cosa que quiero pedirte, algo más serio, me temo… "
"Tiene que ver con el Alma del Cielo."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:87
msgid "Say it."
msgstr "Dilo."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:91
msgid ""
"I have been having some worrying dreams lately, dreams where this gem is "
"taken from me and used to revive Svarballi."
msgstr ""
"He estado teniendo sueños preocupantes últimamente, sueños en los que me "
"quitan esta gema y la usan para revivir a Svarballi."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:95
msgid ""
"A foresight, I see... Well, I don't see how the gem could possibly be taken "
"from you, unless you wanted to hand it over."
msgstr ""
"Una premonición, ya veo… Bueno, no veo cómo podrían quitarte la gema a menos "
"que tú quisieras entregarla."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:99
msgid ""
"Indeed, most beings would never manage to take it from me by force, but we "
"both know there are some beings on this continent who wield powers as "
"strange as they are vast, right?"
msgstr ""
"En efecto, la mayoría de seres nunca lograrían quitármela por la fuerza, "
"pero ambas sabemos que hay algunos seres en este continente que manejan "
"poderes tan extraños como vastos, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:103
msgid ""
"The Celestials, of course... They seem capable of reviving Svarballi; I "
"still haven't forgotten how they praised him."
msgstr ""
"Los Celestiales, por supuesto… Parecen capaces de revivir a Svarballi; aún "
"no he olvidado cómo lo alababan."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:107
msgid ""
"My worries have a more specific cause: the Seraphin Lord Grigorius. Do you "
"remember how he was capable of knowing about the Last War without even "
"leaving Netjer-Ta? I doubt even my mother had a clairvoyance that powerful; "
"as far as we know, he could be spying on me whenever I'm on the surface... "
"Not the most pleasant of thoughts, but there it is."
msgstr ""
"Mis preocupaciones tienen una causa más concreta: el Señor Serafín "
"Grigorius. ¿Recuerdas cómo fue capaz de saber de la Última Guerra sin "
"siquiera salir de Netjer-Ta? Dudo que ni siquiera mi madre tuviera una "
"clarividencia tan poderosa; por lo que sabemos, podría estar espiándome cada "
"vez que estoy en la superficie… No es el pensamiento más agradable, pero ahí "
"está."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:111
msgid "How do you know he can't see you right now?"
msgstr "¿Cómo sabes que no te está viendo ahora mismo?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:115
msgid ""
"Deep caves, such as this one, are out of a clairvoyant's line of sight. Now, "
"I fear Grigorius, or maybe all the four Lords, are plotting to take the Sky "
"Soul, and will use this new war to try and steal it, taking advantage of "
"everyone's distraction."
msgstr ""
"Cuevas profundas como esta están fuera de la línea de visión de un "
"clarividente. Ahora, temo que Grigorius, o quizá los cuatro Señores, estén "
"tramando apoderarse del Alma del Cielo y usarán esta nueva guerra para "
"intentar robármela, aprovechando la distracción de todos."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:119
msgid ""
"I get your point; I've never trusted those Celestials at all, and I have "
"never forgotten about what that rebel, Zaal, said either. I could wage the "
"Book of the Dead that he uncovered some ugly truth about Grigorius, or maybe "
"all the Lords. A shame we didn't help him then..."
msgstr ""
"Entiendo tu punto; nunca he confiado en absoluto en esos celestiales, y "
"tampoco he olvidado lo que dijo ese heraldo rebelde, Zaal. Apostaría el "
"Libro de los Muertos a que descubrió alguna verdad fea sobre Grigorius, o "
"quizá sobre todos los Señores. Lástima que no le ayudáramos entonces…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:123
msgid ""
"You know my reasons for not doing that very well, Akashia. But this is not "
"important; I have told you all these things because I want to ask you to "
"keep the Sky Soul with you at Hiera'Laksha until this war is over."
msgstr ""
"Conoces muy bien mis razones para no haberlo hecho, Akashia. Pero eso no "
"importa; te he contado todo esto porque quiero pedirte que guardes el Alma "
"del Cielo contigo en Hiera’Laksha hasta que acabe esta guerra."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:127
msgid "Keep the Soul? But..."
msgstr "¿Guardar el Alma? Pero…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:131
msgid ""
"Don't worry, I will wrap it in a spell that will hold back its aura. I would "
"never ask you this, friend, but I confess those dreams have scared me. I "
"still have nightmares about the Last War and the Ughure Incident, and I "
"won't risk seeing that horror be repeated on this continent. Besides, I "
"doubt the Seraphins would ever guess that I left the gem with you; either "
"they'd think I'd never relinquish its ownership out of greediness, or that "
"I'd never trust it to someone less powerful than myself. Besides, with the "
"cloaking ciphers I've cast around the jewel, even Grigorius won't be able to "
"sense it."
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes, la envolveré en un hechizo que contendrá su aura. Nunca te "
"pediría esto, amiga, pero confieso que esos sueños me han asustado. Todavía "
"tengo pesadillas con la Última Guerra y el Incidente de Ughure, y no voy a "
"arriesgarme a ver repetido ese horror en este continente. Además, dudo que "
"los Serafines adivinen que dejé la gema contigo; o pensarían que nunca "
"renunciaría a su posesión por avaricia, o que nunca la confiaría a alguien "
"menos poderoso que yo. Además, con los cifrados de ocultación que he lanzado "
"alrededor de la joya, ni siquiera Grigorius podrá sentirla."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:135
msgid "But if even you can't protect it, how can I..."
msgstr "Pero si ni siquiera tú puedes protegerla, ¿cómo puedo yo…?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:139
msgid ""
"I am strong, but I'm not invulnerable to, say, vampire blades, arrows and "
"fangs; in Hiera'Laksha, however, it will be protected by a dwarf-designed "
"mountain fortress and ranks of seasoned Windsong led by you! I won't simply "
"forget about our Foundation either: if I sense any great danger threatening "
"it, I will go to your aid myself."
msgstr ""
"Soy fuerte, pero no soy invulnerable, digamos, a cuchillas de vampiro, "
"flechas y colmillos; en Hiera’Laksha, sin embargo, estará protegida por una "
"fortaleza montañosa diseñada por enanos y filas de experimentadas Hijas del "
"Viento lideradas por ti. Tampoco me olvidaré simplemente de nuestra "
"Fundación: si siento algún gran peligro amenazándola, iré en tu ayuda yo "
"misma."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:143
msgid "Well, I can't see why I couldn't do as you ask me..."
msgstr "Bueno, no veo por qué no podría hacer lo que me pides…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:147
msgid "(hugs Akashia) Thank you, my friend, thank you so much..."
msgstr "(abraza a Akashia) Gracias, amiga mía, muchísimas gracias…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:164
msgid ""
"Myra, have I really seen well what you have just done? I know Akashia is our "
"friend, but..."
msgstr ""
"Myra, ¿he visto bien lo que acabas de hacer? Sé que Akashia es nuestra "
"amiga, pero…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:168
msgid "But, what? Jevyan, you can't be possibly insinuating Akashia will..."
msgstr "¿Pero qué? Jevyan, no estarás insinuando que Akashia va a…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:172
msgid ""
"I'm not insinuating anything, I just... I just think the gem would be better "
"protected in your hands. And Akashia... Well, I'm sure even you noticed how "
"strange she is."
msgstr ""
"No estoy insinuando nada, solo… solo pienso que la gema estaría mejor "
"protegida en tus manos. Y Akashia… Bueno, estoy seguro de que hasta tú "
"notaste lo rara que está."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:176
msgid ""
"She's just like myself in my first years as the new Head of the Windsong, "
"and I don't recall doing anything foolish back the- Right, I know there was "
"that incident at Ughure, but in the end it proved to be the right thing, for "
"it saved us. Besides, Akashia must be feeling abandoned by us; we haven't "
"met her in a long time already."
msgstr ""
"Está igual que yo en mis primeros años como nueva Cabeza de las Hijas del "
"Viento, y no recuerdo haber hecho ninguna tontería entonces… Bueno, sí, sé "
"que estuvo el incidente en Ughure, pero al final resultó ser lo correcto, "
"porque nos salvó. Además, Akashia debe sentirse abandonada por nosotros; "
"hace mucho que no la vemos."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/30_Old_Friends_b.cfg:180
msgid "(sigh) If you say so..."
msgstr "(suspira) Si tú lo dices…"

#. [scenario], id=31_Night_Fire
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:4
msgid "Night Fire"
msgstr "Fuego Nocturno"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:22
msgid "Defeat Lord Vrykos"
msgstr "Derrotar a lord Vrykos"

#. [objectives]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:44
msgid ""
"NOTE: Dvalin may recall the dwarves that fought in scenario 26. Furthermore, "
"the gold he retains at the end of this scenario shall be useful in the next."
msgstr ""
"NOTA: Dvalin puede reincorporar a los enanos que lucharon en el escenario "
"26. Además, el oro que conserve al final de este escenario será útil en el "
"siguiente."

#. [side], type=Methusalem
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:68
msgid "Vrykos"
msgstr "Vrykos"

#. [message], speaker=Mani
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:165
msgid ""
"How much I have longed to lay my eyes on this cursed city and hear the "
"howling of the wargs echo over this valley... YOU HEAR THAT, VRYKOS? YOU "
"HEAR THE SOUND OF YOUR DOOM?"
msgstr ""
"¡Cuánto he deseado posar mis ojos en esta ciudad maldita y oír el aullido de "
"los huargos resonar por este valle…! ¡¿LO OYES, VRYKOS? ¡¿OYES EL SONIDO DE "
"TU PERDICIÓN?!"

#. [message], speaker=Vrykos
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:169
msgid ""
"All I hear, and see, is a bunch of fetid rabid wolves, unwashed midgets and "
"freaks led by a Windsong witch. But I think this is how it was always "
"supposed to be: that our final clash is fought over the Red Pinnacle, so "
"that your blood and bones may join those of the countless fools that have "
"ever dared to defy us!"
msgstr ""
"Todo lo que oigo y veo es un montón de lobos rabiosos apestosos, enanos sin "
"lavar y monstruos liderados por una bruja de las Hijas del Viento. Pero creo "
"que así era como siempre debía ser: que nuestro choque final se librara "
"sobre el Pináculo Rojo, ¡para que vuestra sangre y vuestros huesos se unan a "
"los de los innumerables necios que alguna vez osaron desafiarnos!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:173
msgid ""
"Tsc tsc... It's a shame such beautiful mountain has been tainted by the "
"filth of these blood-suckers..."
msgstr ""
"Tsc tsc… Es una lástima que una montaña tan hermosa haya sido manchada por "
"la suciedad de estos chupasangres…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:177
msgid ""
"But, if we clean it thoroughly, I think it could still be worthy to be "
"inhabited by dwarves."
msgstr ""
"Pero si la limpiamos a fondo, creo que aún podría ser digna de ser habitada "
"por enanos."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:181
msgid ""
"You're right, friend! C'mon boys, this mountain's begging us to wipe the "
"vampire filth off its slopes!"
msgstr ""
"¡Tienes razón, amiga! ¡Vamos muchachos, esta montaña nos está suplicando que "
"limpiemos la suciedad vampírica de sus laderas!"

#. [message], speaker=Mani
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:185
msgid "Wargs, charge! Let's show them who the true Children of the Night are!"
msgstr ""
"¡Huargos, carga! ¡Mostrémosles quiénes son los verdaderos Hijos de la Noche!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:194
msgid ""
"Ha! Dawn approaches, and with it the sun that enfeebles those blood-suckers! "
"Strike them now, boys, and we may finish this battle before next sunset!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ja! El amanecer se acerca, ¡y con él el sol que debilita a esos "
"chupasangres! ¡Golpeadlos ahora, muchachos, y quizá terminemos esta batalla "
"antes del próximo atardecer!"

#. [message], speaker=Vrykos
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:198
msgid ""
"Do not underestimate my power, midget! (raises his arms and his face "
"skywards) O wandering clouds, hearken my call: gather thee over these snowy "
"peaks, let no sun beam cross thy vault, envelop this realm in lingering "
"darkness!"
msgstr ""
"¡No subestimes mi poder, enano! (levanta los brazos y el rostro al cielo) "
"¡Oh nubes errantes, escuchad mi llamada: reuníos sobre estos picos nevados, "
"que ningún rayo de sol cruce vuestra bóveda, ¡volved este reino en oscuridad "
"persistente!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:209
msgid ""
"Darn it, the clouds are really gathering up in the sky! How does he do that?"
msgstr ""
"¡Maldición, las nubes se están acumulando de verdad en el cielo! ¡¿Cómo lo "
"hace?!"

#. [message], speaker=Mani
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:213
msgid "Let darkness cover this land! We too fight better in the dark!"
msgstr ""
"¡Que la oscuridad cubra esta tierra! ¡Nosotros también luchamos mejor en la "
"oscuridad!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:217
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, though, there are far more vampires than wargs here, so I'm "
"sorry, Mani, but I'll have to do something about it..."
msgstr ""
"Desgraciadamente, sin embargo, hay muchos más vampiros que huargos aquí, así "
"que lo siento, Mani, pero tendré que hacer algo al respecto…"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:221
msgid ""
"Saying this, Myra raised her trident, and from her eyes shone that already "
"familiar greenish-blue light; the mass of bulky, dark-grey clouds had "
"already started to cover the mountains when a strong wind gust blew from the "
"east, dispersing them until the sky was absolutely blue."
msgstr ""
"Diciendo esto, Myra levantó su tridente y de sus ojos brilló esa ya familiar "
"luz verde-azulada; la masa de nubes voluminosas y gris oscuro ya había "
"empezado a cubrir las montañas cuando una fuerte ráfaga de viento sopló "
"desde el este, dispersándolas hasta que el cielo quedó completamente azul."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:232
msgid ""
"Och, for a moment I forgot that we have the weather goddess on our side! How "
"did you like that, Vrykos?"
msgstr ""
"Och, por un momento olvidé que tenemos a la diosa del clima de nuestro lado. "
"¿Qué te pareció eso, Vrykos?"

#. [message], speaker=Vrykos
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:236
msgid "(in rage) Damn witch, you will pay for that!"
msgstr "(furioso) ¡Bruja maldita, pagarás por eso!"

#. [message], speaker=Mani
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:253
msgid "Aarrgh! Cursed be these blood-suckers! Fight on without me, friends..."
msgstr ""
"¡Aarrgh! ¡Malditos sean estos chupasangres! ¡Seguid luchando sin mí, amigos…!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:267
msgid "...!!!"
msgstr "…!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:271
msgid "Myra? Is something the matter?"
msgstr "¿Myra? ¿Pasa algo?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:275
msgid "...No... This..."
msgstr "…No… Esto…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:279
msgid "What has happened? You look pale all of a sudden..."
msgstr "¿Qué ha pasado? De repente te has puesto pálida…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:283
msgid ""
"I... I have a bad feeling... Like a claw seizing my heart... Something has "
"happened, Jevyan, something terrible. Let's finish this battle as quickly as "
"we can, and then hurry to Hiera'Laksha..."
msgstr ""
"Yo… Tengo un mal presentimiento… Como una garra agarrando mi corazón… Algo "
"ha pasado, Jevyan, algo terrible. Terminemos esta batalla lo más rápido que "
"podamos y luego corramos a Hiera’Laksha…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:287
msgid ""
"Hiera...? (looks pale) You're right, we must finish this battle, and quickly!"
msgstr ""
"¡Hiera…? (se pone pálido) Tienes razón, ¡debemos terminar esta batalla, y "
"rápido!"

#. [message], speaker=Vrykos
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:296
msgid ""
"Ugh... You may have bested me, but our plague shall continue to haunt the "
"nights...!"
msgstr ""
"Ugh… Puede que me hayáis vencido, ¡pero nuestra plaga seguirá acechando las "
"noches…!"

#. [message], speaker=Mani
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:300
msgid "VICTORY AT LAST!"
msgstr "¡¡¡VICTORIA AL FIN!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:304
msgid ""
"Ah, that was a battle like I haven't had in ages... Wait, where are you "
"going?"
msgstr "Ah, esa fue una batalla como no tenía en años… Espera, ¿adónde vais?"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:308
msgid ""
"Sorry, friend, but you'll have to celebrate this victory without us. Myra "
"sensed some terrible thing has happened in Hiera'Laksha, and so we're going "
"there."
msgstr ""
"Lo siento, amigo, pero tendrás que celebrar esta victoria sin nosotros. Myra "
"sintió que algo terrible ha pasado en Hiera’Laksha, así que vamos para allá."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:312
msgid ""
"Don't worry, it must be the vampires, but they won't succeed in invading "
"Hiera'Laksha, especially now that their king is..."
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes, deben ser los vampiros, pero no conseguirán invadir "
"Hiera’Laksha, especialmente ahora que su rey está…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:316
msgid ""
"You don't understand, Dvalin; Myra has left the... the gem there, with "
"Akashia!"
msgstr "No lo entiendes, Dvalin; ¡Myra dejó allí la… la gema, con Akashia!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:320
msgid ""
"You mean the Sky Soul?! But... Why haven't you said it before? We must be "
"there in no time!"
msgstr ""
"¡¿Te refieres al Alma del Cielo?! Pero… ¡¿Por qué no lo dijisteis antes?! "
"¡Debemos llegar allí en un instante!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:324
msgid ""
"You won't be able to keep with my elementals' pace, Dvalin... Now, you "
"should go back to your home, and make sure Alenya is safe; if my fears are "
"correct, her valley may be at danger."
msgstr ""
"No podrás seguir el ritmo de mis elementales, Dvalin… Ahora deberías volver "
"a tu hogar y asegurarte de que Alenya esté a salvo; si mis temores son "
"ciertos, su valle podría estar en peligro."

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:328
msgid "Damn it girl, now you're scaring me! What are you even..."
msgstr ""
"¡Maldita sea, chica, ahora me estás asustando! ¡¿De qué estás hablando…?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:332
msgid "Just do that, for all you hold sacred! I will contact you later!"
msgstr ""
"¡Solo hazlo, por todo lo que consideras sagrado! ¡Me pondré en contacto "
"contigo después!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:336
msgid ""
"Then take my gold; I have plenty back at home, and if Hiera'Laksha is in "
"danger you'll need every coin you can get your hands on."
msgstr ""
"Entonces toma mi oro; tengo mucho en casa y si Hiera’Laksha está en peligro "
"necesitaréis cada moneda que podáis conseguir."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:340
msgid "Thank you, Dvalin..."
msgstr "Gracias, Dvalin…"

#. [message], speaker=Mani
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:344
msgid ""
"I don't know what you're talking about, but if you don't want to loot "
"Vrykos' treasury, then I'll get all his gold for myself..."
msgstr ""
"No sé de qué estáis hablando, pero si no queréis saquear el tesoro de "
"Vrykos, ¡entonces me quedaré yo con todo su oro…!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/31_Night_Fire.cfg:450
msgid ""
"No! How could we take so much time here, when Hiera'Laksha is in danger?"
msgstr ""
"¡No! ¡¿Cómo hemos podido tardar tanto aquí, cuando Hiera’Laksha está en "
"peligro?!"

#. [scenario], id=32_Fading_Of_A_Flame
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:4
msgid "Fading of a Flame"
msgstr "Apagón de una Llama"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:22
msgid "Resist until the end of turns"
msgstr "Resistir hasta el final de los turnos"

#. [objectives]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:43
msgid "NOTE: Akashia may recall the Windsong formerly under Myra's command."
msgstr ""
"NOTA: Akashia puede reincorporar a las Hijas del Viento que antes estaban "
"bajo el mando de Myra."

#. [side]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:72
msgid "Hiera'Laksha"
msgstr "Hiera’Laksha"

#. [side], type=Celestial Herald
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:80
msgid "Lumens"
msgstr "Lumens"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:178
msgid "No... No..."
msgstr "No… No…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:182
msgid ""
"Hearten yourself, my love, at least we haven't arrived too late, we can "
"still save Hiera'Laksha!"
msgstr ""
"(angustiado) ¡Ánimo, amor mío, al menos no hemos llegado demasiado tarde, "
"aún podemos salvar Hiera’Laksha!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:186
msgid ""
"Myra... You were right all along, these... animals have waited until "
"everyone was up to the neck in the war against the orcs and the vampires... "
"We have just repelled a wave of them, so go back to your war in peace, that "
"they will not get their filthy hands on the Soul, this I swear!"
msgstr ""
"Myra… Tenías razón todo el tiempo, estos… animales han esperado hasta que "
"todos estábamos metidos hasta el cuello en la guerra contra los orcos y los "
"vampiros… Acabamos de repeler una oleada de ellos, así que volved a vuestra "
"guerra en paz, ¡que no pondrán sus sucias manos en el Alma, lo juro!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:190
msgid ""
"Go back to my war? To hell with the war, all I care about right now is you "
"and our sisters!"
msgstr ""
"¿Volver a mi guerra? ¡Al infierno con la guerra, ahora mismo lo único que me "
"importa sois vosotras y nuestras hermanas!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:194
msgid "Please, don't make me laugh..."
msgstr "(riendo cansada) Por favor, no me hagas reír…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:198
msgid "...W-what?"
msgstr "…¿Q-qué?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:202
msgid ""
"You abandoned us five years ago, when you left our Order to build a family, "
"just as so many other former Windsong have done since we left the Great "
"Continent! So don't you act all magnanimous now, we don't need your help; "
"we'll fend off by ourselves, just as we've been doing all these years!"
msgstr ""
"¡Nos abandonaste hace cinco años, cuando dejaste nuestra Orden para formar "
"una familia, igual que tantas otras ex Hijas del Viento desde que dejamos el "
"Gran Continente! ¡Así que no actúes ahora de magnánima, no necesitamos tu "
"ayuda; nos defenderemos solas, ¡como hemos estado haciendo todos estos años!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:206
msgid "(in shock) Akashia, why..."
msgstr "(en shock) Akashia, por qué…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:210
msgid ""
"I can't believe it... Of all things I expected to see here, I honestly... "
"But this is not what we must be worrying about right now; we must go to her "
"aid, and quickly!"
msgstr ""
"No me lo puedo creer… De todas las cosas que esperaba ver aquí, "
"sinceramente… ¡Pero esto no es lo que debemos preocuparnos ahora; debemos ir "
"en su ayuda, y rápido!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:214
msgid "You... you are right, now we... we must fight..."
msgstr "Tienes… tienes razón, ahora debemos… debemos luchar…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:223
msgid "Akashia, please give the gem back to me."
msgstr "Akashia, por favor devuélveme la gema."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:227
msgid ""
"Now is not a good time; we're in the middle of a battle, there are "
"Celestials everywhere; one of them might swoop down and steal the Soul while "
"I'm handing it to you."
msgstr ""
"Ahora no es buen momento; estamos en medio de una batalla, hay celestiales "
"por todas partes; uno de ellos podría abalanzarse y robar el Alma mientras "
"te la estoy dando."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:231
msgid "That won't happen if we're next to each other."
msgstr "Eso no pasará si estamos juntas."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:235
msgid "Why such insistence? Don't you trust me anymore?"
msgstr "¿Por qué tanta insistencia? ¿Ya no confías en mí?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:239
msgid ""
"That's not it, as you know very well! I'm just afraid my spell wasn't enough "
"to hold back the Soul's evil aura..."
msgstr ""
"¡No es eso, como bien sabes! ¡Solo tengo miedo de que mi hechizo no fuera "
"suficiente para contener el aura maligna del Alma…!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:243
msgid "Or maybe you think I'm too susceptible to it..."
msgstr "O quizá piensas que soy demasiado susceptible a ella…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:247
msgid ""
"I... (sigh) All right, keep it until the end of the battle, but I will want "
"it back when we repel the Celestials."
msgstr ""
"Yo… (suspira) De acuerdo, quédate con ella hasta el final de la batalla, "
"pero la quiero de vuelta cuando repeleremos a los celestiales."

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:251
msgid "As you wish..."
msgstr "Como desees…"

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:265
msgid ""
"Tremble, sinners, for thy righteous punishment is on the verge of falling "
"onto thee!"
msgstr ""
"¡Temblad, pecadores, porque vuestro justo castigo está a punto de caer sobre "
"vosotros!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:269
msgid ""
"Do not provoke me, bird-people, you have <i>no damn idea</i> of what I can "
"do..."
msgstr ""
"No me provoquéis, gente-pájaro, ¡no tenéis <i>ni puta idea</i> de lo que "
"puedo hacer…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:290
msgid ""
"Please, don't think I distrust you, I'm just worried that the Soul may be "
"having a negative effect on you! There's no reason to feel ashamed of that, "
"even I was affected by it once, don't you remember?"
msgstr ""
"¡Por favor, no pienses que desconfío de ti, solo estoy preocupada de que el "
"Alma pueda estar teniendo un efecto negativo en ti! ¡No hay razón para "
"avergonzarse de eso, hasta yo fui afectada por ella una vez, no lo "
"recuerdas?!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:294
msgid ""
"If you trust me as much as you claim to do, then let me keep the Soul until "
"the end of this battle; besides, I now want to show you I'm not so "
"susceptible to its aura."
msgstr ""
"Si confías en mí tanto como dices, entonces déjame quedarme con el Alma "
"hasta el final de esta batalla; además, ahora quiero demostrarte que no soy "
"tan susceptible a su aura."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:298
msgid ""
"By the Gods of Light, Akashia, you don't need to prove anything! All right, "
"you know what? I also want to prove that I do trust you, so stay with the "
"Soul until the end of this battle. However, we <i>will</i> sit down and have "
"a serious talk when this is over."
msgstr ""
"¡Por los Dioses de la Luz, Akashia, no necesitas demostrar nada! De acuerdo, "
"¿sabes qué? Yo también quiero demostrar que confío en ti, así que quédate "
"con el Alma hasta el final de esta batalla. Sin embargo, <i>sí</i> nos "
"sentaremos y tendremos una charla seria cuando esto termine."

#. [message], speaker=Lumens
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:317
msgid ""
"I am troubled to admit this, but these sinners are proving themselves a "
"match for us. Unfortunately, their resistance is futile: call in the "
"reserves!"
msgstr ""
"Me duele admitirlo, pero estos pecadores están demostrando ser un rival para "
"nosotros. Desgraciadamente, su resistencia es inútil: ¡llamad a las reservas!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:321
msgid ""
"Damn these Celestials! Hold on, friends, we shall not fall to these "
"treacherous bastards!"
msgstr ""
"¡Malditos celestiales! ¡Aguantad, amigos, no caeremos ante estos bastardos "
"traidores!"

#. [message], speaker=Lumens
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:334
msgid ""
"Blessed be the Heavens, new troops have arrived! Now, there is no way we "
"will be overcome by these sinners!"
msgstr ""
"¡Benditos sean los Cielos, han llegado nuevas tropas! ¡Ahora no hay forma de "
"que nos venzan estos pecadores!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:368
msgid ""
"Curse them! We must evacuate Hiera'Laksha, there's no way we can defeat such "
"a large army!"
msgstr ""
"¡Malditos sean! ¡Debemos evacuar Hiera’Laksha, no hay forma de derrotar a un "
"ejército tan grande!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:372
msgid ""
"Jevyan... Jevyan is right, my sisters, we... we must leave this mountain "
"immediately, or we'll all perish!"
msgstr ""
"Jevyan… Jevyan tiene razón, hermanas mías, nosotros… debemos abandonar esta "
"montaña inmediatamente, ¡o pereceremos todos!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:376
msgid ""
"(trembling in fury) No... I will not simply flee and see our Foundation "
"destroyed, not again!"
msgstr ""
"(temblando de furia) ¡No… no huiré simplemente y veré nuestra Fundación "
"destruida, no otra vez!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:380
msgid ""
"And what do you intend to do? We're completely outnumbered! Do as you "
"Windsong did in Hiera'Shirsha: let the Foundation fall, but save your "
"sisters, for they are the future of your order!"
msgstr ""
"¡¿Y qué pretendes hacer?! ¡Estamos completamente superados en número! ¡Haz "
"como hicieron las Hijas del Viento en Hiera’Shirsha: deja caer la Fundación, "
"pero salva a tus hermanas, porque ellas son el futuro de tu orden!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:384
msgid "NO! WE CAN'T - WE WON'T FLEE AGAIN!"
msgstr "¡¡¡NO!!! ¡NO PODEMOS — NO HUIREMOS OTRA VEZ!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:393
msgid "I know exactly how we shall prevail..."
msgstr "Sé exactamente cómo prevaleceremos…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:397
msgid "And how... Wait, Akashia, you can't possibly be planning..."
msgstr "¿Y cómo…? ¡Espera, Akashia, no estarás planeando…!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:401
msgid ""
"I have studied it during the time I kept it, back when we were crossing the "
"ocean; I even dare say that I understand it better than you did at Ughure, "
"so..."
msgstr ""
"Lo he estudiado durante el tiempo que lo guardé, cuando cruzábamos el "
"océano; incluso me atrevo a decir que lo entiendo mejor que tú en Ughure, "
"así que…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:405
msgid ""
"Don't be stupid, there is no way... Listen, Akashia, please, I beg you, "
"don't..."
msgstr ""
"¡No seas estúpida, no hay forma…! ¡Escucha, Akashia, por favor, te lo "
"suplico, no…!"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:409
msgid ""
"(unwraps the Soul and raises it to the sky) Now, winged bastards, it's "
"payback..."
msgstr ""
"(desenvuelve el Alma y la levanta al cielo) Ahora, bastardos alados, es hora "
"de la venganza…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:455
msgid "...time...?!"
msgstr "…¿hora…?!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:459
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:232
msgid "No..."
msgstr "No…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:463
msgid "AKASHIA!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡AKASHIA!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:467
msgid ""
"I am mostly pleased for this offering, and so (picks the gem) I shall accept "
"it."
msgstr ""
"Estoy muy satisfecho con esta ofrenda, y por eso (toma la gema) la aceptaré."

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:474
msgid ""
"Brave warriors of Light, too many of you have died already; there is no "
"reason for more to perish this day. Furthermore, I have already gotten hold "
"of their evil artefact, so let us return to our tower!"
msgstr ""
"¡Valientes guerreros de la Luz, ya han muerto demasiados de vosotros; no hay "
"razón para que perezcan más este día! Además, ya me he apoderado de su "
"artefacto maligno, ¡así que volvamos a nuestra torre!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:483
msgid ""
"(crying) No... no, no, no, no, why did he have to hit you there...? Stand "
"still, friend, I will cure you in no time..."
msgstr ""
"(llorando) No… no, no, no, no, ¿por qué tuvo que golpearte ahí…? Quédate "
"quieta, amiga, te curaré en un momento…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:487
msgid "No... give it up..."
msgstr "No… déjalo…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:491
msgid ""
"(frantic) Did I hear it well? Did I hear the words 'give up' leaving the "
"mouth of Akashia the Strong? Just stay still; we have been through much "
"worse, it's not a cursed Celestial blade that will defeat us, right?"
msgstr ""
"(frenética) ¿He oído bien? ¿He oído las palabras «déjalo» salir de la boca "
"de Akashia la Fuerte? ¡Solo quédate quieta; hemos pasado por cosas mucho "
"peores, no será una maldita hoja celestial la que nos derrote, verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:495
msgid ""
"Myra, hear me for once in your... life... Take me inside... I want to talk "
"to you..."
msgstr ""
"Myra, escúchame por una vez en tu… vida… Llévame dentro… Quiero hablar "
"contigo…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:499
msgid "(stunned) Myra, let's..."
msgstr "(atónito) Myra, vamos…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:508
msgid "A-all right then..."
msgstr "D-de acuerdo…"

#. [message], speaker=Akashia
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/32_Fading_Of_A_Flame.cfg:565
msgid "I have... fallen...?!"
msgstr "¿He… caído…?!"

#. [scenario], id=33_The_Valley_Of_Silence
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:4
msgid "The Valley of Silence"
msgstr "El Valle del Silencio"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:21
msgid "Defeat Nephel"
msgstr "Derrotar a Nephel"

#. [objectives]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:47
msgid ""
"NOTE: Dvalin may recall the dwarves that fought in scenario 31; also, Myra "
"may now recall the Windsong veterans and units recruited in the previous "
"scenario, but not recruit new Windsong units."
msgstr ""
"NOTA: Dvalin puede reincorporar a los enanos que lucharon en el escenario "
"31; además, Myra ahora puede reincorporar a las veteranas Hijas del Viento y "
"unidades reclutadas en el escenario anterior, pero no reclutar nuevas "
"unidades Hijas del Viento."

#. [side]
#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:72
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/utils/characters.cfg:77
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/utils/intros.cfg:330
msgid "Alenya"
msgstr "Alenya"

#. [side], type=Sage
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:86
msgid "Nephel"
msgstr "Nephel"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:199
msgid ""
"Look, milady! Your fears were right, as expected: the valley is swarming "
"with those winged bastards!"
msgstr ""
"¡Mirad, milady! ¡Vuestros temores eran ciertos, como era de esperar: el "
"valle está plagado de esos bastardos alados!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:203
msgid "Alenya, Dvalin! Hold out just a little longer, we're coming!"
msgstr "¡Alenya, Dvalin! ¡Aguantad un poco más, ya vamos!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:207
msgid ""
"(Laughing in relief) Oh, blessed be the Gods of Light! I feared we would all "
"perish here!"
msgstr ""
"(riendo aliviada) ¡Oh, benditos sean los Dioses de la Luz! ¡Temía que todos "
"pereciéramos aquí!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:211
msgid ""
"Alenya, we have brought some extra gold from Hiera'Laksha, please accept it, "
"for you are clearly in need... But wait, are those maidens elves?"
msgstr ""
"Alenya, hemos traído oro extra de Hiera’Laksha, por favor acéptalo, "
"claramente lo necesitáis… Pero espera, ¿esas doncellas son elfas?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:220
msgid ""
"Thanks very much for the gold, and no, they're fairies; I found them hiding "
"in this valley, but methinks this is not the right time to tell this story!"
msgstr ""
"Muchas gracias por el oro, y no, son hadas; las encontré escondidas en este "
"valle, ¡pero creo que no es el momento de contar esa historia!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:224
msgid ""
"Myra, I... we owe you our lives; hadn't you warned me back there in the "
"north, Alenya would..."
msgstr ""
"Myra, yo… te debemos nuestras vidas; si no me hubieras avisado allá en el "
"norte, Alenya habría…"

#. [message], speaker=Nephel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:228
msgid ""
"Thy fates are fixed already, miserable beings, and it shall not change "
"regardless of how many of thy henchmen come to aid thee!"
msgstr ""
"¡Vuestros destinos ya están sellados, seres miserables, y no cambiarán por "
"muchos lacayos que vengan a ayudaros!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:251
msgid "...it is <i>you</i>..."
msgstr "…eres <i>tú</i>…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:260
msgid "...who will meet your fate here..."
msgstr "…quien encontrará aquí su destino…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:269
msgid "...this I swear."
msgstr "…lo juro."

#. [message], speaker=Nephel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:286
msgid ""
"(thrilled) Can it be? Will I finally have the chance to smite the famous "
"nature heretic? O Great Gods, I humbly thank you for answering my prayers! "
"Come, Myra of Hiera'Shirsha! Let's see how your witchcraft fares against the "
"holy power of the Heavens!"
msgstr ""
"(emocionado) ¿Puede ser? ¿Finalmente tendré la oportunidad de aniquilar a la "
"famosa hereje de la naturaleza? ¡Oh Grandes Dioses, os agradezco "
"humildemente haber escuchado mis plegarias! ¡Ven, Myra de Hiera’Shirsha! "
"¡Veamos cómo le va a tu brujería contra el poder sagrado de los Cielos!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:304
msgid "Argh! No, damn it, why does it have to happen now...?"
msgstr "¡Argh! ¡No, maldición, por qué tiene que pasar ahora…!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:308
msgid "Alenya? What is happening with you?"
msgstr "¿Alenya? ¿Qué te pasa?"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:312
msgid ""
"It... Alenya, get into your home now, and take some of these fairies to help "
"you!"
msgstr ""
"¡Es… Alenya, entra en tu casa ahora mismo y lleva a algunas de estas hadas "
"para que te ayuden!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:316
msgid "I'm fine, it's just..."
msgstr "Estoy bien, solo es que…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:330
msgid ""
"Alenya, you are...! (shouting) Dvalin is right, you must go inside "
"immediately, but I'll choose three Windsong to help you with the labour!"
msgstr ""
"¡Alenya, estás…! (gritando) ¡Dvalin tiene razón, debes entrar "
"inmediatamente, pero yo elegiré a tres Hijas del Viento para ayudarte con el "
"parto!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:334
msgid "What do you mean by 'labour'?! No, wait, is she really..."
msgstr "¿Qué quieres decir con «parto»?! ¡No, espera, de verdad está…!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:338
msgid ""
"Turns out my joke was true, after all; Alenya, you did some job concealing "
"your pregnancy from me, but I would lecture you on how stupid it was of you, "
"to fight in these conditions, if I just had the time for that!"
msgstr ""
"Resulta que mi broma era cierta, después de todo; Alenya, hiciste un gran "
"trabajo ocultándome tu embarazo, ¡pero te daría una buena reprimenda por lo "
"estúpido que fue luchar en estas condiciones si tuviera tiempo para eso!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:342
msgid ""
"Right, I'm withdrawing from battle... Fairies, please... fight for Myra..."
msgstr ""
"De acuerdo, me retiro de la batalla… Hadas, por favor… luchad por Myra…"

#. [message], speaker=Nephel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:359
msgid "Is... Is that blonde female giving birth?"
msgstr "¿Es… esa hembra rubia está dando a luz?"

#. [message], speaker=Nephel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:368
msgid ""
"As the teaching says, 'cut the poisonous herb as soon as it lifts its first "
"branches out of the soil'... Do not let yourselves be fooled by innocent-"
"looking faces, my warriors, and smite the newborn lest it will grow into "
"another sinner!"
msgstr ""
"Como dice la enseñanza, «corta la hierba venenosa en cuanto levante sus "
"primeras ramas del suelo»… ¡No os dejéis engañar por caras de apariencia "
"inocente, guerreros míos, y aniquilad al recién nacido no sea que crezca y "
"se convierta en otro pecador!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:372
msgid "OVER..."
msgstr "¡SOBRE…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:376
msgid "...MY..."
msgstr "…MI…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:380
msgid "...DEAD BODY!"
msgstr "¡CADÁVER!"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:389
msgid "Go meet your gods now, you monster! (beheads the enemy)"
msgstr ""
"¡Ve a reunirte con tus dioses ahora, monstruo! (le corta la cabeza al "
"enemigo)"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:393
msgid ""
"I really don't know how to thank you, my friends; without your aid, we "
"wouldn't have managed to defend this valley, and Alenya... Our child..."
msgstr ""
"De verdad no sé cómo agradecéroslo, amigos; sin vuestra ayuda no habríamos "
"logrado defender este valle, y Alenya… Nuestro hijo…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:397
msgid "Thank us later, now we must see how Alenya is faring!"
msgstr "¡Danos las gracias después, ahora tenemos que ver cómo está Alenya!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:430
msgid "I have fallen without avenging Akashia..."
msgstr "He caído sin vengar a Akashia…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:462
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1330
msgid "Aaahhh!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡Aaahhh!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:466
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1334
msgid "ALENYA, NO!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡ALENYA, NO!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:481
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1349
msgid "Aarrgh!!! Sorry, Alenya, I've failed you..."
msgstr "¡¡¡Aarrgh!!! Lo siento, Alenya, te he fallado…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:485
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1353
msgid "DVALIN, NO!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡DVALIN, NO!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/33_The_Valley_Of_Silence.cfg:498
msgid ""
"We couldn't have lost so much time here! Now, who knows what Grigorius has "
"done with the Soul...?"
msgstr ""
"¡No podíamos haber perdido tanto tiempo aquí! Ahora, quién sabe qué ha hecho "
"Grigorius con el Alma…?"

#. [scenario], id=34_Last_Revelations
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:4
msgid "Last Revelations"
msgstr "Últimas Revelaciones"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:74
msgid "(smiling sadly) It's been a long time, Myra."
msgstr "(sonriendo con tristeza) Ha pasado mucho tiempo, Myra."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:78
msgid ""
"In silence, Myra came closer to the Celestial, and, without warning, punched "
"her on the face with all her strength."
msgstr ""
"En silencio, Myra se acercó a la Celestial y, sin previo aviso, le dio un "
"puñetazo en la cara con todas sus fuerzas."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:90
msgid "Myra, please wait..."
msgstr "Myra, por favor espera…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:94
msgid "I demand to know what this..."
msgstr "¡Exijo saber qué hace esta…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:106
msgid "...cursed..."
msgstr "…maldita…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:117
msgid "...Celestial is doing in our city!"
msgstr "…Celestial en nuestra ciudad!"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:121
msgid "I will tell, but you should not hurt her, she is not our enemy!"
msgstr "Te lo contaré, pero no le hagas daño, ¡no es nuestra enemiga!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:125
msgid ""
"No, Master Tarkyn, let her hit me as much as she wants; I deserve it, after "
"all..."
msgstr ""
"No, maestro Tarkyn, déjala que me pegue cuanto quiera; me lo merezco, "
"después de todo…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:129
msgid ""
"<i>You</i>... (points the Trident at her throat) <i>Do you think I'm "
"jesting? Do you think I'm not capable of butchering you right here and now</"
"i>?"
msgstr ""
"<i>Tú</i>… (le apunta con el Tridente a la garganta) <i>¿Crees que estoy "
"bromeando? ¿Crees que no soy capaz de descuartizarte aquí mismo ahora mismo</"
"i>?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:133
msgid ""
"If you so wish, I swear I will submit myself to your anger, but I beg you to "
"let me live long enough just so that I could transmit to you my... my "
"brother's message..."
msgstr ""
"Si así lo deseas, juro que me someteré a tu ira, pero te suplico que me "
"dejes vivir lo suficiente para poder transmitirte el… el mensaje de mi "
"hermano…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:137
msgid "(in rage) What do you mean?"
msgstr "(furiosa) ¿Qué quieres decir?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:141
msgid ""
"You certainly remember Zaal, whom we killed when you visited the Crystal "
"Tower; and I'm certain you remember that he claimed to have uncovered a "
"terrible secret about our order, right?"
msgstr ""
"Seguro que recuerdas a Zaal, al que matamos cuando visitaste la Torre de "
"Cristal; y estoy segura de que recuerdas que él afirmó haber descubierto un "
"terrible secreto sobre nuestra orden, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:145
msgid "I do."
msgstr "Sí."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:149
msgid ""
"All these years we have deemed him a mere traitor, who let himself be "
"corrupted by the powers of darkness; but my brother, Atron, remained "
"unsatisfied with that explanation, even though I insisted that, as painful "
"as it was, he had to admit that Zaal was not who we thought him to be. "
"However, few days ago..."
msgstr ""
"Todos estos años lo hemos considerado un simple traidor que se dejó "
"corromper por los poderes de las tinieblas; pero mi hermano Atron no quedó "
"satisfecho con esa explicación, aunque yo insistía en que, por doloroso que "
"fuera, tenía que admitir que Zaal no era quien creíamos. Sin embargo, hace "
"pocos días…"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:158
msgid ""
"I was meditating in the middle of the desert, when my brother came to me, "
"terribly injured, barely able to move. He looked into my eyes, and told me "
"that he had just witnessed Lord Grigorius killing... killing the other "
"Lords. I wanted to say no, that he certainly had not seen well, but my "
"brother... I have grown with him, Myra, I am a witness of how... honest, "
"loyal, kind, brave and dedicated he was... I tried to convince myself he had "
"simply seen wrongly, and that, if we explained that to the Lords, they would "
"certainly forgive his foolishness..."
msgstr ""
"Estaba meditando en medio del desierto cuando mi hermano vino a mí, "
"gravemente herido, apenas capaz de moverse. Me miró a los ojos y me dijo que "
"acababa de ver a lord Grigorius matando… matando a los otros Señores. Quise "
"decir que no, que seguro no había visto bien, pero mi hermano… crecí con él, "
"Myra, soy testigo de lo honesto, leal, bondadoso, valiente y entregado que "
"era… Intenté convencerme de que simplemente había visto mal y que, si se lo "
"explicábamos a los Señores, seguro perdonarían su locura…"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:162
msgid "And then a group of Heralds came..."
msgstr "Y entonces llegó un grupo de Heraldos…"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:166
msgid ""
"My brother fought fiercely, but he was wounded and outnumbered. I tried to "
"end that nonsense, I tried to explain that my brother was, and had always "
"been, a renowned Celestial, that whatever wrong he had done was not ill-"
"intentioned, but all they said was, 'this is Lord Grigorius' will', and "
"then... then... they beheaded him, as if he was an animal...! I fled, Myra, "
"I fled and I hid myself for a few days, and then I sought you, for I knew no "
"one else whom I thought I could trust..."
msgstr ""
"Mi hermano luchó con fiereza, pero estaba herido y superado en número. "
"Intenté poner fin a esa locura, intenté explicar que mi hermano era, y "
"siempre había sido, un Celestial renombrado, que cualquier error que hubiera "
"cometido no fue con mala intención, pero todo lo que decían era «esta es la "
"voluntad de lord Grigorius», y luego… luego… ¡lo decapitaron, como si fuera "
"un animal…! Huí, Myra, huí y me escondí unos días, y luego te busqué porque "
"no sabía a quién más podía confiar…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:170
msgid ""
"I recall you were extremely dedicated to the Lords, just as you claim your "
"brother was; do you want me to believe you have turned your back on them out "
"of a sudden?"
msgstr ""
"Recuerdo que tú eras extremadamente devota a los Señores, igual que dices "
"que lo era tu hermano; ¿quieres que me crea que de repente les has dado la "
"espalda?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:174
msgid ""
"I was dedicated, yes; I was proud of serving an order that served the light, "
"that wanted to protect the world; I was proud of serving Lords that were "
"supremely powerful, but who were also wise, kind and forgiving. But the "
"Lords I served would never have treated my brother like that, not after all "
"he had done for the Celestials."
msgstr ""
"Sí lo era; estaba orgullosa de servir a una orden que servía a la luz, que "
"quería proteger el mundo; estaba orgullosa de servir a Señores que eran "
"supremamente poderosos, pero también sabios, bondadosos y misericordiosos. "
"Pero los Señores a los que yo servía nunca habrían tratado así a mi hermano, "
"no después de todo lo que él había hecho por los Celestiales."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:178
msgid ""
"You know what Grigorius has just done to Hiera'Laksha, don't you? (more "
"menacingly) You know what he did to my friend Akashia, don't you?"
msgstr ""
"Sabes lo que Grigorius acaba de hacerle a Hiera’Laksha, ¿verdad? (más "
"amenazante) Sabes lo que le hizo a mi amiga Akashia, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:182
msgid ""
"(crying) I'm sorry, I really am! I know how it feels, Myra, to lose a loved "
"one, I have just lost my brother!"
msgstr ""
"(llorando) ¡Lo siento, lo siento de verdad! Sé cómo se siente, Myra, perder "
"a un ser querido, ¡acabo de perder a mi hermano!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:191
msgid ""
"You said Grigorius killed the other Lords; is that all you know? Can't you "
"tell, for example, whether he has any secret ally or power?"
msgstr ""
"Dijiste que Grigorius mató a los otros Señores; ¿es eso todo lo que sabes? "
"¿No puedes decir, por ejemplo, si tiene algún aliado secreto o poder?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:195
msgid "No, not that I know..."
msgstr "No, que yo sepa no…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:199
msgid "Well, so now he has a weapon. He stole the Sky Soul."
msgstr "Pues ahora tiene un arma. Ha robado el Alma del Cielo."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:203
msgid "(gets pale) He <i>what</i>?"
msgstr "(se pone pálido) ¿Que ha hecho <i>qué</i>?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:207
msgid ""
"And also for that reason, I'm going to the Crystal Tower, kill him and every "
"Celestial that stands between us, and recover the Soul."
msgstr ""
"Y por eso mismo, voy a ir a la Torre de Cristal, matarlo a él y a todo "
"Celestial que se interponga, y recuperar el Alma."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:211
msgid ""
"But... he can't possibly be thinking about using that evil power! I mean..."
msgstr ""
"Pero… ¡no puede estar pensando en usar ese poder maligno! Quiero decir…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:215
msgid ""
"So even now you defend him? (sigh) Listen, if that was all you wanted to "
"tell me, know that it was completely useless. Now, leave this city while I "
"still allow it."
msgstr ""
"¿Todavía ahora lo defiendes? (suspira) Escucha, si eso era todo lo que "
"querías contarme, sab que ha sido totalmente inútil. Ahora, abandona esta "
"ciudad mientras aún te lo permita."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:219
msgid ""
"I... I understand. But listen, Myra, I have a useful information, in case "
"you really go fight Lord Grigorius: you may deem him powerful, but what you "
"have seen is barely half of his power. He fears you, this I know, and so I "
"am certain that, if you challenge him, he'll undergo Apotheosis."
msgstr ""
"Yo… Lo entiendo. Pero escucha, Myra, tengo información útil por si realmente "
"vas a luchar contra lord Grigorius: puedes considerarlo poderoso, pero lo "
"que has visto es apenas la mitad de su poder. Te teme, eso lo sé, y por eso "
"estoy segura de que, si lo desafías, pasará por la Apoteosis."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:223
msgid "Will you mind explaining what does it mean?"
msgstr "¿Te importa explicar qué significa eso?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:227
msgid ""
"See, we Celestials are actually but descendants of the true, original "
"Celestials. Those amongst us with more of their blood also have much of "
"their power as well. However, the Seraphins, the highest amongst us, are "
"able to awaken their full Celestial might: this is the Apotheosis. Through "
"it, they reach a power level similar to those of the original Celestials."
msgstr ""
"Mira, nosotros los Celestiales somos en realidad solo descendientes de los "
"verdaderos Celestiales originales. Aquellos entre nosotros con más sangre "
"suya también tienen mucho de su poder. Sin embargo, los Serafines, los más "
"altos entre nosotros, pueden despertar todo su poder Celestial: eso es la "
"Apoteosis. Con ella alcanzan un nivel de poder similar al de los Celestiales "
"originales."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:231
msgid ""
"For once in your life you were useful... Now, I suppose you have no more "
"precious information, so leave this city immediately. You may hide in the "
"northern mountains; Vrykos is no more, the vampires are weakened and "
"leaderless, so you may find some safety there."
msgstr ""
"Por una vez en tu vida has sido útil… Ahora supongo que no tienes más "
"información valiosa, así que abandona esta ciudad de inmediato. Puedes "
"esconderte en las montañas del norte; Vrykos ya no está, los vampiros están "
"debilitados y sin líder, allí podrás encontrar algo de seguridad."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:235
msgid "Thank you, Myra... I... I sincerely hope you... defeat him..."
msgstr "Gracias, Myra… Yo… de verdad espero que espero que… lo derrotes…"

#. [message], speaker=Aldrik
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:250
msgid "Mom, what's up? Where's dad?"
msgstr "Mamá, ¿qué pasa? ¿Dónde está papá?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:254
msgid ""
"(smiling faintly) Dad is fine, he is with aunt Alenya and uncle Dvalin... "
"Guess what? They've just had a baby girl! When she's a bit older, you will "
"become real good friends!"
msgstr ""
"(sonriendo débilmente) Papá está bien, está con la tía Alenya y el tío "
"Dvalin… ¡Adivina! ¡Acaban de tener una niña! Cuando sea un poco mayor, "
"¡seréis muy buenos amigos!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:263
msgid ""
"I love you so much, my son... You understand that everything I do is for "
"your good, don't you?"
msgstr ""
"Te quiero muchísimo, hijo mío… Entiendes que todo lo que hago es por tu "
"bien, ¿verdad?"

#. [message], speaker=Aldrik
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:267
msgid "Of co... Of course!"
msgstr "¡C-claro!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:271
msgid ""
"(laughing) I will play a little with you later, but now mom needs to do "
"something; meanwhile, stay with grandpa, right?"
msgstr ""
"(riendo) Jugaré un poco contigo más tarde, pero ahora mamá tiene que hacer "
"algo; mientras, quédate con el abuelo, ¿vale?"

#. [message], speaker=Aldrik
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:275
msgid "Yes!"
msgstr "¡Sí!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:283
msgid "It's fine, father, for now I'll just meditate a little..."
msgstr "Está bien, padre, por ahora solo voy a meditar un poco…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:305
msgid ""
"We haven't talked with each other so directly in a long time, Nitiballi."
msgstr "Hace mucho que no hablamos tan directamente, Nitiballi."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:310
msgid "Because we have not needed to talk."
msgstr "Porque no hemos necesitado hablar."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:314
msgid ""
"And why do we need now? Do you have any objections to my plan of destroying "
"the Soul?"
msgstr ""
"¿Y por qué ahora sí? ¿Tienes alguna objeción a mi plan de destruir el Alma?"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:319
msgid "I do. You cannot possibly destroy it; no being on this world can."
msgstr "Sí. No puedes destruirla; ningún ser en este mundo puede hacerlo."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:323
msgid ""
"Everything that exists can be destroyed; I refuse to believe his soul is an "
"exception."
msgstr ""
"Todo lo que existe puede ser destruido; me niego a creer que su alma sea una "
"excepción."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:328
msgid "It is not, but you are not the one who can do that."
msgstr "No lo es, pero tú no eres quien puede hacerlo."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:332
msgid ""
"Then who is? Tell me, that I will find him or her, even if I have to extend "
"my life with necromancy to do that!"
msgstr ""
"Entonces ¿quién? Dímelo, que lo encontraré, ¡aunque tenga que alargar mi "
"vida con nigromancia!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:337
msgid ""
"I see you will not give up... Very well, I will tell you the full story of "
"the High Dragons' creation; this will go against my creator's orders, but if "
"that is necessary to prevent you from doing anything foolish, then I shall "
"do it."
msgstr ""
"Veo que no vas a rendirte… Está bien, te contaré toda la historia de la "
"creación de los Grandes Dragones; esto va contra las órdenes de mi creadora, "
"pero si es necesario para evitar que hagas alguna locura, lo haré."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:341
msgid "Please, tell me..."
msgstr "Por favor, cuéntame…"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:346
msgid ""
"This, Myra, is not the only world that exists in our universe. As you well "
"know, being the daughter of Maat. There are plenty of others, each with its "
"own creatures and ecologies, all connected by the Weave of Worlds. And we "
"owe all this universe to ancient beings of supreme might, beings whose very "
"essence gave origin to everything that exists: life, time, magic, matter "
"itself. You know them as the Ancient Ones and as Gods, but I knew them as "
"the Avatars."
msgstr ""
"Este, Myra, no es el único mundo que existe en nuestro universo. Como bien "
"sabes, siendo hija de Maat. Hay muchos otros, cada uno con sus propias "
"criaturas y ecologías, todos conectados por el Tejido de los Mundos. Y a "
"todos estos universos se los debemos a seres antiguos de poder supremo, "
"seres cuya misma esencia dio origen a todo lo que existe: la vida, el "
"tiempo, la magia, la materia misma. Los conocéis como los Antiguos y como "
"Dioses, pero yo los conocí como los Avatares."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:351
msgid ""
"One of these Avatars was known as Demere, and from her very being Life "
"sprung. She chose this planet as her abode, due to it having the gentlest, "
"most balanced weather; consequently, of all planets this one became the "
"fullest of life. And she loved it and all its beings - her children - "
"equally; when the dragons rampaged across this planet, instead of destroying "
"them, she gave me my powers, hoping that I would be able to pacify and lead "
"them. As you well know, I ended nearly killing them all myself, and so she "
"created Agniballi to counter my own rampage. Having been empowered by the "
"Avatar of Life herself, we were beings of great might."
msgstr ""
"Uno de esos Avatares se llamaba Demere, y de su mismo ser brotó la Vida. "
"Eligió este planeta como su morada por tener el clima más suave y "
"equilibrado; por eso, de todos los planetas, este se convirtió en el más "
"lleno de vida. Y lo amaba a él y a todos sus seres —sus hijos— por igual; "
"cuando los dragones arrasaron este planeta, en vez de destruirlos, me otorgó "
"mis poderes esperando que pudiera pacificarlos y guiarlos. Como bien sabes, "
"yo mismo estuve a punto de matarlos a todos, y entonces ella creó a "
"Agniballi para contrarrestar mi propio descontrol. Al haber sido empoderados "
"por el Avatar de la Vida en persona, éramos seres de gran poder."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:356
msgid ""
"The three of us watched over Irdya for a long time. One day, however, Demere "
"sensed that her days were coming to an end. She told both me and Agniballi "
"about that, explaining that, though her self would vanish, her essence - the "
"life energy that impregnates every living being - would continue to exist. "
"She then asked both me and Agniballi to watch over this world and keep its "
"balance."
msgstr ""
"Los tres vigilamos Irdya durante mucho tiempo. Un día, sin embargo, Demere "
"sintió que sus días llegaban a su fin. Nos lo contó a Agniballi y a mí, "
"explicando que, aunque su ser desaparecería, su esencia —la energía vital "
"que impregna a todo ser vivo— seguiría existiendo. Luego nos pidió a ambos "
"que veláramos por este mundo y mantuviéramos su equilibrio."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:361
msgid ""
"It was then that another Avatar called Ananke decided to intervene. Hers was "
"the essence of Will, the mightiest force that exists, which can alter the "
"course of destiny in unpredictable ways. Ananke loved Demere, and so she too "
"decided to do something for her beloved world. She did not believe we would "
"be good protectors of Irdya, for we had inherited Demere's turbulent spirit, "
"and so Ananke herself created anorther dragon, one with a spirit of pure "
"harmony, who would serve as mediator in case either I or Agniballi went out "
"of control. This dragon, as you well know, was Svarballi, whom Ananke made "
"nearly as strong as an actual Avatar."
msgstr ""
"Fue entonces cuando otro Avatar llamado Ananke decidió intervenir. El suyo "
"era la esencia de la Voluntad, la fuerza más poderosa que existe, capaz de "
"alterar el curso del destino de formas impredecibles. Ananke amaba a Demere "
"y también decidió hacer algo por su amado mundo. No creía que fuéramos "
"buenos protectores de Irdya, pues habíamos heredado el espíritu turbulento "
"de Demere, así que Ananke creó ella misma otro dragón, uno con un espíritu "
"de pura armonía, que serviría de mediador en caso de que yo o Agniballi "
"perdiéramos el control. Ese dragón, como bien saben, fue Svarballi, a quien "
"Ananke hizo casi tan fuerte como un verdadero Avatar."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:366
msgid ""
"Furthermore, some of Ananke's own servants, powerful beings themselves, "
"decided to come to Irdya and help watch over it, as a demonstration of their "
"love for Demere, who had populated the universe. They originated the "
"Celestials. The rest of the story you can guess already: Ananke's self "
"vanished as well, the High Dragons battled each other, and ironically, the "
"one supposed to be the best of the three was the one that nearly destroyed "
"Irdya... I do not know what has happened up in the heavens, but I have not "
"heard from any other Avatar ever again, and this world was left to its "
"inhabitants - which I'm certain to have been Demere's intention all along..."
msgstr ""
"Además, algunos de los propios sirvientes de Ananke, poderosos seres por "
"derecho propio, decidieron venir a Irdya y ayudar a vigilarlo, como muestra "
"de su amor por Demere, que había poblado el universo. Ellos dieron origen a "
"los Celestiales. El resto de la historia ya lo puedes imaginar: el ser de "
"Ananke también desapareció, los Grandes Dragones se enfrentaron entre sí, y "
"paradójicamente, el que se suponía que era el mejor de los tres fue quien "
"casi destruyó Irdya… No sé qué ha pasado allá arriba en los cielos, pero "
"nunca volví a saber de ningún otro Avatar, y este mundo quedó en manos de "
"sus habitantes —lo cual estoy seguro fue la intención de Demere desde el "
"principio…"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:371
msgid ""
"Do you understand now why you cannot destroy Svarballi? Agniballi and I may "
"have been able to defeat him by drawing upon the energy we know as the "
"spirits of Nature; Maat may have repeated the feat by channelling the sheer "
"might of the Worlds' Weave; but to completely destroy the god-like Svarballi "
"it would take a god, or a heiress to one's might - and we do not have any on "
"this planet, not anymore."
msgstr ""
"¿Entiendes ahora por qué no puedes destruir a Svarballi? Agniballi y yo "
"pudimos derrotarlo usando la energía que conocemos como los espíritus de la "
"Naturaleza; Maat pudo repetir la hazaña canalizando el puro poder del Tejido "
"de los Mundos; pero para destruir completamente al divino Svarballi haría "
"falta un dios, o una heredera de su poder… y ya no tenemos ninguno en este "
"planeta."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:380
msgid ""
"(in despair) So... so what would you have me do? Even if I defeat Grigorius, "
"there'll be others that may capture the Soul and use it for evil deeds! I am "
"not immortal, Nitiballi, I won't always be here to keep it from falling into "
"wrong hands..."
msgstr ""
"(desesperada) Entonces… entonces ¿qué quieres que haga? ¡Aunque derrote a "
"Grigorius, habrá otros que puedan capturar el Alma y usarla para fines "
"malvados! No soy inmortal, Nitiballi, ¡no estaré siempre aquí para evitar "
"que caiga en malas manos…!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:385
msgid ""
"Every era has a hero, or a heroine. You and Maat were the heroines of this "
"age, as Agniballi and I were the heroes of ours, as An-Usrukhar, First of "
"Mages, was the hero of his... As long as there is life, as long as there is "
"a heart that seeks justice, and as long as there is love, there will be "
"heroes pledging their own lives in defence of those who cannot defend "
"themselves."
msgstr ""
"Cada era tiene su héroe, o su heroína. Tú y Maat fuisteis las heroínas de "
"esta era, como Agniballi y yo fuimos los héroes de la nuestra, como An-"
"Usrukhar, Primero de los Magos, fue el héroe de la suya… Mientras haya vida, "
"mientras haya un corazón que busque justicia y mientras exista el amor, "
"habrá héroes que ofrezcan sus vidas en defensa de quienes no pueden "
"defenderse."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/34_Last_Revelations.cfg:390
msgid ""
"Myra of Hiera'Shirsha, I have told these things because I do not want you to "
"forfeit your life in vain, but I will not object to you trying to recover "
"that gem. Rather, I say we must not tarry here any longer; the enemy has the "
"Sky Soul in his possession, and we must recover it before he unleashes its "
"powers once again upon Irdya!"
msgstr ""
"Myra de Hiera’Shirsha, te he contado estas cosas porque no quiero que "
"pierdas tu vida en vano, pero no me opondré a que intentes recuperar esa "
"gema. Más bien digo que no debemos demorarnos más aquí; el enemigo tiene el "
"Alma del Cielo en su poder, ¡y debemos recuperarla antes de que vuelva a "
"desatar sus poderes sobre Irdya!"

#. [scenario], id=35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:4
msgid "Wrath of the Heavens"
msgstr "Ira de los Cielos"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:23
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:313
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:444
msgid "Wait for Grigorius to rise"
msgstr "Esperar a que Grigorius se alce"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:154
msgid ""
"Behold, the heretics have saved us the effort of hunting them down, and "
"willingly came to their doom!"
msgstr ""
"¡Mirad, los herejes nos han ahorrado la molestia de cazarlos y han venido "
"voluntariamente a su perdición!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:158
msgid "Frankly, I've just had enough of their stupid arrogance!"
msgstr "Francamente, ya estoy harta de su estúpida arrogancia."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:162
msgid "You're not the only one..."
msgstr "No eres la única…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:166
msgid ""
"Yes, we have come, but to fight your coward of a leader, since he fled from "
"the battlefield before I could reach him last time we met! Tell me, where is "
"he now? Why doesn't he leave his high throne and come fight me himself?"
msgstr ""
"Sí, hemos venido, ¡pero para luchar contra vuestro cobarde líder, que huyó "
"del campo de batalla antes de que pudiera alcanzarlo la última vez que nos "
"encontramos! ¡Decidme, dónde está ahora! ¿Por qué no abandona su alto trono "
"y viene a luchar conmigo él mismo?"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:170
msgid ""
"Lord Grigorius is busy with more concerning matters, heretic, and has "
"commissioned us to wave thee aside!"
msgstr ""
"Lord Grigorius está ocupado con asuntos más importantes, hereje, y nos ha "
"encomendado apartaros del camino."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:174
msgid ""
"Seems like he's chosen you as fodder, to wear us out... I just wonder, has "
"he told you what he has done with the other Lords?"
msgstr ""
"Parece que os ha elegido como carne de cañón, para desgastarnos… Solo me "
"pregunto, ¿os ha contado qué ha hecho con los otros Señores?"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:178
msgid ""
"Be thou silent, o viper! Lord Grigorius has told us already of how your vile "
"arts have contaminated our dear Lords! Even Lord Grigorius himself believes "
"that, weren't he so wise and experienced, he would have fallen prey to thee "
"as well!"
msgstr ""
"¡Cállate, víbora! Lord Grigorius ya nos ha contado cómo tus viles artes han "
"contaminado a nuestros queridos Señores. ¡Incluso el propio lord Grigorius "
"cree que, de no ser tan sabio y experimentado, también habría caído presa de "
"ti!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:182
msgid ""
"I see there is really no arguing with you... Very well, if you refuse to "
"listen to the language of reason, then I shall use the language of steel!"
msgstr ""
"Ya veo que no hay forma de razonar con vosotros… Está bien, si os negáis a "
"escuchar el lenguaje de la razón, ¡entonces usaré el lenguaje del acero!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:186
msgid ""
"That's it, my friend! Now, let's begin this fight at once, that my arm is "
"itching to let my axe fall on these bird bastards!"
msgstr ""
"¡Eso es, amiga mía! ¡Empecemos esta pelea de una vez, que mi brazo está "
"deseando dejar caer el hacha sobre estos bastardos alados!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:190
msgid "Windsong, charge! Today we shall avenge Akashia!"
msgstr "¡Hijas del Viento, carga! ¡Hoy vengaremos a Akashia!"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:209
msgid ""
"We have been given the honour of spilling your dirty blood before all "
"others, sinners! You shall not reach the citadel's holy walls unscathed!"
msgstr ""
"¡Nos ha sido concedido el honor de derramar vuestra sucia sangre antes que "
"nadie, pecadores! ¡No llegaréis ilesos a las santas murallas de la ciudadela!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:218
msgid "My eyes...! Is it normal for the sun to shine so brightly?"
msgstr "¡Mis ojos…! ¿Es normal que el sol brille tan fuerte?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:222
msgid "I'm afraid it isn't; this must be some Celestial trick..."
msgstr "Me temo que no; esto debe ser algún truco celestial…"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:226
msgid ""
"Ha! This is just a small demonstration of Lord Grigorius' power: the Sacred "
"Sky, which increases our power with the holy heavenly light!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ja! ¡Esto es solo una pequeña muestra del poder de lord Grigorius: el Cielo "
"Sagrado, que aumenta nuestro poder con la santa luz celestial!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:230
msgid ""
"It may last only half a day, but their power increase under this light is "
"incredible; we must choose carefully the time to attack."
msgstr ""
"Puede que solo dure medio día, pero el aumento de poder bajo esta luz es "
"increíble; debemos elegir con cuidado el momento de atacar."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:283
msgid ""
"Father! But... What are you doing here? Who is watching Maat'Kare? Who's "
"taking care of..."
msgstr ""
"¡Padre! Pero… ¿Qué haces aquí? ¿Quién vigila Maat’Kare? ¿Quién cuida de…?"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:287
msgid ""
"The rest of the city's council is administering it, the wargs are protecting "
"it, Aldrik is at the Academy, and I'm here because... Well, you didn't "
"really think I would just sit there and let you have all the glory, right? "
"I'm old, but not useless."
msgstr ""
"El resto del consejo de la ciudad lo está administrando, los huargos lo "
"protegen, Aldrik está en la Academia y yo estoy aquí porque… Bueno, no "
"pensarías que me quedaría allí sentado dejando que te lleves toda la gloria, "
"¿verdad? Soy viejo, pero no inútil."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:291
msgid "But you shouldn't..."
msgstr "Pero no deberías…"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:295
msgid ""
"Listen, who do you think you are to tell me what I should do? You may be a "
"mighty heroine, but I'm still your father, never forget that!"
msgstr ""
"Escucha, ¿quién te crees que eres para decirme lo que debo hacer? Puede que "
"seas una gran heroína, ¡pero sigo siendo tu padre, no lo olvides nunca!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:299
msgid ""
"(chuckling) Stubborn to the end... Well then, now that you have come all the "
"way here, then let's fight!"
msgstr ""
"(riendo) Terco hasta el final… Bueno, ya que has venido hasta aquí, "
"¡entonces luchemos!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:303
msgid ""
"A pity Ravyan is so far away... He's fought alongside us for so long, only "
"to miss this great battle..."
msgstr ""
"Lástima que Ravyan esté tan lejos… Ha luchado a nuestro lado tanto tiempo, "
"solo para perderse esta gran batalla…"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:307
msgid "(smiles)"
msgstr "(sonríe)"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:410
msgid "Did you miss me?"
msgstr "¿Me echabais de menos?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:414
msgid ""
"(puzzled) But... How did you know... And what is <i>she</i> doing alongside "
"you?"
msgstr "(perpleja) Pero… ¿Cómo sabías…? Y ¿qué hace <i>ella</i> contigo?"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:418
msgid ""
"Well, we were about to destroy Hagor's capital, when she appeared out of "
"nowhere, begging me to hurry to help you... I took some time to believe her, "
"but when she said Grigorius had stolen the Sky Soul, and that Akashia... "
"Well, I talked with Eranak and the dwarves, they pledged themselves to "
"finish the defeat of Hagor, and so we searched for you. Liliel was "
"invaluable then, she scouted ahead of us and eventually sighted this "
"battle..."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, estábamos a punto de destruir la capital de Hagor cuando ella "
"apareció de la nada, suplicándome que corriera a ayudarte… Me costó creerle, "
"pero cuando dijo que Grigorius había robado el Alma del Cielo y que Akashia… "
"Bueno, hablé con Eranak y los enanos, se comprometieron a terminar de "
"derrotar a Hagor, y así salimos en tu busca. Liliel fue invaluable, exploró "
"delante y finalmente divisó esta batalla…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:422
msgid ""
"(smiling) Well, seems like you have been useful yet again, Liliel... Keep "
"going like this, and we may even let you live with us."
msgstr ""
"(sonriendo) Bueno, parece que has vuelto a ser útil, Liliel… Sigue así y "
"quizá hasta te dejemos vivir con nosotros."

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:426
msgid "(smiles shyly)"
msgstr "(sonríe tímidamente)"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:430
msgid "But, will you fight against your former comrades?"
msgstr "¿Pero lucharás contra tus antiguos camaradas?"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:434
msgid ""
"I now understand fully well what Zaal said that day... It pains me to do so, "
"but, if it's to save this world from Grigorius' evil, then I yes, I will."
msgstr ""
"Ahora entiendo perfectamente lo que dijo Zaal aquel día… Me duele hacerlo, "
"pero si es para salvar este mundo del mal de Grigorius, entonces sí, lo haré."

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:438
msgid ""
"The weeds always grow next to each other... It makes perfect sense that the "
"sister of the traitor Zaal's best friend turns her blade against this "
"glorious Tower as well! But it does not matter how many reinforcements you "
"receive, heretics, you shall perish all te same!"
msgstr ""
"Las malas hierbas siempre crecen juntas... ¡Tiene todo el sentido que la "
"hermana de la mejor amiga del traidor Zaal también vuelva su espada contra "
"esta gloriosa Torre! ¡Pero no importa cuántos refuerzos reciban, herejes, de "
"todos modos perecerán!"

#. [message], speaker=Liliel
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:492
msgid ""
"I receive the punishment for having been such a fool... At least I shall now "
"be reunited with my brother and Zaal..."
msgstr ""
"Recibo el castigo por haber sido tan necia… Al menos ahora me reuniré con mi "
"hermano y con Zaal…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:496
msgid ""
"Rest in peace, Liliel. You have always dedicated yourself to what you deemed "
"good, and so you didn't deserve to die like this. We shall never forget you."
msgstr ""
"Descansa en paz, Liliel. Siempre te dedicaste a lo que creías bueno, y no "
"merecías morir así. Nunca te olvidaremos."

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:534
msgid ""
"Myra of Hiera'Shirsha... I had planned on giving thee a chance to live "
"peacefully, but you truly seem eager to die..."
msgstr ""
"Myra de Hiera’Shirsha… Había planeado darte una oportunidad de vivir en paz, "
"pero parece que tienes muchas ganas de morir…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:538
msgid ""
"Did you really think I'd not destroy you for what you have done to Akashia "
"and my Windsong sisters? Did you really think I would simply allow "
"Svarballi's Soul to remain in your corrupted hands?"
msgstr ""
"¿De verdad creías que no te destruiría por lo que le hiciste a Akashia y a "
"mis hermanas Hijas del Viento? ¿De verdad pensabas que simplemente "
"permitiría que el Alma de Svarballi permaneciera en tus manos corrompidas?"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:542
msgid ""
"(smirking) Actually, I did not... In fact, I was expecting - no, I desired "
"you to come, so that I might smite you myself and put a definitive end to "
"your heresy!"
msgstr ""
"(sonriendo con sorna) En realidad, no… De hecho, esperaba —no, deseaba— que "
"vinieras, para poder aniquilarte yo mismo y poner fin definitivo a tu "
"herejía."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:546
msgid ""
"You call us heretics and sinners, but you are the real monster! Would that "
"we had given heed to Zaal, who first saw your true face, before!"
msgstr ""
"¡Nosotros herejes y pecadores, pero el verdadero monstruo eres tú! ¡Ojalá "
"hubiéramos escuchado a Zaal, que fue el primero en ver tu verdadero rostro!"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:550
msgid ""
"Zaal was an idealistic fool; he believed this world could be fixed with "
"passive vigilance and pacifism, but the truth is, this world can only be "
"fixed by a strong, righteous hand! <i>Mine</i> is the hand fated to bring "
"peace and harmony to Irdya, and now there are no more foolish High Dragons "
"to stop me!"
msgstr ""
"Zaal era un iluso idealista; creía que este mundo podía arreglarse con "
"vigilancia pasiva y pacifismo, ¡pero la verdad es que este mundo solo puede "
"arreglarse con una mano fuerte y justa! <i>La mía</i> es la mano destinada a "
"traer paz y armonía a Irdya, ¡y ahora ya no hay dragones supremos estúpidos "
"que me detengan!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:554
msgid ""
"You call them foolish, but you seem unaware of how similar to Svarballi you "
"sound..."
msgstr ""
"Los llamas estúpidos, pero parece que no te das cuenta de lo parecido que "
"suenas a Svarballi…"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:558
msgid ""
"(in rage) Enough with useless words! Onwards, soldiers of Light! Only one "
"obstacle stands between us and a better world, and it stands right before us!"
msgstr ""
"(furioso) ¡Basta de palabras inútiles! ¡Adelante, soldados de la Luz! ¡Solo "
"un obstáculo nos separa de un mundo mejor, y está justo delante de nosotros!"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:564
msgid "Put an end to Grigorius' insanity"
msgstr "Poner fin a la locura de Grigorius"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:611
msgid ""
"Lowly spawn of darkness, you are no match for the highest of Celestials!"
msgstr ""
"¡Baja prole de las tinieblas, no sois rival para el más alto de los "
"Celestiales!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:625
msgid "I'm here, Grigorius! Now, FIGHT ME!"
msgstr "¡Estoy aquí, Grigorius! ¡Ahora, PELEA CONMIGO!"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:636
msgid "NO!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡NO!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:640
msgid "This is your end, Grigorius!"
msgstr "¡Este es tu fin, Grigorius!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:651
msgid "Yes! We are victorious!"
msgstr "¡Sí! ¡Hemos vencido!"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:655
msgid "No... No!!! How... How can our Lord be defeated by heretics?!"
msgstr ""
"¡No… No!!! ¡¿Cómo… cómo puede nuestro Señor ser derrotado por herejes?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:659
msgid ""
"Celestials! You have done us great harm, but I, in the name of the humans of "
"Netjer-Ta, offer you the chance to..."
msgstr ""
"¡Celestiales! Nos habéis hecho mucho daño, pero yo, en nombre de los humanos "
"de Netjer-Ta, os ofrezco la oportunidad de…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:668
msgid "Um, the chance to...?"
msgstr "Eh, la oportunidad de…?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:672
msgid "Myra, is everything all right?"
msgstr "¿Myra, estás bien?"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:676
msgid ""
"Myra did not answer; she had suddenly sensed a faint, but terrifying spark "
"of energy coming from her back, where the formerly mighty Celestial lord "
"still agonized... Then, she understood what was about to happen, and ran "
"towards Grigorius to stop him, but it was too late: just as he incrusted the "
"Soul into his breastplate, she was thrown back by a powerful explosion at "
"the same time a spine-chilling roar echoed in the Silent Desert, and as "
"maelstroms of an overwhelmingly evil energy surged from where the Apotheosis "
"Seraphin had made his last stand..."
msgstr ""
"Myra no respondió; de repente había sentido una chispa de energía débil pero "
"aterradora que venía de su espalda, donde el antes poderoso señor Celestial "
"aún agonizaba… Entonces comprendió lo que iba a pasar y corrió hacia "
"Grigorius para detenerlo, pero ya era tarde: justo cuando él incrustó el "
"Alma en su coraza, ella fue arrojada hacia atrás por una potente explosión "
"al mismo tiempo que un rugido escalofriante resonó en el Desierto "
"Silencioso, y remolinos de una energía abrumadoramente maligna surgieron del "
"lugar donde el Serafín de la Apoteosis había hecho su última resistencia…"

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:684
msgid "W-what is happening?!"
msgstr "¡¿Q-qué está pasando?!"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:688
msgid "This... Oh, no, he didn't do this..."
msgstr "Esto… ¡Oh, no, no lo ha hecho…!"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:692
msgid "Did what?"
msgstr "¿Hizo qué?"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:696
msgid ""
"Grigorius is... channelling the Soul's full power... Not unleashing it, like "
"Myra has once done, but... absorbing it..."
msgstr ""
"Grigorius está… canalizando todo el poder del Alma… No liberándolo, como "
"hizo Myra una vez, sino… absorbiéndolo…"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:715
msgid "What..."
msgstr "Qué…"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:719
msgid "...the hell..."
msgstr "…demonios…"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:723
msgid "...is that thing?"
msgstr "…es esa cosa?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:727
msgid ""
"Grigorius, you fool! Can't you see you will destroy yourself by absorbing "
"the Soul's power?"
msgstr ""
"¡Grigorius, necio! ¡¿No ves que te destruirás a ti mismo absorbiendo el "
"poder del Alma?!"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:731
msgid "Grigorius... is no more..."
msgstr "Grigorius… ya no existe…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:735
msgid "What? You..."
msgstr "¿Qué? Tú…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:744
msgid "No... No, this... This I refuse to..."
msgstr "No… No, esto… ¡Esto me niego a…!"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:748
msgid ""
"Come now, we have been close to each other long enough for you to recognize "
"my aura on the spot!"
msgstr ""
"¡Vamos, hemos estado lo bastante cerca el uno del otro como para que "
"reconozcas mi aura al instante!"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:757
msgid ""
"(shouting) Heed me, miserable wretches, Grigorius the Fool is no more! I am "
"Svarballi, the Chosen of Ananke, Deliverer of this world!"
msgstr ""
"(gritando) ¡Escuchadme, miserables gusanos, Grigorius el Necio ya no existe! "
"¡Yo soy Svarballi, el Gran Dragón del Cielo!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:761
msgid ""
"Everyone, from dwarves to humans to Celestials, stood still, too shocked by "
"that revelation to speak anything. The Celestials stared at the transformed "
"body of their former leader in utter disbelief; those who had seen Svarballi "
"before at Garet-Desh stood appalled and terrified, but Myra, who remained on "
"the ground after being thrown away by the explosion, to her own surprise "
"felt a burning, growing rage inside herself. There stood the monster who had "
"caused the Last War, the deaths of Veela and Maat, the destruction of "
"Hiera'Shirsha and Akashia's downfall; there stood the root of all the "
"suffering she and so many others had endured for years..."
msgstr ""
"Todos, desde enanos hasta humanos y celestiales, se quedaron inmóviles, "
"demasiado impactados por esa revelación para decir nada. Los celestiales "
"miraban incrédulos el cuerpo transformado de su antiguo líder; quienes "
"habían visto a Svarballi antes en Garet-Desh se quedaron horrorizados y "
"aterrorizados, pero Myra, que seguía en el suelo tras ser arrojada por la "
"explosión, para su propia sorpresa sintió una rabia ardiente y creciente "
"dentro de sí. Allí estaba el monstruo que había causado la Última Guerra, "
"las muertes de Veela y Maat, la destrucción de Hiera’Shirsha y la caída de "
"Akashia; allí estaba la raíz de todo el sufrimiento que ella y tantos otros "
"habían soportado durante años…"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:765
msgid ""
"It is ironic that this fool has tried to master my soul, and that it was I "
"who mastered his... But I should thank him; after all, were it not for his "
"foolishness, I would still be trapped within that cursed gem..."
msgstr ""
"Es irónico que este necio haya intentado dominar mi alma y que haya sido yo "
"quien lo dominó a él… Pero debería agradecerle; al fin y al cabo, de no ser "
"por su necedad, aún estaría atrapado dentro de esa gema maldita…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:769
msgid ""
"(getting to her feet) Jevyan, father, Ravyan, gather all our soldiers and "
"flee this place immediately! You stand no chance against him!"
msgstr ""
"(poniéndose en pie) ¡Jevyan, padre, Ravyan, reunid a todos nuestros soldados "
"y huid de este lugar inmediatamente! ¡No tenéis ninguna posibilidad contra "
"él!"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:773
msgid ""
"...a gem created by the mother of this young girl that stands before me. I "
"acknowledge the High Ascendant caught me off guard, but by Ananke, I will "
"not let that happen again..."
msgstr ""
"…una gema creada por la madre de esta joven que está ante mí. Reconozco que "
"la Gran Ascendente me pilló desprevenido, ¡pero por Ananke, no dejaré que "
"vuelva a pasar…!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:777
msgid ""
"You were created to protect the world of your creator's beloved, Svarballi; "
"will you go against his will and destroy it?"
msgstr ""
"Fuiste creado para proteger el mundo del amado de tu creadora, Svarballi; "
"¿vas a ir contra su voluntad y destruirlo?"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:781
msgid ""
"Ananke's will means nothing now, she no longer exists in this universe, and "
"the same goes for all the other Avatars! This world has been abandoned, Myra "
"of Hiera'Shirsha, and all its dwellers have been left to suffer! I have "
"tried to put an end to their senseless existence, but fools have hindered me "
"- but no longer! This time, there is no more Maat, no more Nitiballi..."
msgstr ""
"¡La voluntad de Ananke ya no significa nada, ella ya no existe en este "
"universo, y lo mismo ocurre con los demás Avatares! ¡Este mundo ha sido "
"abandonado, Myra de Hiera’Shirsha, y todos sus habitantes han quedado "
"abandonados al sufrimiento! Intenté poner fin a su existencia sin sentido, "
"pero necios me lo impidieron… ¡pero ya no! ¡Esta vez no hay más Maat, no hay "
"más Nitiballi…!"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:790
msgid ""
"No, I am mistaken... Nitiballi still exists, now I can sense his energy "
"coming from within you... Then I shall have a chance to exact revenge on "
"both Nitiballi and Maat at once... So..."
msgstr ""
"No, me equivoco… Nitiballi aún existe, ahora siento su energía viniendo de "
"dentro de ti… Entonces tendré la oportunidad de vengarme de Nitiballi y Maat "
"al mismo tiempo… Así que…"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:803
msgid "...let the end BEGIN!"
msgstr "…¡QUE COMIENCE EL FIN!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:822
msgid "Jevyan, friends, you must leave this place immediately!"
msgstr "¡Jevyan, amigos, debéis abandonar este lugar inmediatamente!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:826
msgid "What?! No way I'm leaving you to fight this beast alone!"
msgstr "¡¿Qué?! ¡De ninguna manera te dejo luchar contra esta bestia sola!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:830
msgid "I SAID LEAVE THIS PLACE!"
msgstr "¡¡¡HE DICHO QUE OS VAYÁIS!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:839
msgid ""
"Please, friends, do not make me see more of you dying, I... I have had "
"enough of that..."
msgstr ""
"Por favor, amigos, no me hagáis ver morir a más de vosotros, yo… ya he "
"tenido bastante de eso…"

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:848
msgid "She... She is right, Jevyan, there is nothing we can do now.."
msgstr "Ella… Tiene razón, Jevyan, ahora no podemos hacer nada…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:852
msgid "(crying) Myra..."
msgstr "(llorando) Myra…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:856
msgid ""
"I-I am happy that I have met you all... Please, take care of Maat'Kare for "
"me; do not let all our sacrifices be in vain..."
msgstr ""
"E-estoy feliz de haberos conocido a todos… Por favor, cuidad de Maat’Kare "
"por mí; no dejéis que todos nuestros sacrificios hayan sido en vano…"

#. [message]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:951
msgid ""
"The heretics are fleeing, but we cannot abandon our dear tower to this "
"monster! Come, soldiers of Light, let's save our dear Lord from this "
"corrupting demon!"
msgstr ""
"¡Los herejes huyen, pero no podemos abandonar nuestra querida torre a este "
"monstruo! ¡Venid, soldados de la Luz, salvemos a nuestro querido Señor de "
"este demonio corruptor!"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:955
msgid "Pathetic little beings, when will you learn to DISAPPEAR!!!"
msgstr "¡Patéticos seres diminutos, cuándo aprenderéis a ¡DESAPARECER!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:974
msgid "Now it is better, only the two of us, Myra..."
msgstr "Ahora está mejor, solo tú y yo, Myra…"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:979
msgid "Myra, you know what to do."
msgstr "Myra, sabes qué hacer."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:983
msgid "I have known that since the Fountain of Life..."
msgstr "Lo sé desde la Fuente de la Vida…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:992
msgid ""
"*Spirits of Nature, before me stands the Destroyer, the enemy of all life; "
"please, grant me the power to stop him, use my body as your vessel, let your "
"power flow through me!*"
msgstr ""
"*Espíritus de la Naturaleza, ante mí está el Destructor, el enemigo de toda "
"vida; concededme el poder para detenerlo, usad mi cuerpo como vuestro "
"recipiente, ¡dejad que vuestro poder fluya a través de mí!*"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1030
msgid ""
"Interesting... As expected, you can channel Nature's power as well as "
"Nitiballi himself... (smirking) Not that it will change the outcome of this "
"battle, though..."
msgstr ""
"Interesante… Como era de esperar, puedes canalizar el poder de la Naturaleza "
"tan bien como el propio Nitiballi… (sonriendo con sorna) Aunque eso no "
"cambiará el resultado de esta batalla…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1034
msgid "We'll see about that, Sky Dragon...!"
msgstr "¡Ya veremos eso, Dragón del Cielo…!"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1045
msgid "Defeat the awakened Svarballi, even if that costs your life"
msgstr "Derrotar al Svarballi despertado, aunque te cueste la vida"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1075
msgid "Aaargh!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡Aaargh!!!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1080
msgid "Myra, please resist!"
msgstr "¡Myra, por favor resiste!"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1084
msgid ""
"I have warned you, I would not commit the same mistakes again! Do you see "
"now how much more powerful I am? Do you see now that there is no hope for "
"your victory?"
msgstr ""
"¡Te lo advertí, no cometeré los mismos errores otra vez! ¿Ves ahora lo mucho "
"más poderoso que soy? ¿Ves ahora que no hay esperanza para tu victoria?"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1088
msgid "No, Svarballi..."
msgstr "No, Svarballi…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1092
msgid "As long as there is life..."
msgstr "Mientras haya vida…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1096
msgid "...as long as there is love and a heart that seeks justice..."
msgstr "…mientras haya amor y un corazón que busque justicia…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1100
msgid "...there is hope."
msgstr "…hay esperanza."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1115
msgid "*Do not lecture me, you've done that once too...*"
msgstr "*No me des lecciones, ya lo hiciste una vez…*"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1152
msgid ""
"Stubborn wretch, why do you insist on living this miserable existence? When "
"will learn to just give up and DIE?!"
msgstr ""
"¡Obstinada desgraciada, por qué insistes en vivir esta miserable existencia? "
"¿Cuándo aprenderás a rendirte y MORIR?!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1156
msgid "Never. Now, let's end this, Svarballi!"
msgstr "Nunca. ¡Ahora, acabemos con esto, Svarballi!"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1162
msgid "Put an end to Svarballi's menace"
msgstr "Poner fin a la amenaza de Svarballi"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1187
msgid ""
"You helpless fool, you are killing yourself, and for what? This is far from "
"being enough to kill me!"
msgstr ""
"¡Necia indefensa, te estás matando a ti misma, y para qué? ¡Esto está muy "
"lejos de ser suficiente para matarme!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1191
msgid ""
"I can't... kill you... but I can... keep you locked... until the one... who "
"can do that... comes..."
msgstr ""
"No puedo… matarte… pero puedo… mantenerte encerrado… hasta que llegue… el "
"que… pueda hacerlo…"

#. [message], speaker=Corrupted Grigorius
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1195
msgid ""
"You may have managed to lock me again, but know that Grigorius was not the "
"last fool who will find and unleash my soul! And, when this happens again, "
"you will not be here to stop me!"
msgstr ""
"Puede que hayas logrado encerrarme de nuevo, ¡pero sabe que Grigorius no fue "
"el último necio que encontrará y liberará mi alma! ¡Y cuando vuelva a pasar, "
"tú no estarás aquí para detenerme!"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1199
msgid "I... won't... but... every... era... has... its... heroes..."
msgstr "Yo… no estaré… pero… cada… era… tiene… sus… héroes…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1203
msgid "*...right, Nitiballi?*"
msgstr "*…¿verdad, Nitiballi?*"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1208
msgid ""
"(glad) I knew I was right in choosing you, my child. I am so proud of you."
msgstr ""
"(contento) Sabía que no me equivocaba al elegirte, hija mía. Estoy tan "
"orgulloso de ti."

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1212
msgid "*As I am for having been with you, Water Dragon*"
msgstr "*Como yo lo estoy de haber estado contigo, Dragón del Agua*"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1217
msgid ""
"You have fought hard and for a long time; you have bled and suffered, and "
"faced all kinds of perils; but you have overcome them all to save your "
"people. Now, Myra of Hiera'Shirsha, let us rest in peace; we both deserve "
"it..."
msgstr ""
"Has luchado duro y durante mucho tiempo; has sangrado y sufrido, y has "
"afrontado todo tipo de peligros; pero los has superado todos para salvar a "
"tu pueblo. Ahora, Myra de Hiera’Shirsha, descansemos en paz; ambos lo "
"merecemos…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1296
msgid "T have fought so much, only to fall at the end..."
msgstr "He luchado tanto, solo para caer al final…"

#. [message], speaker=Myra
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/35_Wrath_Of_The_Heavens.cfg:1386
msgid "Father, no! Please, don't die, Aldrik needs you...!"
msgstr "¡Padre, no! ¡Por favor, no mueras, Aldrik te necesita…!"

#. [scenario], id=36_A_New_Legend_Rises
#. [scenario], id=36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises.cfg:4
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:4
msgid "A New Legend Rises"
msgstr "Nace una Nueva Leyenda"

#. [message], speaker=Dvalin
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises.cfg:133
msgid ""
"I met her as my father tasked me with escorting her through the roads of our "
"old home, but fate had it that we would fight together across ocean and "
"continents. I have met her as a young Windsong fleeing her Haven, but I have "
"parted with her as a legend. Myra, without you we might never have found "
"peace again; without you, I might never have met my love. The Aigathol owe "
"you everything, but I owe you everything and more. Rest with the ancestors, "
"my friend... You and Veela have earned it."
msgstr ""
"La conocí cuando mi padre me encargó escoltarla por los caminos de nuestro "
"antiguo hogar, pero el destino quiso que lucháramos juntos a través de "
"océanos y continentes. La conocí como una joven Hija del Viento huyendo de "
"su Refugio, pero me despedí de ella como una leyenda. Myra, sin ti quizá "
"nunca habríamos encontrado la paz de nuevo; sin ti, quizá nunca habría "
"conocido a mi amor. Los aigathol te lo debemos todo, pero yo te debo todo y "
"más. Descansa con los ancestros, amiga mía… Tú y Veela os lo habéis ganado."

#. [message], speaker=Ravyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises.cfg:137
msgid ""
"As I grew hearing tales of the deeds of Maat, so will our children and their "
"children grow hearing tales of Myra's valour. You have led us to a new home, "
"but more than that, you taught us so much. Wherever your soul may be, my "
"friend, watch us closely, for we shall continue your work and build a world "
"you will be proud of."
msgstr ""
"Como yo crecí escuchando historias de las hazañas de Maat, así crecerán "
"nuestros hijos y los hijos de nuestros hijos escuchando historias del valor "
"de Myra. Nos guiaste a un nuevo hogar, pero más que eso, nos enseñaste "
"tanto. Dondequiera que esté tu alma, amiga mía, míranos de cerca, porque "
"continuaremos tu obra y construiremos un mundo del que estarás orgullosa."

#. [message], speaker=Tarkyn
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises.cfg:141
msgid ""
"For so many years I regretted letting you and Ysara go, and for so many "
"years I dreamed of what sort of person you had grown up to be. I could say "
"the time we spent together was too short, daughter... but instead, I'll be "
"thankful for them, as I'm thankful to both your mothers for raising such a "
"wonderful woman... as I'm thankful the gods allowed me to be your father."
msgstr ""
"Durante tantos años me arrepentí de haber dejado marchar a ti y a Ysara, y "
"durante tantos años soñé con qué clase de persona te habrías convertido. "
"Podría decir que el tiempo que pasamos juntos fue demasiado corto, hija… "
"pero en cambio, estaré agradecido por él, como estoy agradecido a ambas "
"madres por criar a una mujer tan maravillosa… como estoy agradecido a los "
"dioses por permitirme ser tu padre."

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises.cfg:145
msgid ""
"History will remember Myra of Hiera'Shirsha as a mighty Ascendant, a valiant "
"fighter, a formidable leader; the Dragonbane, the Chosen of the Water "
"Dragon, the Wielder of the Trident of the Seas, the Foe of the Sky Dragon; "
"the heroine who united former enemies, who led Windsong, Aragwaithi and "
"Hannuks across the oceans to a new home. However, in time no one will be "
"left that will remember her as the woman she was: a loyal friend, a loving "
"mother..."
msgstr ""
"La historia recordará a Myra de Hiera’Shirsha como una poderosa Ascendente, "
"una luchadora valiente, una líder formidable; la Matadragones, la Elegida "
"del Dragón del Agua, la Portadora del Tridente de los Mares, la Enemiga del "
"Dragón del Cielo; la heroína que unió a antiguos enemigos, que guió a Hijas "
"del Viento, aragwaithi y hannuk a través de los océanos hacia un nuevo "
"hogar. Sin embargo, con el tiempo no quedará nadie que la recuerde como la "
"mujer que fue: una amiga leal y entregada, una madre amorosa, una esposa "
"cariñosa…"

#. [message], speaker=Alenya
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises.cfg:149
msgid ""
"The scrolls must not be the only keepers of our memory. Let us not forget "
"anything: the ordeal we endured, or the sacrifices we made, or the blood and "
"tears we shed. Let us not forget High Ascendant Maat, or High King Abhai, or "
"Veela the Kind, or Varthan the Brave, or Akashia the Strong; let us not "
"forget the Windsong, the Aragwaithi and the Hannuks who fought endless "
"enemies to find a safe haven where the future generations could live in "
"peace; let us not forget the leader, the heroine, the warrior and the woman, "
"Myra of Hiera'Shirsha."
msgstr ""
"Los pergaminos no deben ser los únicos guardianes de nuestra memoria. No "
"olvidemos nada: la ordalía que soportamos, ni los sacrificios que hicimos, "
"ni la sangre y las lágrimas que derramamos. No olvidemos a la Gran "
"Ascendente Maat, ni al Alto Rey Abhai, ni a Veela la Bondadosa, ni a Varthan "
"el Valiente, ni a Akashia la Fuerte; no olvidemos a las Hijas del Viento, "
"los aragwaithi y los hannuk que lucharon contra enemigos interminables para "
"encontrar un refugio seguro donde las generaciones futuras pudieran vivir en "
"paz; no olvidemos a la líder, la heroína, la guerrera y la mujer, Myra de "
"Hiera’Shirsha."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:72
msgid "It is getting dark and cold, son, let's get back to the city..."
msgstr "Se está haciendo oscuro y frío, hijo, volvamos a la ciudad…"

#. [message], speaker=Aldrik
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:76
msgid "All right."
msgstr "Está bien."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:80
msgid "See, Aldrik... How are you feeling about all this? About mom's..."
msgstr "Mira, Aldrik… ¿Cómo te sientes con todo esto? Con lo de mamá…"

#. [message], speaker=Aldrik
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:84
msgid "It's fine, dad. Mom didn't go away forever, she will return one day."
msgstr "Tranquilo, papá. Mamá no se fue para siempre, volverá un día."

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:88
msgid "Son, we have talked about this before..."
msgstr "Hijo, ya hemos hablado de esto…"

#. [message], speaker=Aldrik
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:92
msgid "But it's true, dad. Look, she's there, smiling for us!"
msgstr "Pero es verdad, papá. ¡Mira, está ahí, sonriéndonos!"

#. [message], speaker=Jevyan
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:99
msgid "(appalled) Where...? Where are you seeing her?"
msgstr "(horrorizado) ¿Dónde…? ¿Dónde la ves?"

#. [message], speaker=Aldrik
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:103
msgid "(pointing at the sea) There!"
msgstr "(señala al mar) ¡Allí!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/36_A_New_Legend_Rises_b.cfg:110
msgid ""
"<i>Just as a mother lives on long after her own death in the blood of her "
"children, Myra shall live on in her legacy: all the life that dwells on "
"Irdya.</i>"
msgstr ""
"<i>Así como una madre vive mucho después de su muerte en la sangre de sus "
"hijos, Myra vivirá en su legado: toda la vida que habita en Irdya.</i>"

#. [scenario], id=Epilogue_ASoF
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue_ASoF.cfg:4
msgid "Epilogue"
msgstr "Epílogo"

#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue_ASoF.cfg:11
msgid ""
"The Continental War did not last much longer; with Hagor dead, there was no "
"one capable of uniting the orcs under a single banner, and the orcish tribes "
"returned to their inner squabbling."
msgstr ""
"La Guerra Continental no duró mucho más; muerto Hagor, no había nadie capaz "
"de unir a los orcos bajo una sola bandera, y las tribus orcas volvieron a "
"sus disputas internas."

#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue_ASoF.cfg:15
msgid ""
"The vampires, also leaderless, were reduced to small, wandering bands for a "
"time, until a lord managed to reunite and rebuild their civilization. After "
"his death, the vampire nation was divided between his sons, and many smaller "
"fiefdoms were formed."
msgstr ""
"Los vampiros, también sin líder, quedaron reducidos a pequeñas bandas "
"errantes durante un tiempo, hasta que un lord logró reunir y reconstruir su "
"civilización. Tras su muerte, la nación vampírica se dividió entre sus hijos "
"y se formaron muchos pequeños feudos."

#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue_ASoF.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The Celestials, in spite of losing their capital and their lords, kept "
"fighting the Maat'Karians, who, aided by their dwarvish and warg allies, "
"were ultimately victorious. A few of them accepted the humans' offer of "
"amnesty, and joined them; their magical knowledge would originate a new "
"school of magic that dealt with the holy arts. The celestials who didn't "
"join the humans, by their turn, left Netjer-Ta and were never heard of again."
msgstr ""
"Los Celestiales, a pesar de perder su capital y a sus señores, siguieron "
"luchando contra los maat’karianos, que, ayudados por sus aliados enanos y "
"huargos, resultaron vencedores al final. Algunos aceptaron la oferta de "
"amnistía de los humanos y se unieron a ellos; sus conocimientos mágicos "
"darían origen a una nueva escuela de magia que trataría las artes sagradas. "
"Los celestiales que no se unieron a los humanos abandonaron Netjer-Ta y "
"nunca más se supo de ellos."

#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue_ASoF.cfg:23
msgid ""
"The Windsong, despite their massive losses, managed to recover from the "
"damages of the war, led by a new Head, one who had fought alongside Myra and "
"Maat in the Last War. Thanks to the copies owned by Maat'Kare, the gaps in "
"Hiera'Laksha's shelves - a result of the Celestial attack - were refilled. "
"The Book of the Dead remained there; and, in a special mausoleum carved into "
"one of the Bald Mountain's highest pinnacles, stood the ice coffin from "
"whence Akashia overlooked her precious Foundation, uncorrupted by death and "
"decay."
msgstr ""
"Las Hijas del Viento, a pesar de sus enormes pérdidas, lograron recuperarse "
"de los daños de la guerra, lideradas por una nueva Cabeza, una que había "
"luchado junto a Myra y Maat en la Última Guerra. Gracias a las copias que "
"poseía Maat’Kare, se rellenaron los huecos en los estantes de Hiera’Laksha —"
"resultado del ataque Celestial—. El Libro de los Muertos permaneció allí; y, "
"en un mausoleo especial tallado en uno de los picos más altos de la Montaña "
"Calva, se alzaba el ataúd de hielo desde donde Akashia velaba su preciosa "
"Fundación, incorrupta por la muerte y la descomposición."

#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue_ASoF.cfg:27
msgid ""
"In the faraway Great Continent, the Dragon War raged on for many years even "
"after the Continental War. The massive losses at Garet-Desh and Ughure, "
"however, put an end to the dragons' eastern campaign, and in the west, the "
"alliance between elves and dwarves won many victories against them. Finally, "
"a civil war between the followers of Shek'kahan and those of Khrakrahs "
"undermined the drakes' western campaign as well. Few were the dragons that "
"survived that war, and those who did went into hiding, to avoid being killed "
"by hunters; even the sons of Shek'har exiled themselves. Never again did the "
"dragons recover their old numbers, and the Dragons' Land became an empty "
"desert."
msgstr ""
"En el lejano Gran Continente, la Guerra de los Dragones continuó durante "
"muchos años incluso después de la Guerra Continental. Sin embargo, las "
"enormes pérdidas en Garet-Desh y Ughure pusieron fin a la campaña oriental "
"de los dragones, y en el oeste, la alianza entre elfos y enanos logró muchas "
"victorias contra ellos. Finalmente, una guerra civil entre los seguidores de "
"Shek’kahan y los de Khrakrahs socavó también la campaña occidental de los "
"dracos. Pocos fueron los dragones que sobrevivieron a esa guerra, y los que "
"lo hicieron se escondieron para evitar ser cazados; incluso los hijos de "
"Shek’har se exiliaron. Nunca más recuperaron los dragones sus antiguos "
"números, y la Tierra de los Dragones se convirtió en un desierto vacío."

#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue_ASoF.cfg:31
msgid ""
"As for the Sky Soul, it remained lost after the final battle at the Crystal "
"Tower; Ravyan once suggested - unofficially, since the truth about the gem "
"remained a secret between Myra's closest friends - sending an expedition to "
"recover it, but Jevyan insisted that it should be left in the abyss created "
"from that cataclysmic explosion. Later, he formed a secret group of warriors "
"with the sole objective of watching over that abyss, to prevent any "
"adventurer from entering it."
msgstr ""
"En cuanto al Alma del Cielo, quedó perdida después de la batalla final en la "
"Torre de Cristal; Ravyan sugirió una vez —extraoficialmente, pues la verdad "
"sobre la gema seguía siendo un secreto entre los amigos más cercanos de Myra"
"— enviar una expedición a recuperarla, pero Jevyan insistió en que debía "
"dejarse en el abismo creado por aquella explosión cataclísmica. Más tarde "
"formó un grupo secreto de guerreros con el único objetivo de vigilar ese "
"abismo, para impedir que ningún aventurero entrara en él."

#. [part]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue_ASoF.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Years passed, the seasons succeeded each other in their eternal cycle, and "
"Maat'Kare thrived again, supported by its new generation - amongst them "
"Aldrik, the prodigy of the Academy, who had somehow inherited his mother's "
"elemental powers; and Belendra, the half-elf, half-dwarf maiden who was "
"dubbed the Steel Princess of the Cyan Mountains. They did not live in their "
"parents' shadow for long, and authored great deeds themselves in their "
"continent and even in the new one that was discovered few years after the "
"Continental War... But that is another story. The one I have been telling, "
"the song of Myra of Hiera'Shirsha, ends here."
msgstr ""
"Los años pasaron, las estaciones se sucedieron en su ciclo eterno, y "
"Maat’Kare prosperó de nuevo, sostenida por su nueva generación —entre ellos "
"Aldrik, el prodigio de la Academia, que de alguna forma había heredado los "
"poderes elementales de su madre; y Belendra, la doncella mitad elfa mitad "
"enana a la que apodaron la Princesa de Acero de las Montañas Cian. No "
"vivieron mucho tiempo a la sombra de sus padres y escribieron ellos mismos "
"grandes hazañas en su continente e incluso en el nuevo que fue descubierto "
"pocos años después de la Guerra Continental… Pero esa es otra historia. La "
"que he estado contando, la canción de Myra de Hiera’Shirsha, termina aquí."

