msgstr "Hannuks"

#. [race], id=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:13
msgid ""
"The Hannuks are a human people who inhabits the vast steppes in the Great "
"Continent's Far East, between the Aragwaith Meadows and the Stormy Sea. They "
"were originally nomads, moving all around the steppes and the lands "
"surrounding it, but at some point in their History they began to settle down "
"on the plains after learning agriculture. Even so, they have not forgotten "
"the nomadic skills of their ancestors, and preserve them through rituals and "
"oral tradition.\n"
"\n"
"Their society is very conservative, and so their customs and beliefs change "
"little throughout the centuries. They are divided into many different clans, "
"some of them rule by their eldest, others by their strongest and most "
"cunning warrior; but all the clans are united under the authority of the "
"Great Shamans, the wisest amongst the Hannuks, who keep their ancient lore "
"and who have the monopoly over their rudimentary magical arts. These Shamans "
"sit at Ughure, the largest city of the Hannuks, and one of the largest of "
"all human settlements.\n"
"\n"
"The Hannuks are not an expansionistic nation; because of their preference "
"for horse-riding, they do not occupy irregular lands, such as forests, "
"swamps, deserts and mountains. However, they frequently leave the steppes to "
"raid neighbouring lands; and every now and then there is a Hannuk chieftain "
"who decides to further expand the frontiers of his people's lands, which "
"they often succeed."
msgstr ""
"Los hannuks son un pueblo humano que habita las vastas estepas en el Lejano "
"Oriente del Gran Continente, entre los Prados Aragwaith y el Mar "
"Tempestuoso. Originalmente eran nómadas, recorriendo las estepas y las "
"tierras circundantes, pero en algún momento de su historia comenzaron a "
"asentarse en las llanuras tras aprender la agricultura. Aun así, no han "
"olvidado las habilidades nómadas de sus antepasados y las preservan mediante "
"rituales y tradición oral.\n"
"\n"
"Su sociedad es muy conservadora, por lo que sus costumbres y creencias "
"cambian poco a lo largo de los siglos. Están divididos en numerosos clanes, "
"algunos gobernados por sus ancianos, otros por su guerrero más fuerte y "
"astuto; pero todos los clanes están unidos bajo la autoridad de los Grandes "
"Chamanes, los más sabios entre los hannuks, guardianes de su antiguo saber y "
"con el monopolio de sus rudimentarias artes mágicas. Estos chamanes residen "
"en Ughure, la mayor ciudad de los hannuks y una de las mayores asentamientos "
"humanos.\n"
"\n"
"Los hannuks no son una nación expansionista; por su preferencia por la "
"caballería, no ocupan terrenos irregulares como bosques, pantanos, desiertos "
"o montañas. Sin embargo, frecuentemente salen de las estepas para saquear "
"tierras vecinas, y de vez en cuando surge un jefe hannuk que decide expandir "
"aún más las fronteras de su pueblo, lo que a menudo consigue."

#. [race], id=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:26
msgid "race^Celestial"
msgstr "Celestial"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:27
msgid "race+female^Celestial"
msgstr "Celestial"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:28
msgid "race^Celestials"
msgstr "Celestiales"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:32
msgid ""
"The Celestials have vestigial wings that for most of them do not mature. "
"Celestials believe that light and darkness each have power, and they choose "
"as a culture to fight for the light, and to spread it through-out the world. "
"They are a militaristic society with great law and order that gives them "
"strength and unity which caries over into their style of fighting. The order "
"and unified purpose of celestial society tends to make them form larger "
"nations than the other factions giving the Celestials great military "
"strength."
msgstr ""
"Los celestiales tienen alas vestigiales que en la mayoría no llegan a "
"desarrollarse. Los celestiales creen que la luz y la oscuridad tienen poder "
"propio, y eligen como cultura luchar por la luz y difundirla por todo el "
"mundo. Son una sociedad militarista con gran ley y orden que les otorga "
"fuerza y unidad, lo que se refleja en su estilo de combate. El orden y "
"propósito unificado de la sociedad celestial tiende a hacer que formen "
"naciones más grandes que otras facciones, otorgando a los celestiales una "
"gran fuerza militar."

#. [race], id=dryad
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:39
msgid "race^Dryad"
msgstr "Dríada"

#. [race], id=dryad
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:40
msgid "race^Dryads"
msgstr "Dríadas"

#. [race], id=warg
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:54
msgid "race^Warg"
msgstr "Huargo"

#. [race], id=warg
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:55
msgid "race+female^Warg"
