#. [race], id=warg
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:60
msgid ""
"Warg are also known as wolfmen. They live in the wilds and woods in almost "
"any climate, some favor the lush jungle, others the arctic woods, others "
"alpine mountains. The warg tend to live in packs or clans, and establish "
"their hunting grounds where they tend not to like intruders. Although "
"hunters, they are for the most part peaceful, however they have a primal "
"blood-lust, that can be inspired by various things, especially if vampires "
"are involved."
msgstr ""
"Los huargos también son conocidos como hombres-lobo. Viven en zonas salvajes "
"y bosques en casi cualquier clima: algunos prefieren la selva exuberante, "
"otros los bosques árticos, otros las montañas alpinas. Los huargos suelen "
"vivir en manadas o clanes y establecen sus terrenos de caza donde no suelen "
"tolerar intrusos. Aunque son cazadores, en su mayoría son pacíficos; sin "
"embargo, tienen una sed de sangre primal que puede desencadenarse por varias "
"causas, especialmente si hay vampiros de por medio."

#. [race], id=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:259
msgid "race^Aragwaith"
msgstr "Aragwaith"

#. [race], id=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:260
msgid "race+female^Aragwaith"
msgstr "Aragwaith"

#. [race], id=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:261
msgid "race^Aragwaithi"
msgstr "Aragwaithi"

#. [race], id=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/factions.cfg:265
msgid ""
"During most of the Golden Age, the humans who inhabited the Great Continent "
"were mostly Wesnothians, divided across various territories such as the "
"Northlands, Elensefar and the kingdom of Wesnoth itself. However, there was "
"once a time of great strife during which a new race of humans started to "
"appear from nowhere. They were the 'Aragwaithi', which meant 'noble' in "
"their native language.\n"
"\n"
"It has been since then rumored that they came from the Vast Sea to settle in "
"Wesnoth. They mostly lived as mercenaries in that time, until the Fall. "
"After that, they supposedly moved to the northmost lands of the Continent, "
"were the sands could not reach, and the green could survive.\n"
"\n"
"Albeit being humans, many of their customs and racial features are "
"incredibly different to the standards, to the point it puts them close to "
"elves in terms of their dexterity with bows. Their wisemen have a mastery of "
"magic not to be underestimated in the battlefield, for it has surprised and "
"overseded the best magi often."
msgstr ""
"Durante la mayor parte de la Edad Dorada, los humanos que habitaban el Gran "
"Continente eran principalmente wesnothianos, divididos en varios territorios "
"como las Tierras del Norte, Elensefar y el propio reino de Wesnoth. Sin "
"embargo, hubo una época de gran conflicto durante la cual comenzó a aparecer "
"de la nada una nueva raza humana. Eran los «aragwaithi», que en su lengua "
"nativa significaba «nobles».\n"
"\n"
"Desde entonces se rumorea que llegaron del Mar Infinito para asentarse en "
"Wesnoth. En aquella época vivían principalmente como mercenarios, hasta la "
"Caída. Después de eso, supuestamente se trasladaron a las tierras más "
"septentrionales del Continente, donde las arenas no podían llegar y el verde "
"podía sobrevivir.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque son humanos, muchas de sus costumbres y características raciales son "
"increíblemente diferentes a las habituales, hasta el punto de acercarlos a "
"los elfos en destreza con el arco. Sus sabios dominan una magia que no debe "
"subestimarse en el campo de batalla, pues a menudo ha sorprendido y superado "
"a los mejores magos."

#. [unit_type], id=High Seraph, race=celestial, gender=male
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Ascended_Seraphin.cfg:5
msgid "Apotheosis Seraph"
msgstr "Serafín de Apoteosis"

#. [unit_type], id=High Seraph, race=celestial, gender=male
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Ascended_Seraphin.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Some Seraphs manage to awaken their full inner power, stemmed from the "
"heavenly blood that runs in their veins, and thus become creatures of "
"amazing might. Although no one has ever seen the beings from which the "
"Celestials descend, gazing upon an Apotheosis Seraph offers the observer a "
"glimpse of their power and glory."
msgstr ""
"Algunos serafines logran despertar todo su poder interior, proveniente de la "
"sangre celestial que corre por sus venas, convirtiéndose así en criaturas de "
"increíble fuerza. Aunque nadie ha visto jamás a los seres de los que "
"descienden los celestiales, contemplar a un Serafín de Apoteosis ofrece al "
"observador un atisbo de su poder y gloria."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Ascended_Seraphin.cfg:40
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Ascended_Seraphin.cfg:52
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Corrupted_Seraphin.cfg:43
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Corrupted_Seraphin.cfg:55
msgid "Thronos Sword"
msgstr "Espada del Trono"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Ascended_Seraphin.cfg:64
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Corrupted_Seraphin.cfg:67
msgid "Heaven's Justice"
msgstr "Vislumbre Celestial"

#. [unit_type], id=Corrupted Seraph, race=celestial, gender=male
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Corrupted_Seraphin.cfg:5
msgid "Corrupted Seraph"
msgstr "Serafín Corrompido"

#. [unit_type], id=Corrupted Seraph, race=celestial, gender=male
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/Corrupted_Seraphin.cfg:20
msgid ""
"There is no data on this monstrosity, this is the first time anyone "
"witnesses it."
msgstr ""
"No existen datos sobre esta monstruosidad, es la primera vez que alguien la "
"presencia."

#. [unit_type], id=Celestial Crusader, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a1_Crusader.cfg:5
msgid "Crusader"
msgstr "Cruzado"

#. [unit_type], id=Celestial Crusader, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a1_Crusader.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Crusaders undergo rigorous martial training as well as rudimentary medicinal "
"training to help their injured allies on the field of battle. Crusaders' "
"swords are infused with the arcane energy of the Light Spirits - a tradition "
"that started during the Great Crusade against the vampires."
msgstr ""
"Los cruzados pasan por un riguroso entrenamiento marcial y también por un "
"entrenamiento médico básico para ayudar a sus aliados heridos en el campo de "
"batalla. Las espadas de los cruzados están imbuidas con la energía arcana de "
"los espíritus de luz, una tradición que comenzó durante la Gran Cruzada "
"contra los vampiros."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a1_Crusader.cfg:32
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Divine_Knight.cfg:31
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Quester.cfg:37
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a3_Divine_Champion.cfg:32
msgid "blessed sword"
msgstr "espada bendita"

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a1_Crusader.cfg:41
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Divine_Knight.cfg:40
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Quester.cfg:46
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a3_Divine_Champion.cfg:41
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d1_Messenger.cfg:34
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d2_Claimant.cfg:34
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d3_Herald.cfg:35
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/wargs/c2_Warrior_Warg.cfg:23
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/wargs/c3_Pack_Leader.cfg:27
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/wargs/c4_Garou.cfg:28
msgid "Sword"
msgstr "Espada"

#. [unit_type], id=Divine Knight, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Divine_Knight.cfg:5
msgid "Divine Knight"
msgstr "Caballero Divino"

#. [unit_type], id=Divine Knight, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Divine_Knight.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A crusader who survives many fierce battles is granted the honor of "
"knighthood. At this time the knight receives a ceremonial mace he must carry "
"at all times."
msgstr ""
"Un cruzado que sobrevive a muchas batallas encarnizadas recibe el honor de "
"ser nombrado caballero. En ese momento el caballero recibe una maza "
"ceremonial que debe llevar siempre consigo."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Divine_Knight.cfg:49
msgid "heavy mace"
msgstr "maza pesada"

#. [unit_type], id=Protector, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Protector.cfg:5
msgid "Protector"
msgstr "Protector"

#. [unit_type], id=Protector, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Protector.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Protector's swords have been magically enchanted with the power of Fire by "
"Celestial Wizards. Protectors also carry a large shield which they use to "
"bash and Slow their opponents."
msgstr ""
"Las espadas de los protectores han sido encantadas mágicamente con el poder "
"del fuego por magos celestiales. Los protectores también llevan un gran "
"escudo que usan para golpear y ralentizar a sus oponentes."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Protector.cfg:31
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a3_Holy_Sentinel.cfg:32
msgid "enchanted sword"
msgstr "espada encantada"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Protector.cfg:40
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a3_Holy_Sentinel.cfg:41
msgid "shield bash"
msgstr "golpe de escudo"

#. [unit_type], id=Quester, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Quester.cfg:5
msgid "Quester"
msgstr "Buscador"

#. [unit_type], id=Quester, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Quester.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Most Celestials don't ride horses, or wander alone, but some crusaders feel "
"the call to work abroad on their own. These celestials follow the 'quest' to "
"bring light to the world individually through works of valor. Knowing they "
"must travel great distances, they learn to ride horses, and adapt a lance "
"for devastating charge attacks. Although the quest is supposed to be an "
"individual thing, Questers have no problems grouping up with other people if "
"it helps them accomplish their task."
msgstr ""
"La mayoría de los celestiales no montan caballos ni viajan solos, pero "
"algunos cruzados sienten la llamada de actuar en el extranjero por su "
"cuenta. Estos celestiales siguen la «búsqueda» para llevar la luz al mundo "
"de forma individual mediante actos de valor. Sabiendo que deben recorrer "
"grandes distancias, aprenden a montar a caballo y adaptan una lanza para "
"devastadores ataques de carga. Aunque la búsqueda se supone que es algo "
"individual, los buscadores no tienen problema en unirse a otras personas si "
"eso les ayuda a cumplir su misión."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a2_Quester.cfg:55
msgid "Lance"
msgstr "Lanza"

#. [unit_type], id=Divine Champion, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a3_Divine_Champion.cfg:5
msgid "Divine Champion"
msgstr "Campeón Divino"

#. [unit_type], id=Divine Champion, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a3_Divine_Champion.cfg:18
msgid ""
"For a Knight to be recognized as a Champion he must first commit at least "
"two Great Deeds and have shown his form to be exceptional to other Knights "
"on the battle field. Champions are reguarded as highly as Messengers, if not "
"perhaps even higher."
msgstr ""
"Para que un caballero sea reconocido como campeón debe haber realizado al "
"menos dos Grandes Hazañas y haber demostrado en el campo de batalla ser "
"excepcional entre los demás caballeros. Los campeones son tan respetados "
"como los mensajeros, o quizá incluso más."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a3_Divine_Champion.cfg:50
msgid "Flail"
msgstr "Flagelo"

#. [unit_type], id=Holy Sentinel, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a3_Holy_Sentinel.cfg:5
msgid "Holy Sentinel"
msgstr "Centinela Sagrado"

#. [unit_type], id=Holy Sentinel, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/a3_Holy_Sentinel.cfg:18
msgid ""
"These crusaders hold the line with flaming sword, and great sheild. They are "
"famous for their ability to bash their way forward and then hold the ground "
"they just earned."
msgstr ""
"Estos cruzados mantienen la línea con espada llameante y gran escudo. Son "
"famosos por su capacidad de abrirse paso a golpes y luego mantener el "
"terreno que acaban de ganar."

#. [unit_type], id=Legionnaire, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b1_Legionnaire.cfg:5
msgid "Legionnaire"
msgstr "Legionario"

#. [unit_type], id=Legionnaire, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b1_Legionnaire.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Legionnaires are staunch defenders of the Celestial homelands. With "
"extensive studies in the arts of defensive combat, Legionnaires have good "
"physical resistancies."
msgstr ""
"Los legionarios son firmes defensores de las tierras celestiales. Gracias a "
"sus amplios estudios en las artes del combate defensivo, poseen buenas "
"resistencias físicas."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b1_Legionnaire.cfg:36
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b2_Keeper.cfg:35
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b3_Sentinel.cfg:36
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/wargs/b1_Stalker.cfg:27
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/wargs/b2_Shadow_Pelt.cfg:27
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/wargs/b3_Night_Eye.cfg:29
msgid "Spear"
msgstr "Lanza"

#. [unit_type], id=Keeper, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b2_Keeper.cfg:5
msgid "Keeper"
msgstr "Custodio"

#. [unit_type], id=Keeper, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b2_Keeper.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Keepers are staunch defenders of the Celestial homelands. With stout hearts, "
"and hardened skin they will hold till death or relief comes."
msgstr ""
"Los custodios son firmes defensores de las tierras celestiales. Con "
"corazones valientes y piel endurecida, resistirán hasta la muerte o hasta "
"que llegue el relevo."

#. [unit_type], id=Sentinel, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b3_Sentinel.cfg:5
msgid "Sentinel"
msgstr "Centinela"

#. [unit_type], id=Sentinel, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b3_Sentinel.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The great guardians of important celestials are called Sentinels, for their "
"silent, but imposing presence, and their complete immunity to boredom."
msgstr ""
"Los grandes guardianes de los celestiales importantes reciben el nombre de "
"centinelas por su presencia silenciosa pero imponente y por su completa "
"inmunidad al aburrimiento."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/b3_Sentinel.cfg:48
msgid "Javelin"
msgstr "Jabalina"

#. [unit_type], id=Light Spirit, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/c1_Light_Spirit.cfg:5
msgid "Light Spirit"
msgstr "Espíritu de Luz"

#. [unit_type], id=Light Spirit, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/c1_Light_Spirit.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Light Spirits are a breed of faeries who possess an aura of arcane energy "
"that infuses their entire body with a radiant light. They share their energy "
"with the Celestials in return for protection, and to some extent worship."
msgstr ""
"Los espíritus de luz son una raza de hadas que poseen un aura de energía "
"arcana que impregna todo su cuerpo con una luz radiante. Comparten su "
"energía con los celestiales a cambio de protección y, en cierta medida, "
"adoración."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/c1_Light_Spirit.cfg:76
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/c2_Lantern_Archon.cfg:75
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/c3_Master_of_Light.cfg:77
msgid "shock of light"
msgstr "descarga de luz"

#. [unit_type], id=Lantern Archon, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/c2_Lantern_Archon.cfg:5
msgid "Lantern Archon"
msgstr "Arconte Linterna"

#. [unit_type], id=Lantern Archon, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/c2_Lantern_Archon.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Lantern Archons are a breed of faeries who possess an aura of arcane energy "
"that infuses their entire body with a radiant light. Lantern Archons defend "
"themselves with powerful shocks of arcane energy at a distance; up close "
"they are quite defenseless."
msgstr ""
"Los arcontes linterna son una raza de hadas que poseen un aura de energía "
"arcana que impregna todo su cuerpo con una luz radiante. Los arcontes "
"linterna se defienden con poderosas descargas de energía arcana a distancia; "
"de cerca están bastante desprotegidos."

#. [unit_type], id=Master of Light, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/c3_Master_of_Light.cfg:5
msgid "Master of Light"
msgstr "Maestro de la Luz"

#. [unit_type], id=Master of Light, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/c3_Master_of_Light.cfg:24
msgid ""
"A faerie who exercises her output of arcane energy may master using it as a "
"weapon to such a degree that they are named Masters of Light."
msgstr ""
"Un hada que entrena su emisión de energía arcana puede dominar su uso como "
"arma hasta tal punto que recibe el nombre de maestro de la luz."

#. [unit_type], id=Messenger, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d1_Messenger.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Messengers are chosen as Celestial leaders for the simple and traditional "
"reason that their wings grow in adolescence rather than fall off or remain "
"vestigial. Unlike other Celestials, Messengers can fly over the battlefield "
"and give orders, granting a bonus to surrounding troops."
msgstr ""
"Los mensajeros son elegidos como líderes celestiales por la sencilla y "
"tradicional razón de que sus alas crecen en la adolescencia en lugar de "
"caerse o permanecer vestigiales. A diferencia de otros celestiales, los "
"mensajeros pueden volar sobre el campo de batalla y dar órdenes, otorgando "
"una bonificación a las tropas cercanas."

#. [female]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d1_Messenger.cfg:71
msgid "female^Messenger"
msgstr "Mensajera"

#. [unit_type], id=Claimant, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d2_Claimant.cfg:5
msgid "Claimant"
msgstr "Reclamante"

#. [unit_type], id=Claimant, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d2_Claimant.cfg:18
msgid ""
"All winged Celestials were once named Claimants. They were called this by "
"their bretheren in the beginning days of Celestial society as they claimed "
"to be the natural leaders of the Celestial people. Claimants now exclusively "
"write Celestial law, which Messengers then spread to the people."
msgstr ""
"Todos los celestiales alados fueron en su día llamados reclamantes. Sus "
"hermanos los llamaron así en los primeros días de la sociedad celestial "
"porque reclamaban ser los líderes naturales del pueblo celestial. Ahora los "
"reclamantes redactan exclusivamente la ley celestial, que luego los "
"mensajeros difunden entre el pueblo."

#. [female]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d2_Claimant.cfg:72
msgid "female^Claimant"
msgstr "Reclamante"

#. [unit_type], id=Celestial Herald, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d3_Herald.cfg:5
msgid "Herald"
msgstr "Heraldo"

#. [unit_type], id=Celestial Herald, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d3_Herald.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Heralds are the highest ranking officers, skilled with sword, and words they "
"inspire their troops to victory. They proclaim a message of hope to their "
"fellows, and a message of death to their foes."
msgstr ""
"Los heraldos son los oficiales de mayor rango, expertos con la espada y con "
"la palabra; inspiran a sus tropas hacia la victoria. Proclaman un mensaje de "
"esperanza a sus compañeros y un mensaje de muerte a sus enemigos."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d3_Herald.cfg:47
msgid "heavenly light"
msgstr "luz celestial"

#. [female]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d3_Herald.cfg:116
msgid "female^Herald"
msgstr "Heraldo"

#. [unit_type], id=Seraph, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d4_Seraphin.cfg:6
msgid "Seraph"
msgstr "Serafín"

#. [unit_type], id=Seraph, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d4_Seraphin.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Exalted is the title given to the mightiest of winged celestials. They are "
"honored to the point where they are no longer considered officers in the "
"army, but rather the manifestation of glory. Few  exist that fight with "
"greater strength, or with greater ability to inspire and lead."
msgstr ""
"Exaltado es el título que reciben los celestiales alados más poderosos. Son "
"honrados hasta el punto de que ya no se les considera oficiales del "
"ejército, sino la manifestación misma de la gloria. Pocos luchan con mayor "
"fuerza o con mayor capacidad para inspirar y liderar."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d4_Seraphin.cfg:39
msgid "sword of mercy"
msgstr "espada de misericordia"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d4_Seraphin.cfg:51
msgid "divine mandate"
msgstr "mandato divino"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d4_Seraphin.cfg:62
msgid "glimpse of heaven"
msgstr "atisbo del cielo"

#. [female]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/d4_Seraphin.cfg:132
msgid "female^Seraph"
msgstr "Serafina"

#. [unit_type], id=Celestial Wizard, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e1_Wizard.cfg:5
msgid "Acolyte"
msgstr "Acólito"

#. [unit_type], id=Celestial Wizard, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e1_Wizard.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Celestials who lose their vestigial wings in adolescence are not allowed to "
"fight in the military. As a result, they must undertake other endeavors. The "
"practice of magic is one of such endeavors. Originally used to create the "
"everglowing lights in Celestial towns using Holy energy, some Wizards have "
"harnessed magical powers for more militaristic purposes in order to join "
"their bretheren in battle. The Celestial Heralds have allowed them this "
"honor."
msgstr ""
"Los celestiales que pierden sus alas vestigiales en la adolescencia no "
"tienen permiso para combatir en el ejército. Por eso deben dedicarse a otras "
"actividades. La práctica de la magia es una de ellas. Originalmente se usaba "
"para crear las luces eternamente brillantes en los pueblos celestiales "
"mediante energía sagrada, pero algunos magos han canalizado poderes mágicos "
"con fines más militares para poder unirse a sus hermanos en batalla. Los "
"heraldos celestiales les han concedido ese honor."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e1_Wizard.cfg:28
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e2_Mystic.cfg:28
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e3_Prophet.cfg:29
msgid "Staff"
msgstr "Bastón"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e1_Wizard.cfg:37
msgid "flare"
msgstr "destello"

#. [unit_type], id=Great Wizard, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e2_Great_Wizard.cfg:5
msgid "Great Wizard"
msgstr "Gran Mago"

#. [unit_type], id=Great Wizard, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e2_Great_Wizard.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The wizards of the celestials have always harnessed the suns power for their "
"magic. Those who fight with the military for a while become adept at pulling "
"the suns power into rapid magical blasts."
msgstr ""
"Los magos celestiales siempre han aprovechado el poder del sol para su "
"magia. Aquellos que combaten con el ejército durante un tiempo se vuelven "
"expertos en canalizar el poder del sol en rápidas ráfagas mágicas."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e2_Great_Wizard.cfg:28
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e3_Sage.cfg:29
msgid "Hammer"
msgstr "Martillo"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e2_Great_Wizard.cfg:37
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e2_Mystic.cfg:37
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e3_Prophet.cfg:38
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e3_Sage.cfg:38
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Dragon_Ascendant.cfg:85
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Dragon_Sorceress.cfg:84
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Nature_Avatar.cfg:65
msgid "Lightning"
msgstr "Relámpago"

#. [unit_type], id=Mystic, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e2_Mystic.cfg:5
msgid "Mystic"
msgstr "Místico"

#. [unit_type], id=Mystic, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e2_Mystic.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Many celestial wizards focus on the study of spirits rather than raw sun "
"magic. These are known as mystics. Their skills in this area allow them to "
"aid the army in new ways."
msgstr ""
"Muchos magos celestiales se centran en el estudio de los espíritus más que "
"en la magia solar pura. A estos se les conoce como místicos. Sus habilidades "
"en esta área les permiten ayudar al ejército de nuevas maneras."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e2_Mystic.cfg:49
msgid "Lightbeam"
msgstr "Rayo de Luz"

#. [unit_type], id=Prophet, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e3_Prophet.cfg:5
msgid "Prophet"
msgstr "Profeta"

#. [unit_type], id=Prophet, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e3_Prophet.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Mystics who become skilled enough in their arts develop the strange ability "
"to foretell events. No one is certain how they do this or when any of the "
"things they say will happen, records have shone prophecies thousands of "
"years old coming true. These wizards are also deadly warriors in combat."
msgstr ""
"Los místicos que alcanzan suficiente destreza en sus artes desarrollan la "
"extraña capacidad de predecir eventos. Nadie sabe con certeza cómo lo hacen "
"ni cuándo ocurrirán las cosas que anuncian, pero los registros muestran "
"profecías de miles de años de antigüedad que se han cumplido. Estos magos "
"también son guerreros letales en combate."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e3_Prophet.cfg:50
msgid "divine lightning"
msgstr "relámpago divino"

#. [unit_type], id=Sage, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e3_Sage.cfg:5
msgid "Sage"
msgstr "Sabio"

#. [unit_type], id=Sage, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/e3_Sage.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The celestials believe the power of a wizard is not measured by his skill "
"with magic, but by his wisdom of it's use. A wizard who has achieved both "
"power and wisdom is known as a sage."
msgstr ""
"Los celestiales creen que el poder de un mago no se mide por su destreza "
"mágica, sino por la sabiduría con que la emplea. Un mago que ha alcanzado "
"tanto poder como sabiduría recibe el nombre de sabio."

#. [unit_type], id=Zealot, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f1_Zealot.cfg:5
msgid "Zealot"
msgstr "Fanático"

#. [unit_type], id=Zealot, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f1_Zealot.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The celestial society tends to breed people who would fearlessly battle with "
"no regard for their own life or family. More in fact than they can support "
"in their standing army. However if the armies go marching off, a crowd of "
"zealots will almost always follow, and the armies although not accepting "
"these into their ranks, do not deny them the chance to fight."
msgstr ""
"La sociedad celestial tiende a criar personas que lucharían sin temor alguno "
"sin importarles su propia vida o su familia. De hecho, más de los que pueden "
"mantener en su ejército permanente. Sin embargo, si los ejércitos marchan a "
"la guerra, casi siempre les sigue una multitud de fanáticos, y aunque los "
"ejércitos no los aceptan en sus filas, no les niegan la oportunidad de "
"luchar."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f1_Zealot.cfg:28
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f2_Militant.cfg:28
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f3_Sicarius.cfg:31
msgid "chakram slice"
msgstr "corte de chakram"

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f1_Zealot.cfg:37
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f2_Militant.cfg:37
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f3_Sicarius.cfg:40
msgid "chakram throw"
msgstr "lanzamiento de chakram"

#. [unit_type], id=Militant, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f2_Militant.cfg:5
msgid "Militant"
msgstr "Militante"

#. [unit_type], id=Militant, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f2_Militant.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The celestials have always had a very militant, and totalitarian mindset. "
"They believe that the battle with evil should be fought until it is over. As "
"a result there is no shortage of civilians who are willing to join and fight "
"for the army at a minutes notice. Some of them even practice in case such a "
"chance comes up."
msgstr ""
"Los celestiales siempre han tenido una mentalidad muy militante y "
"totalitaria. Creen que la batalla contra el mal debe librarse hasta que "
"termine. Como resultado, nunca faltan civiles dispuestos a unirse al "
"ejército y luchar en cuestión de minutos. Algunos incluso entrenan por si se "
"presenta la oportunidad."

#. [unit_type], id=Sicarius, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f3_Sicarius.cfg:7
msgid "Sicarius"
msgstr "Sicario"

#. [unit_type], id=Sicarius, race=celestial
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/celestials/f3_Sicarius.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Civilian warriors who have proven their worth time and time again, are "
"granted an honorary rank known as Sicarius. It is quite an honor in "
"Celestial society."
msgstr ""
"Los guerreros civiles que han demostrado su valía una y otra vez reciben el "
"rango honorario conocido como sicario. Es todo un honor en la sociedad "
"celestial."

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Charioteer, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Charioteer.cfg:5
msgid "Charioteer"
msgstr "Conductor de Carro"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Charioteer, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Charioteer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Hannuks have never been very familiar with sailing, and this proved to "
"be a problem at first, since horses could not transport great loads of game, "
"traded good or even people. They solved this problem by developing large, "
"resistant chariots drawn by two or more horses that could transport great "
"cargo; but it didn't take long until they found out that, by placing archers "
"on them, the chariots became deadly war machines. In spite of their low "
"speed and of the difficulty their archers have in hitting a target while "
"moving, charioteers are the favourite units for battles in which melee "
"combat is dominant."
msgstr ""
"Los hannuks nunca han sido muy amigos de la navegación, y eso supuso un "
"problema al principio, ya que los caballos no podían transportar grandes "
"cargas de caza, mercancías o personas. Resolvieron este problema "
"desarrollando grandes y resistentes carros tirados por dos o más caballos "
"que podían transportar grandes cargas; pero no tardaron en descubrir que, al "
"colocar arqueros en ellos, los carros se convertían en mortales máquinas de "
"guerra. A pesar de su baja velocidad y de la dificultad que tienen sus "
"arqueros para acertar a un blanco en movimiento, los conductores de carros "
"son las unidades favoritas en batallas donde domina el combate cuerpo a "
"cuerpo."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Charioteer.cfg:40
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Conqueror.cfg:39
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Scythe_Charioteer.cfg:52
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/War_Charioteer.cfg:53
msgid "trample"
msgstr "pisotear"

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Charioteer.cfg:51
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Forest_Bane.cfg:65
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Horse_Archer.cfg:38
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Mangudai.cfg:38
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Scythe_Charioteer.cfg:63
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Sharpshooter.cfg:59
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Tarkan.cfg:44
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Tarkyn_Tarkan.cfg:44
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/War_Charioteer.cfg:64
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Wood_Hunter.cfg:50
msgid "composite bow"
msgstr "arco compuesto"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Conqueror, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Conqueror.cfg:5
msgid "Conqueror"
msgstr "Conquistador"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Conqueror, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Conqueror.cfg:19
msgid ""
"After certain number of villages razed, most Raiders become known, and "
"consequently feared, all over the steppes, and sometimes even outside of "
"them. Their mere sight makes even the rulers of larger cities tremble, for "
"they know their beloved lands are about to be conquered and pillaged. The "
"Conquerors may be hated and despised by most of the Hannuks, but no one can "
"deny that it is thanks to them that the frontiers of the Hannuk nation have "
"expanded across the centuries."
msgstr ""
"Tras arrasar cierto número de aldeas, la mayoría de los saqueadores se "
"vuelven conocidos y, en consecuencia, temidos en todas las estepas y a veces "
"incluso fuera de ellas. Su mera visión hace temblar incluso a los "
"gobernantes de las ciudades más grandes, pues saben que sus queridas tierras "
"están a punto de ser conquistadas y saqueadas. Los conquistadores pueden ser "
"odiados y despreciados por la mayoría de los hannuks, pero nadie puede negar "
"que gracias a ellos las fronteras de la nación hannuk se han expandido a lo "
"largo de los siglos."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Conqueror.cfg:30
msgid "battle axe"
msgstr "hacha de batalla"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Conqueror.cfg:50
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Raider.cfg:40
msgid "torch"
msgstr "antorcha"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Forest Bane, race=hannuk, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Forest_Bane.cfg:5
msgid "Forest Bane"
msgstr "Pesadilla del Bosque"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Forest Bane, race=hannuk, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Forest_Bane.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The Hannuks' unfamiliarity with the forest have made way for many legends "
"about beings and spirits that dwell in them. One of these legends tells of "
"the Forest Bane, a vicious spirit that never fails to kill a prey that has "
"caught its eye. Thus, the fact that the most skilled and experienced female "
"hunters have been compared to those legendary spirits is a sign of their "
"prowess.\n"
"        \n"
"Even so, some of them disdain this name, claiming that, unlike the spirit, "
"they are equally deadly on any terrain."
msgstr ""
"La poca familiaridad de los hannuk con el bosque ha dado lugar a muchas "
"leyendas sobre seres y espíritus que habitan en ellos. Una de estas leyendas "
"habla de la Pesadilla del Bosque, un espíritu feroz que nunca falla al matar "
"a una presa que ha captado su atención. Por tanto, que las cazadoras más "
"hábiles y experimentadas hayan sido comparadas con esos espíritus "
"legendarios es señal de su destreza.\n"
"\n"
"Aun así, algunas de ellas desdeñan este nombre, afirmando que, a diferencia "
"del espíritu, ellas son igual de letales en cualquier terreno."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Forest_Bane.cfg:33
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Forest_Bane.cfg:42
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Horse_Archer.cfg:29
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Sharpshooter.cfg:27
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Sharpshooter.cfg:36
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Wood_Hunter.cfg:27
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Ancient_Banner_Ravyan.cfg:46
msgid "scythe"
msgstr "guadaña"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Forest_Bane.cfg:54
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Sharpshooter.cfg:48
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Wood_Hunter.cfg:39
msgid "bolas"
msgstr "bolas"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Great Shaman, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Great_Shaman.cfg:5
msgid "Great Shaman"
msgstr "Gran Chamán"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Great Shaman, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Great_Shaman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Although they do not rule any clan directly, the Great Shamans are the "
"highest authority amongst the Hannuk: theirs is the last word in settling "
"disputes between different clans and in taking decisions that will affect "
"the Hannuk nation as a whole; they preserve the people's history and lore, "
"and are responsible for organizing the major religious ceremonies; they are "
"the only ones who can organize the Golden Horde of the Hannuks; also, they "
"can determine the destruction of an entire clan if it is deemed, and proved, "
"to be nocive to the integrity of the Hannuk nation. As if it wasn't enough, "
"they have an extensive knowledge of the herbs that may be found over the "
"steppes (some of which are poisonous and used in their staffs) and also are "
"the only ones allowed to learn and practice the primitive, but lethal, "
"Hannuk magic. With all this power, it comes as no surprise that they are "
"both feared and respected by every member of the steppe society."
msgstr ""
"Aunque no gobiernan directamente ningún clan, los grandes chamanes son la "
"máxima autoridad entre los hannuks: suya es la última palabra en la "
"resolución de disputas entre clanes y en la toma de decisiones que afecten a "
"la nación hannuk en su conjunto; preservan la historia y el saber del pueblo "
"y son responsables de organizar las grandes ceremonias religiosas; son los "
"únicos que pueden organizar la Horda Dorada de los hannuks; también pueden "
"decretar la destrucción de un clan entero si se considera y se demuestra que "
"es perjudicial para la integridad de la nación hannuk. Como si fuera poco, "
"poseen un amplio conocimiento de las hierbas que se encuentran en las "
"estepas (algunas venenosas y usadas en sus bastones) y son los únicos "
"autorizados a aprender y practicar la primitiva pero letal magia hannuk. Con "
"todo este poder, no sorprende que sean tanto temidos como respetados por "
"todos los miembros de la sociedad de las estepas."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Great_Shaman.cfg:43
msgid "curse"
msgstr "maldición"

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Great_Shaman.cfg:56
msgid "steppe chill"
msgstr "frío de la estepa"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Horse Archer, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Horse_Archer.cfg:5
msgid "Horse Archer"
msgstr "Arquero a Caballo"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Horse Archer, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Horse_Archer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"In the Hannuk culture, horse-riding is considered essential for any member "
"of the society. Many prefer staying on their feet, or using chariots, but "
"others remain on horseback, developing a real friendship with their own "
"horses. They also seek to perfect the difficult art of horse-archery that is "
"like a signature of the Hannuks. Horse Archers are mainly hunters, armed "
"with powerful composite bows and scythes to eviscerate their game; "
"nevertheless, they have more than once unbalanced a battle in favour of "
"their own side, and are feared by their enemies for their speed and for the "
"range of their bows."
msgstr ""
"En la cultura hannuk, montar a caballo se considera esencial para cualquier "
"miembro de la sociedad. Muchos prefieren permanecer a pie o usar carros, "
"pero otros permanecen a caballo, desarrollando una verdadera amistad con sus "
"propios caballos. También buscan perfeccionar el difícil arte del tiro con "
"arco a caballo que es como la firma de los hannuks. Los arqueros a caballo "
"son principalmente cazadores, armados con poderosos arcos compuestos y "
"guadañas para destripar su presa; sin embargo, más de una vez han "
"desequilibrado una batalla a favor de su bando y son temidos por sus "
"enemigos por su velocidad y el alcance de sus arcos."

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Mangudai, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Mangudai.cfg:5
msgid "Mangudai"
msgstr "Mangudai"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Mangudai, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Mangudai.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Not all horse archers manage to go much beyond their own rank and skill; "
"those who do, however, are admired by his kinsmen as the embodiment of the "
"Hannuks' ideal warrior: man and horse move across the steppes like a single "
"body, and the former's archery skill is superior to that of most foot "
"bowmen. Armed no longer with mere scythes, but with sharp swords, they are "
"called the Mangudai, which means, in the Hannuk language, 'Wind of Death', a "
"name that testifies both their speed and deadliness."
msgstr ""
"No todos los arqueros a caballo logran ir mucho más allá de su propio rango "
"y habilidad; los que sí lo hacen, sin embargo, son admirados por sus "
"parientes como la encarnación del guerrero ideal hannuk: hombre y caballo se "
"mueven por las estepas como un solo cuerpo, y la habilidad con el arco del "
"primero es superior a la de la mayoría de los arqueros a pie. Ya no armados "
"con simples guadañas, sino con afiladas espadas, se les llama mangudai, que "
"en lengua hannuk significa «Viento de Muerte», un nombre que da fe de su "
"velocidad y letalidad."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Mangudai.cfg:29
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Tarkan.cfg:35
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Tarkyn_Tarkan.cfg:35
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Captain_Ravyan.cfg:38
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Greatbow_Jevyan.cfg:64
msgid "sword"
msgstr "espada"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Raider, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Raider.cfg:5
msgid "Raider"
msgstr "Saqueador"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Raider, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Raider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Horse-archery is a difficult art, and therefore, not for everyone. Those who "
"do not see a bright future with the bow and the arrow, but isn't willing to "
"get off horseback either, choose a different set of weapons. Unlike the "
"Mangudai, who are mostly hunters, the Raiders are fully dedicated to "
"warfare: armed with blades and torches, they mercilessly burn any village "
"that stands on their way. Because of their violence, they are despised by "
"most Hannuks, but are nevertheless employed by all chieftains who want to "
"completely destroy their enemies.\n"
"        \n"
"Because they are more heavily armoured, they are slower than most horse-"
"riders; and, though their lack of the bow makes them vulnerable to ranged "
"attacks, they are extremely deadly in melee combat."
msgstr ""
"El tiro con arco a caballo es un arte difícil y, por tanto, no apto para "
"todos. Quienes no ven un futuro brillante con el arco y la flecha, pero "
"tampoco están dispuestos a bajar del caballo, eligen un conjunto diferente "
"de armas. A diferencia de los mangudai, que son principalmente cazadores, "
"los saqueadores se dedican por completo a la guerra: armados con cuchillas y "
"antorchas, queman sin piedad cualquier aldea que se cruza en su camino. "
"Debido a su violencia, son despreciados por la mayoría de los hannuk, pero "
"aun así son empleados por todos los jefes que quieren destruir completamente "
"a sus enemigos.\n"
"\n"
"Al ir más pesadamente armados, son más lentos que la mayoría de los jinetes; "
"y aunque la falta del arco los hace vulnerables a los ataques a distancia, "
"son extremadamente letales en combate cuerpo a cuerpo."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Raider.cfg:31
msgid "axe"
msgstr "hacha"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Scythe Charioteer, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Scythe_Charioteer.cfg:5
msgid "Scythe Charioteer"
msgstr "Carro Guadaña"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Scythe Charioteer, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Scythe_Charioteer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A problem noticed by charioteers when going to battle was that, though "
"anyone who stood in front of the vehicle was trampled, the flanks of the "
"chariot were a huge weakness. Enemies, of course, noticed that too, and "
"constantly got near the vehicle, taking advantage of the fact that the "
"archers were busy hitting faraway targets, and stabbed them from below. To "
"solve this problem, the Hannuks installed sharp, long and curved blades all "
"over the chariot's sides. This kept enemies at a safer distance, but could "
"also be used to hack enemies who tried to hijack the vehicle while it was "
"moving. If you come across a battlefield and see a great number of severed "
"heads and limbs and slashed torsos, know that Scythe Chariots have fought "
"there."
msgstr ""
"Un problema que notaron los conductores de carros al entrar en batalla era "
"que, aunque cualquiera que se pusiera delante del vehículo era pisoteado, "
"los flancos del carro eran una enorme debilidad. Los enemigos, por supuesto, "
"también lo notaron y se acercaban constantemente al vehículo aprovechando "
"que los arqueros estaban ocupados disparando a objetivos lejanos y los "
"apuñalaban desde abajo. Para solucionar este problema, los hannuks "
"instalaron afiladas, largas y curvas cuchillas por todo el lateral del "
"carro. Esto mantenía a los enemigos a una distancia más segura, pero también "
"podía usarse para cortar en pedazos a los enemigos que intentaran tomar el "
"vehículo en marcha. Si te encuentras en un campo de batalla y ves gran "
"cantidad de cabezas y extremidades cortadas y torsos destrozados, sabe que "
"allí han combatido carros guadaña."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Scythe_Charioteer.cfg:40
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/War_Charioteer.cfg:41
msgid "scythes"
msgstr "guadañas"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Sharpshooter, race=hannuk, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Sharpshooter.cfg:5
msgid "Sharpshooter"
msgstr "Tiradora de Élite"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Sharpshooter, race=hannuk, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Sharpshooter.cfg:18
msgid ""
"When the Doe Clan allowed their women to do activities formerly banned to "
"them, many Hannuks, even from that clan, were skeptical that they would "
"succeed in any of them, and would quickly return to their old domestic "
"tasks. However, some Wood Hunters have managed to prove that they had skills "
"beyond those they had learned as little girls. After much practice in the "
"dark of the woods, they refined their archery skills to a level higher than "
"that of many male archers, successfully hunting game formerly considered "
"nearly impossible to kill, such as wild boars. Additionally, months of "
"constant running through the forests' irregular terrain, climbing on trees "
"and bending the composite bow have strenghtened these women, rendering their "
"blows and shots more deadly."
msgstr ""
"Cuando el Clan de la Cierva permitió a sus mujeres realizar actividades que "
"antes les estaban prohibidas, muchos hannuks, incluso del mismo clan, "
"dudaban que tuvieran éxito en alguna de ellas y que pronto volverían a sus "
"antiguas tareas domésticas. Sin embargo, algunas cazadoras del bosque han "
"logrado demostrar que tenían habilidades más allá de las que aprendieron de "
"niñas. Tras mucho entrenamiento en la oscuridad del bosque, refinaron sus "
"habilidades con el arco hasta un nivel superior al de muchos arqueros "
"varones, cazando con éxito presas que antes se consideraban casi imposibles "
"de abatir, como jabalíes salvajes. Además, meses de correr constantemente "
"por el terreno irregular del bosque, trepar a los árboles y tensar el arco "
"compuesto han fortalecido a estas mujeres, haciendo sus golpes y disparos "
"más mortales."

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Tarkan, race=hannuk
#. [unit_type], id=Tarkyn_Tarkan, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Tarkan.cfg:5
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Tarkyn_Tarkan.cfg:5
msgid "Tarkan"
msgstr "Tarkan"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Tarkan, race=hannuk
#. [unit_type], id=Tarkyn_Tarkan, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Tarkan.cfg:19
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Tarkyn_Tarkan.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The Mangudai are considered by most Hannuks as the peak of human horse-"
"archery: the best of them are only slightly quicker, or stronger, or more "
"dexterous than the average Mangudai. Thus, when any of them show a notably "
"higher level of prowess, he is called 'Tarkan', which means 'master', and is "
"held almost as a living legend: other horse archers look up to him in awe, "
"young women dream of marrying him, peasants obey him without thinking twice. "
"Thus, it comes as no surprise that Tarkans are often seen as the head of "
"isolated villages, or at the forefront of large armies; watching one thunder "
"across the steppes, taking down game and enemy alike with otherwordly ease, "
"it is not hard to understand why few nations dare fight the Hannuks on their "
"own territory."
msgstr ""
"Los mangudai son considerados por la mayoría de los hannuks como la cima del "
"tiro con arco a caballo humano: los mejores solo son ligeramente más "
"rápidos, más fuertes o más diestros que el mangudai promedio. Por eso, "
"cuando alguno de ellos muestra un nivel de proeza notablemente superior, se "
"le llama «tarkan», que significa «maestro», y se le considera casi una "
"leyenda viviente: otros arqueros a caballo lo admiran con reverencia, las "
"jóvenes sueñan con casarse con él, los campesinos le obedecen sin pensarlo "
"dos veces. Por eso no sorprende que los tarkanes suelan verse como jefes de "
"aldeas aisladas o al frente de grandes ejércitos; ver a uno galopando por "
"las estepas, derribando caza y enemigos con facilidad sobrenatural, hace "
"fácil entender por qué pocas naciones se atreven a enfrentarse a los hannuks "
"en su propio territorio."

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk War Charioteer, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/War_Charioteer.cfg:5
msgid "War Charioteer"
msgstr "Carro de Guerra"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk War Charioteer, race=hannuk
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/War_Charioteer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Clad in iron plates, with reinforced wheels and drawn by the strongest and "
"sturdiest horses in all of the steppes, the War Chariots are nearly "
"invincible juggernauts; its mere sight is enough to make many enemies flee "
"the battlefield, and those who stay are either crushed mercilessly under the "
"vehicle's weight, hacked to pieces by the scythes all over its flanks, or "
"pierced by volleys of arrows shot by seasoned archers."
msgstr ""
"Cubiertos de placas de hierro, con ruedas reforzadas y tirados por los "
"caballos más fuertes y resistentes de todas las estepas, los carros de "
"guerra son casi invencibles; su mera visión basta para hacer huir a muchos "
"enemigos del campo de batalla, y los que se quedan son aplastados sin piedad "
"bajo el peso del vehículo, hechos pedazos por las guadañas de sus flancos o "
"atravesados por andanadas de flechas disparadas por arqueros expertos."

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Wood Hunter, race=hannuk, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Wood_Hunter.cfg:5
msgid "Wood Hunter"
msgstr "Cazadora del Bosque"

#. [unit_type], id=Hannuk Wood Hunter, race=hannuk, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/hannuks/Wood_Hunter.cfg:18
msgid ""
"In Hannuk society, women are relegated to domestic tasks, such as taking "
"care of the house, weaving, crafting and childcare. However, the women of "
"the Doe Clan have decided to break this tradition, and learned archery and "
"hunting skills. Because the horse was still forbidden to them for religious "
"reasons, they developed a tool with which they could slow down their prey, "
"and it proved to be highly effective not only against game, but also, as "
"they have recently noticed, against human enemies. Furthermore, because the "
"steppes were already dominated by horse-riders, they started hunting in the "
"woods, where horses have never fared well."
msgstr ""
"En la sociedad hannuk, las mujeres están relegadas a tareas domésticas como "
"cuidar la casa, tejer, fabricar y cuidar niños. Sin embargo, las mujeres del "
"Clan de la Cierva han decidido romper con esta tradición y han aprendido "
"habilidades de tiro con arco y caza. Como el caballo todavía les estaba "
"prohibido por razones religiosas, desarrollaron una herramienta con la que "
"podían ralentizar a sus presas, y resultó ser muy efectiva no solo contra la "
"caza, sino también, como han notado recientemente, contra enemigos humanos. "
"Además, como las estepas ya estaban dominadas por jinetes, comenzaron a "
"cazar en los bosques, donde los caballos nunca se han desenvuelto bien."

#. [unit_type], id=Abhai Ancient Banner, race=aragwaith
#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Ancient Banner Ravyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Abhai_Ancient_Banner.cfg:5
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Ancient_Banner_Ravyan.cfg:5
msgid "Ancient Banner"
msgstr "Estandarte Ancestral"

#. [unit_type], id=Abhai Ancient Banner, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Abhai_Ancient_Banner.cfg:28
msgid ""
"What little is known about the past of the Aragwaithi is told through oral "
"history by their wise women. These are tales of an ancient, lost homeland, "
"of devastating wars and deeds of heroism from ages barely remembered even by "
"elves; tales enshrouded in legend and myth.\n"
"\n"
"But not only through their oral memory does the history of the Aragwaithi "
"survive the ages. For the older lineages of their people are careful to "
"preserve the memory of their ancestors - and nowhere is that memory better "
"preserved than on the banners of their oldest dynasties. These are banners "
"brought from their ancient homeland, banners under which the greatest deeds "
"of the Aragwaithi people were achieved, and in whose threads are engraved "
"the proofs of their old glories.\n"
"\n"
"Such banners may only be carried onto the battlefield by the strongest, "
"bravest and most renowned warrior, and the sight of one of them billowing in "
"the winds is enough to fill those rallied around it with the valour of "
"countless generations."
msgstr ""
"Lo poco que se sabe del pasado de los aragwaithi se transmite a través de la "
"historia oral por sus mujeres sabias. Son cuentos de una patria antigua y "
"perdida, de guerras devastadoras y hazañas heroicas de eras apenas "
"recordadas incluso por los elfos; cuentos envueltos en leyenda y mito.\n"
"\n"
"Pero la historia de los aragwaithi no sobrevive a los siglos solo a través "
"de su memoria oral. Las estirpes más antiguas de su pueblo cuidan de "
"preservar el recuerdo de sus antepasados, y en ningún lugar está mejor "
"preservado ese recuerdo que en los estandartes de sus dinastías más "
"antiguas. Son estandartes traídos de su patria ancestral, bajo los cuales se "
"lograron las mayores hazañas del pueblo aragwaith, y en cuyos hilos están "
"grabadas las pruebas de sus antiguas glorias.\n"
"\n"
"Tales estandartes solo pueden ser llevados al campo de batalla por el "
"guerrero más fuerte, valiente y renombrado, y la vista de uno de ellos "
"ondeando al viento es suficiente para llenar de valor de innumerables "
"generaciones a quienes se agrupan a su alrededor."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Abhai_Ancient_Banner.cfg:41
msgid "Banner of Maethar"
msgstr "Estandarte de Maethar"

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Abhai_Ancient_Banner.cfg:49
msgid "white tiger's claw"
msgstr "garra del tigre blanco"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Abhai_Ancient_Banner.cfg:58
msgid "Rod of Justice"
msgstr "Vara de la Justicia"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Ancient Banner Ravyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Ancient_Banner_Ravyan.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Some great Aragwaithi officiers bring on the battlefield the flags of their "
"ancients. These Ancient Banners are skilled and deadly veterans, who have "
"leaded troops in the cruelest battles of the Aragwaithi."
msgstr ""
"Algunos grandes oficiales aragwaithi llevan al campo de batalla las banderas "
"de sus antepasados. Estos estandartes ancestrales son veteranos hábiles y "
"letales que han liderado tropas en las batallas más cruentas de los "
"aragwaithi."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Ancient_Banner_Ravyan.cfg:38
msgid "Banner of the Aracynes"
msgstr "Estandarte de los Aracinos"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Captain Ravyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Captain_Ravyan.cfg:5
msgid "Captain"
msgstr "Capitán"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Captain Ravyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Captain_Ravyan.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Aragwaithi captains lead the troops on the battlefield and are known as the "
"best human officers existing: they can predict the enemy tactics and nullify "
"their strategies."
msgstr ""
"Los capitanes aragwaithi lideran las tropas en el campo de batalla y son "
"conocidos como los mejores oficiales humanos existentes: pueden predecir las "
"tácticas enemigas y anular sus estrategias."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Captain_Ravyan.cfg:30
msgid "spear"
msgstr "lanza"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Flagbearer Ravyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Flagbearer_Ravyan.cfg:5
msgid "Flagbearer"
msgstr "Abanderado"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Flagbearer Ravyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Flagbearer_Ravyan.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Only the bravest and strongest soldiers have the great honour to bring the "
"Aragwaithi flag on the battlefield. These warriors, called flagbearers, have "
"been trained at sword and spear and represent a serious threat to the "
"enemies of the Aragwaithi."
msgstr ""
"Solo los soldados más valientes y fuertes tienen el gran honor de llevar la "
"bandera aragwaith al campo de batalla. Estos guerreros, llamados "
"abanderados, han sido entrenados con espada y lanza y representan una seria "
"amenaza para los enemigos de los aragwaithi."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Flagbearer_Ravyan.cfg:31
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Slayer_Jevyan.cfg:34
msgid "glaive"
msgstr "guadaña"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Greatbow Jevyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Greatbow_Jevyan.cfg:5
msgid "Greatbow"
msgstr "Gran Arco"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Greatbow Jevyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Greatbow_Jevyan.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Finally moving on from the dirk and dagger to the sword, the Greatbow is "
"superior to the Strongbow in melee combat, but not as powerful as the "
"Slayer. Their bow, however, is a masterpiece of military design. Several "
"months are spent crafting a single bow, and each bow is crafted by the user, "
"to his individual specifications. Due to the incredible strength required to "
"pull these bows, anyone but the crafter who attempts to draw it could suffer "
"serious injury."
msgstr ""
"Pasando finalmente del puñal y la daga a la espada, el gran arco es superior "
"al arco fuerte en combate cuerpo a cuerpo, pero no tan poderoso como el "
"matador. Sin embargo, su arco es una obra maestra del diseño militar. Se "
"pasan varios meses fabricando un solo arco, y cada arco es creado por el "
"propio usuario según sus especificaciones individuales. Debido a la "
"increíble fuerza necesaria para tensar estos arcos, cualquiera que no sea su "
"creador que intente usarlos podría sufrir lesiones graves."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Greatbow_Jevyan.cfg:73
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Slayer_Jevyan.cfg:46
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Nature_Weaver.cfg:63
msgid "bow"
msgstr "arco"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Slayer Jevyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Slayer_Jevyan.cfg:5
msgid "Slayer"
msgstr "Matador"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Slayer Jevyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Slayer_Jevyan.cfg:27
msgid ""
"While improving only marginally on the power of their bow, the Slayer "
"abandons the blade in favor of training with a glaive, improving his skills "
"in hand-to-hand combat. He is not as rugged as others of comparable skill, "
"but far deadlier."
msgstr ""
"Aunque solo mejora marginalmente el poder de su arco, el matador abandona la "
"espada en favor del entrenamiento con una guadaña, mejorando sus habilidades "
"en combate cuerpo a cuerpo. No es tan resistente como otros de habilidad "
"comparable, pero es mucho más letal."

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Strongbow Jevyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Strongbow_Jevyan.cfg:5
msgid "Strongbow"
msgstr "Arco Fuerte"

#. [unit_type], id=Aragwaith Strongbow Jevyan, race=aragwaith
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-aragwaith/Aragwaith_Strongbow_Jevyan.cfg:17
msgid ""
"By wielding a stronger bow and training almost constantly, the Aragwaith "
"Strongbow fires a far deadlier shot than the average archer. Their dirks are "
"longer than the daggers used by the typical archer, and they wield them far "
"more effectively."
msgstr ""
"Al usar un arco más fuerte y entrenar casi constantemente, el arco fuerte "
"aragwaith dispara un tiro mucho más letal que el arquero promedio. Sus "
"puñales son más largos que las dagas usadas por el arquero típico, y los "
"manejan con mucha mayor efectividad."

#. [unit_type], id=Akashia Heretic, race=windsong, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Akashia_Heretic.cfg:5
msgid "female^Heretic"
msgstr "Hereje"

#. [unit_type], id=Akashia Heretic, race=windsong, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Akashia_Heretic.cfg:36
msgid ""
"The Windsong Council preaches the importance of patience and pacifism, that "
"one should not give in to anger and instead think carefully about every "
"decision. It is this belief that has kept the Windsong out of conflict for "
"so long.\n"
"\n"
"There is a faction, however, that believes that the balance of the world can "
"only be brought about by action, and thus espouses a more active role for "
"the Windsong, pushing constantly for war and the expansion of the Windsong's "
"influence in the outside world.  Though they are known as Heretics, their "
"opinions are nonetheless valued, and those Gatekeepers who follow the "
"philosophy are allowed to train themselves in the forbidden arts of "
"swordplay and ancient fire magic."
msgstr ""
"El Consejo de las Hijas del Viento predica la importancia de la paciencia y "
"el pacifismo, que no se debe ceder a la ira y que hay que pensar "
"cuidadosamente cada decisión. Esta creencia es la que ha mantenido a las "
"Hijas del Viento alejadas del conflicto durante tanto tiempo.\n"
"\n"
"Sin embargo, existe una facción que cree que el equilibrio del mundo solo "
"puede alcanzarse mediante la acción, y por tanto defiende un papel más "
"activo para las Hijas del Viento, presionando constantemente por la guerra y "
"la expansión de su influencia en el mundo exterior. Aunque se les conoce "
"como herejes, sus opiniones son valoradas, y a las guardianas de los "
"portales que siguen esta filosofía se les permite entrenarse en las artes "
"prohibidas de la esgrima y la antigua magia de fuego."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Akashia_Heretic.cfg:42
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Akashia_Warmonger.cfg:50
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Akashia_Warmonger.cfg:62
msgid "Deva Sword"
msgstr "Espada Deva"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Akashia_Heretic.cfg:54
msgid "fireball"
msgstr "bola de fuego"

#. [unit_type], id=AkashiaWarmonger, race=windsong, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Akashia_Warmonger.cfg:5
msgid "female^Warmonger"
msgstr "Belicista"

#. [unit_type], id=AkashiaWarmonger, race=windsong, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Akashia_Warmonger.cfg:46
msgid ""
"Stunningly powerful warriors, Harbingers epitomize the warlike path of the "
"Heretic. Their command of the forbidden flame cipher, as well as the "
"bloodthirsty furor they unleash upon their opponents, make them the terror "
"of their allies as much as of their enemies. Yet even the peaceful Windsong "
"realize that such power must be put to use, and they are often selected to "
"lead groups of their fellow Heretics into battle."
msgstr ""
"Guerreras impresionantemente poderosas, las Belicistas encarnan el camino "
"bélico de las herejes. Su dominio del cifrado de llamas prohibido, así como "
"el furor sanguinario que desatan sobre sus oponentes, las convierten en el "
"terror tanto de sus aliados como de sus enemigos. Aun así, incluso las "
"pacíficas Hijas del Viento reconocen que tal poder debe ser utilizado, y a "
"menudo son seleccionadas para liderar grupos de sus compañeras herejes en "
"batalla."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Akashia_Warmonger.cfg:76
msgid "sunburst"
msgstr "estallido solar"

#. [unit_type], id=Dragon Ascendant, race=windsong, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Dragon_Ascendant.cfg:5
msgid "female^Dragon Ascendant"
msgstr "Ascendiente Dragón"

#. [unit_type], id=Dragon Ascendant, race=windsong, gender=female
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Dragon_Ascendant.cfg:27
msgid ""
"The Dragon Ascendant has reached the pinnacle of her own power; merging both "
"traditional Windsong magic with her own peculiar techniques, she can easily "
"be counted amongst the mightiest beings ever to walk on Irdya."
msgstr ""
"La Ascendiente Dragón ha alcanzado la cima de su propio poder; fusionando la "
"magia tradicional de las Hijas del Viento con sus propias técnicas "
"peculiares, puede considerarse fácilmente entre los seres más poderosos que "
"jamás hayan caminado por Irdya."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Dragon_Ascendant.cfg:73
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Dragon_Sorceress.cfg:72
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Nature_Avatar.cfg:53
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Nature_Avatar_Extreme.cfg:53
msgid "Trident of the Seas"
msgstr "Tridente de los Mares"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#. [effect]
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Dragon_Ascendant.cfg:97
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Dragon_Sorceress.cfg:96
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/utils/character-utils.cfg:86
msgid "Degeneration"
msgstr "Degeneración"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: wesnoth-A_Song_of_Fire/units/heroes-windsong/Dragon_Ascendant.cfg:111
